      <name>South London</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>🟢410

https://web.archive.org/web/20120423225918/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/south-london-gangs/oc-organised-crime-one-chance-out-creamin</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X6tBzmt_Axu-Qv9BQkQjBpUNpRqAH87x_NrPCYpGncqwckSxqdHYY8NRRAxU-YMklB30l2FnrqRagbHhsqmx5jKLWSYRstQNxglYwr_D2RIxzkmejS39cRzBzbPnEpUi1vZ2FbL2ur8IunEPL_u0IXg5jVNTtplgYL35mO_q6ZRQDWe4oSHfMIiOHbbtGkBQaGp3Ko?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Lambeth, Brixton, Myatts Field SW9<br><br>410 are a large street gang based on the Myatts Field estate and the nearby Cowley and Church Manor estates in Brixton within the SW9 postcode. The Myatts Fields area is referred to as 'Baghdad' and 'Fields' whilst the 410 gang also refer to themselves as "Crash Gang" (CG).  410 formed around 2012 as a younger generation of an older gang known as OC. Like their predecessors, they identify with the colour green.<br><br>OC, which had primarily stood for 'Organised Crime' but also 'Out Creamin' and 'One Chance' were a large gang formed by members of another gang known as the 'Nastie Squad' (NS) in 2003. The 'Nastie Squad' (NS) were active in the 1990s to early 2000s. They were originally from the Myatts Field area of Brixton.  A younger generation, known as 'Younger Nastie Squad' (YNS) were drawn from a larger area, including Tulse Hill and West Norwood. The members from the Myatts Field Cowley and Vassall Road estates created OC in 2003.  Older members of the 'Nastie Squad' (NS)  were affiliated with the 'South Man Syndicate' (SMS) as were olders of the OC gang who followed. There was tension between NS and PDC, with NS members being more aligned to PDC rivals the Peckham Boys. This meant there was also tension between OC olders and PDC. <br><br>OC olders never really got on with PDC,  who were the other main Brixton gang,  in their early days and were at one time more aligned with Stockwell. However, as with many gangs rivalries and alliances can be subject to change throughout the different generations.  On some levels there were loose alliances between members of the ABM and OC gangs, but this had altered somewhat within the youngest generations of OC. Some OC olders also have affiliations with Peckham Boys, however by the late 2000s the younger generations of OC were in conflict with Peckham. The younger generations of OC were known as 'Younger OC' and 'Tiny OC'. During the late 2000s, around late 2007/08 'Tiny OC' linked up with the youngest generations from Angell Town and Loughborough (Y.28s) and Somerleyton (MZ) to form 'GAS Gang'. GAS had stood for ‘Grind And Stack’ and ‘Guns And Shanks’ and ‘Grip And Shoot’. GAS had originally identified with the colours of green for Myatts Field and purple for Angell Town.  Younger OC members had repped both OC and GAS, whilst the older members had only repped OC. The younger OC generations were affiliated with Brixton gangs, including  GAS, SIRU and RSG, as well as 'Brooklyn' from Old Kent Road and 031 from Stockwell. They came into conflict with the 'Peckham Boys', ABM (Stockwell), BYM (Kennington) and TN1 (Tulse Hill).  <br><br>By the early 2010s many of the OC main leaders had left the road, and the beef with Peckham had died. It was like an old era had ended, and a new era was beginning. The OC gangs main territory of Myatts Fields was also undergoing a major regeneration,  with the estates old blocks being replaced by modern apartments. These changes were the inspiration for the gang changing the gang name from OC to 410 (four-ten) around 2012/13.  Myatts Fields was being renamed as 'Oval Quarter' so the members took O¼ (Oval Quarter) and flipped it to became 4/10. In the mid 2010s 410 had become one of the most popular 'UK Drill' groups and pioneers of the genre alongside fellow Brixton groups, like 150 and 67. Their main allies are nearby 150, 17, 031, 37, Claptown and Uptop. They beef Harlem, KuKu, Moscow17, ABM, 674, RP and LTH. They also come into conflict with former allies SIRU.<br><br>Associated Rappers} AM / Skengdo / BT / Rendo / TS / SMoney / Lil Rass]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-7CB342-2801-77</styleUrl>
