e shot dead during 2004/2005. One of those killed was Solomon Martin known as "Blacker". The closest friends and family of "Blacker", including PDC rapper "Shak Corleone", disbanded from PDC and formed a new set known as CFR. CFR is interpreted as either 'Corleone Family Riderz' or the 'Certified Riderz', and were later adopted under the umbrella of the 031 Bloods who had been started by yet another former PDC member, "Tanna". Through close family connections (Ratlin Corleone), the 'Mozart Bloods' (HRB), in West London, are sometimes referred to as the Mozart CFR. CFR were closely linked with another street gang formed by former PDC members, known as 'Paid In Full' (PIF). PIF were primarily based around Angell Town and Loughborough and identified with the colour of purple. By 2005/2006 several of PDC elders began to move into more legitimate businesses, with their PDC acronym becoming more commonly referred to as 'Poverty Driven Children', or 'Pray Days Change' to now reflect the more positive nature of their group, or now more suitably "movement", with a focus on the music industry as an outlet for their energy.<br><br>During 2007/08 the youngest generation from Angell Town, known as the 'Y.28s' (not to be confused with the Y.28s that preceded PDC) began to form friendships with neighbouring Brixton gangs such as 'Tiny OC' from Myatts Fields and also 'Murderzone' (MZ) from Somerleyton. The Y28s and Tiny OC had inherited a fierce rivalry with the Peckham based gangs and decided that the Brixton gangs needed to unite together as one. The youngest generations from Angell Town, Myatts Field, Loughborough and Somerleyton (the four main blocks of Brixton) joined forces to form the collective known as the GAS Gang. GAS can be translated as ‘Grind And Stack’ or as ‘Guns And Shanks’ and ‘Grip And Shoot’. GAS identified with combined colours of green for Myatts Field (OC) and purple for Angell Town (Y28s). GAS began to arise noticeably from 2007/2008 and inherited a fierce r