      <Placemark>
        <name>⚫SIRU / Siraq / 727

https://web.archive.org/web/20120427205254/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/south-london-gangs/gas-gang-gas

https://web.archive.org/web/20120206081321/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/south-london-gangs/crips-cripset</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X6KbKi3J9WiDdwvaqfQstZNdUX6XS4ibL4PX5-vcPQVcFz7KqPMArsuFpyPas2MsjJXofJGevTebXYXldTNw_cc8JfCLvYrBHihHS_UFYVJI8q4umaFuyTwjrG-m1iWBsmJNgl9m4BFUKg2x7DSbAO6_3Rmz2ASKzjKv1No96E1FmZNxRzcE7reGi3INzKM-nrHSTM?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Lambeth, Brixton, Somerleyton SW9<br><br>SIRU, also known as 'Siraq', or simply 'Raq', are a street gang who are based around the Moorlands estate and Southwyck House (known as the Barrier Block) in the Somerleyton area of Brixton, within the SW9 postcode. The gang were formed by younger members of an old gang known as 'Murderzone' (MZ) in the late 2000s. MZ were part of the Cripset alliance around 2006-2008/09 which was a linkup of ALC, MZ, ABM, Dorset Road and Claptown. The youngest generation of MZ later joined forces with the younger generation from Angell Town, Loughborough and Myatts Fields estates to form the GAS Gang during 2007/08.  As 'GAS Gang' grew the old MZ name began to die out and their youngest generation would begin referring to the gang as SIRU, or GAS/SIRU.<br><br>During 2007/08 the youngest generation from Angell Town, known as the 'Y.28s' (not to be confused with the Y.28s that preceded PDC) began to form friendships with neighbouring Brixton gangs such as 'Tiny OC' from Myatts Fields and also 'Murderzone' (MZ) from Somerleyton. The Y28s and Tiny OC had inherited a fierce rivalry with the Peckham based gangs and decided that the Brixton gangs needed to unite together as one. The youngest generations from Angell Town, Myatts Field, Loughborough and Somerleyton (the four main blocks of Brixton) joined forces to form the collective known as the GAS Gang. GAS can be translated as ‘Grind And Stack’ or as ‘Guns And Shanks’ and ‘Grip And Shoot’. GAS identified with combined colours of green for Myatts Field (OC) and purple for Angell Town (Y28s). GAS began to arise noticeably from 2007/2008 and inherited a fierce rivalry with Peckham from their predecessors- OC, PDC, PIF and CFR. This fierce rivalry between Brixton and Peckham during the 2000s was one of the most reputed rivalries and fiercest wars in London at the time between some of Londons largest and most renowned gang territories. By 2010 that beef with Peckham had began to die down, whilst a new and growing rivalry with Tulse Hill (TN1) was developing. The beef with Tulse Hill brought GAS into conflicts with Stockwell (ABM) and Brixton Hill who had sided with Tulse Hill. GAS were closely affiliated with nearby Brixton gangs, most notably OC from Myatts Field and SIRU (formerly Murderzone) from Somerleyton. Members of GAS from Myatts Field repped both OC and GAS whilst members from Somerleyton repped both SIRU and GAS. GAS also had affiliations with other gangs including YRS from Brixton, 031 from Stockwell and Brooklyn from Old Kent Road area. GAS began to split up through 2013, following personal disputes, and accusations of snitching. The Angell Town, Myatts Field and Loughborough areas remained closely affiliated, leaving GAS/SIRU members from Somerleyton now ostracized from the rest of Brixton beefing with their former allies, as well as historical rivals. Those GAS members from Angell Town and Loughborough went on to form a new clique known as '150'. The founders of '150' had previously been prominent figures within GAS Gang.<br><br>Following the split in GAS Gang, SIRU started to become more commonly referred to as 'Siraq' and '727'. They are considered by many to be one of the strongest, and also most tight-knit, gangs in south London as they no longer have any real allies and they are now surrounded by rival gangs.  The main allies they have are Harlem. They beef 674, LTH, RP, 55, ABM, Mitcham and Pollards Hill. Some younger members also beef 150, 410, 17, Claptown and Uptop.<br><br>Associated Rappers} SR / Bellzey / 5Star / Yung bush / Burbz / Shak / Sshmoney / Ruger]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-000000-2401-120</styleUrl>
