      <Placemark>
        <name>⚫KuKu / Black Prince</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X4tzMJV1nzggB6IrpblWGTusMbC6U1_kdKTMwLlOnQ1dU0OipUH84YtDr80u43XiAiBpM_W1a8Vbhknv_XOLyGgTDnpITkM46pri9IRDi97lr-wygWdqLckAVQQm3tiu9nMQeESdQwSwGWlrKh05jH8pfXLM2Y0RV9hjny1y-NXAMUf6O_-g87iPn8hJeZGJgt988U?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Lambeth, Kennington SE11<br><br>KuKu also known as Black Prince (BP) are a street gang who are based around Black Prince Road in Kennington, most notably on Vauxhall Gardens and Ethelred estates. They used to be known as BYM (Bang Your Mash) in the late 2000s and early 2010s. BYM formed as the younger generation to olders known as 'KTown', and 'Kennington Black Mobb'. There was also a short lived Crip set in the area in the mid 2000s. KuKu/Black Prince are allied with nearby Harlem, ABM, Moscow17, Browning17, AY17 and 674 whilst they beef 410, 150, 17, 031, 37, Claptown and Uptop. They also have beef with nearby China Walk area<br><br>Associated Rappers} Oboy / Shorta / GSmarko]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-000000-2601-120</styleUrl>
