      <Placemark>
        <name>🔵Ghetto / Shower / WPE / 14th

https://web.archive.org/web/20120506224702/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/south-london-gangs/ghetto-boys

https://web.archive.org/web/20111011222004/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/south-london-gangs/shower</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X6aLrD8T4xkWok8SOr01KwXKzUibX601L76ir4jWpWZLLdZIzLt9BbcqTcviYjn-g8hJIoQbvmt8keOrw9zu82EpcKvTL5lnbdgPy4ar0IYZ3Lwm3qGFA6Ato0dPuUQDV5hKH5sU0y64HbyNnw3_8pZlkKHPDHQa8eio-F8L-kwloWIzpIGSZGV0gx1W-zzvu05J3I?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Lewisham, New Cross SE14<br><br>The Ghetto Boys are a large street gang originating from the Milton Court estate, more commonly known as Woodpecker estate, in New Cross within the SE14 postcode. Their area is known locally as 'Ghetto' which is where they get their name from. The Ghetto Boys had began to develop during the late 1970s and early 1980s and at their gangs peak were spread throughout Lewisham borough, incorporating areas such as Deptford, Lewisham and Catford with Brockley closely allied to them. Ghetto are one of the largest, and most well known gangs in London. The gang have long been associated with the colour blue, with Lewisham borough often referred to as "Blue Borough". Oldest members would be responsible for a younger member who would adopt their name forming part of the younger generation. For example, the younger Ghetto members would be known as 'Young Ghetto Boys' (YGB), or 'Younger Younger Ghetto Boys' (YYGB) similar to the nearby 'Peckham Boys' organisation. When the Woodpecker estate was re-developed, during the mid 1990s, the residents were re-housed to other estates around the borough meaning the later generations of the Ghetto Boys established new sets in areas such as Catford and Lewisham. So this meant as well as having age breakdowns to denote the newer generations of the gang, there was also some geographical breakdowns, which included the 'New Cross Ghetto Boy', 'Deptford Ghetto Boy' and 'Lewisham Ghetto Boy' factions.<br><br>Ghetto Boys were predominantly of Caribbean descent, and not wanting to rob from their own communities would often travel to nearby Peckham which was dominated by Africans to commit crime. As that beef between the Ghetto Boys and Peckham Boys grew through the late 1990s and 2000s their conflict then became very much Lewisham borough against Southwark borough as Ghetto had influence over Lewisham and Peckham over Southwark. This meant that Ghetto Boys also came into conflict with some other areas of Southwark including, Walworth, Dulwich and Bermondsey. Ghetto Boys and Peckham Boys rivalry had also been one of the longest running and most infamous 'Postcode Wars' in London, but has since ceased as of 2009/10 with both gangs being torn apart by inner conflicts within both the gangs. Other notable rivalries involving Ghetto Boys had historically been against gangs from Greenwich, notably the 'Woolwich Boys' and the 'Cherry Boys'. In the 1990s, up until 2006, Andrew Wanogho, known as "Sparks", was seen to be in charge of Ghetto Boys throughout Lewisham. He developed a fearsome reputation for violence and robbery, and had an amateur boxing career, which included 5 fights and 5 wins by TKO whilst on the run for murder in Coconut Creek, Florida. He robbed rapper "Ja Rule" of his gold chain and had also served a prison term in New York’s infamous Rykers Island penitentiary. The Ghetto Boys were most powerful during the 1990s and 2000s.<br><br>During 2005/2006 internal conflicts within the Ghetto Boys began and the gang began to defragment rapidly following the deaths of "Sparks", and several other prominent figures such as "Damage". The Ghetto Boys began breaking up into smaller separate, and later independent gangs, such as the 'Pepys Gang Bangers' (Pepys estate) or 'D-Block' (Deptford) and 'Shower' (Younger Ghetto Boys) from New Cross. Their gangs name of "Shower" comes from the "Southern Shower Syndicate", a group of the Ghetto Boys who have close links with the original 'Shower Syndicate', or 'Shower Posse', from Jamaica. 'Shower' have been what the recent generations of Ghetto Boys have been known as since the late 2000s. They have also been referred to as the 'Young Ghetto Boys' (YGB), and the 'Real Ghetto Boys' (RGB). During the break up of the gang came the disassociation of the Ghetto Boys from New Cross and Deptford with Ghetto Boys factions from Catford and Lewisham. New Cross and Deptford then began to beef with Catford and Lewisham. These conflicts stemmed from disputes around women, status, and of course money. That former Ghetto Boy faction from Catford went on to form the 'Anti Shower' gang, as a provocative response to 'New Cross Ghetto Boys' (also known as Shower). During the late 2000s the 'Shower' gang came into conflict with 'Anti Shower' from Catford, Black Mafia from Lewisham and Monson from New Cross Gate area<br><br>The "Shower" gang are now primarily based on Woodpecker estate but draw members from across the wider New Cross and Deptford area. The current generations from New Cross (SE14) are known as 14th whilst members in Deptford (SE8) are known as 8th. The younger generation during the mid to late 2010s were also known as 814 after the SE8 (Deptford) and SE14 (New Cross) postcodes. Their current generations are allied with BSide and Block 6. They beef nearby Monson, SG, M20, 4Anti and Lovelinch.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Showkey / MDot / Lil MDot / AD / Blicksz / Bolo B / Fuze]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-3949AB-2801-77</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X6aLrD8T4xkWok8SOr01KwXKzUibX601L76ir4jWpWZLLdZIzLt9BbcqTcviYjn-g8hJIoQbvmt8keOrw9zu82EpcKvTL5lnbdgPy4ar0IYZ3Lwm3qGFA6Ato0dPuUQDV5hKH5sU0y64HbyNnw3_8pZlkKHPDHQa8eio-F8L-kwloWIzpIGSZGV0gx1W-zzvu05J3I?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
          </Data>
