      <Placemark>
        <name>🟣Claptown (CT)

https://web.archive.org/web/20120206081321/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/south-london-gangs/crips-cripset</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X4u8TB8VS-YSqGutLdmfBTFEK1_baZN4UMEdPfRlZsOz5pyAA95Fn8-Y4bUvUXEvvXhsePRLork65cz1_JxZonxLdZE0qog7KxcRjrWRNUDQAFZlDXrGmL3jZc8bm0z7-qO-1kGWLf4HoZIuNZ6-5Ek1YiMH4zCEg2NXg8Z-iCJsFKepS9f2M-qsPBTXsUD5j3WuoM?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Lambeth, Clapham SW4/SW9<br><br>Claptown (CT) are a street gang from Clapham area, within the SW4 and SW9 postcodes. They are most active on both Notre Dame estate (Worsopp Drive) and the Fenwick estate (NorthDrive). Claptown only really became actively known in the early 2010s when the Worsopp Drive set fronted by their rapper Perm emerged as close allies to nearby 17, 031, 150, 410 and Uptop in the beef with gangs like 674 and LTH. The younger generation of Claptown Crips from Fenwick estate, including their young set called YFE (Young Fully Equipped), were part of the Cripset alliance which was a linkup of ALC, MZ, ABM, Dorset Road and Claptown around 2006-2008/09 times.  They are allied with 17, 031, 37, 150, 410 and Uptop. They beef with 674, LTH, 55, 417, KuKu, SIRU, ABM, Harlem, Moscow17, Browning17 and AY17.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Perm / Saviest / Squeezy ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-9C27B0-2601-77</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X4u8TB8VS-YSqGutLdmfBTFEK1_baZN4UMEdPfRlZsOz5pyAA95Fn8-Y4bUvUXEvvXhsePRLork65cz1_JxZonxLdZE0qog7KxcRjrWRNUDQAFZlDXrGmL3jZc8bm0z7-qO-1kGWLf4HoZIuNZ6-5Ek1YiMH4zCEg2NXg8Z-iCJsFKepS9f2M-qsPBTXsUD5j3WuoM?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
