      <Placemark>
        <name>🔵ALC / Acre Lane

https://web.archive.org/web/20120206081321/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/south-london-gangs/crips-cripset</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X6-hin8nF6ghMbP40ZF5tSgJCceYPeMfOvrBLL4AP6bxiJzswQ4BN-QfD6VTnEFBXGp1J4B7xS24fh2xEtQDsQb-8DQbKPzGPGHtSfyInTVb_pAqdImapigLYURfYE6pjxBzMCHixq9RsZr_wg6UnlKUibUXEXjby2kpaKf0EDLTMCrcaPoqCOLOyLebfLuNgCFW50?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Lambeth, Brixton SW2/SW4/SW9<br><br>ALC (Acre Lane Campaign/Crips) are a street gang based on the estates around Acre Lane, between the Brixton and Clapham area. They formed around 2005/06 and were part of the Cripset alliance which was a linkup of ALC, MZ, ABM, Dorset Road and Claptown.  They were on friendlier terms with most Brixton sets. By 2008/09 the gang had began to die out with younger members linking up with other gangs such as GAS. The current generation in the area tend to be aligned with gangs such as 674.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-1A237E-2701-77</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X6-hin8nF6ghMbP40ZF5tSgJCceYPeMfOvrBLL4AP6bxiJzswQ4BN-QfD6VTnEFBXGp1J4B7xS24fh2xEtQDsQb-8DQbKPzGPGHtSfyInTVb_pAqdImapigLYURfYE6pjxBzMCHixq9RsZr_wg6UnlKUibUXEXjby2kpaKf0EDLTMCrcaPoqCOLOyLebfLuNgCFW50?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
