      <Placemark>
        <name>🔵ABM / M Block / TeamRaw

https://web.archive.org/web/20111012132657/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/south-london-gangs/all-bout-money</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X4blSgh8QazgIT107JCAbDLKgo057RexUa1beMBCZ77G0S74TZLDeZqsSQaTf3cu5H5kzs4prEfxzr-iMY-9lfliZTdP-hD71PEU_ZYM11cMaaXbeYgv6aCYsqQGB73JsshsXcrxhsFd0Cep5yQApnQjH3pdr1iC4060nMFlmygU74BKfq_sSURSKoDcAB5wwcJcMA?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Lambeth, Stockwell SW9<br><br>All Bout Money (ABM), who are now more commonly known as 'M Block' and 'TeamRaw', are a large street gang based in Stockwell, within the SW9 postcode. They are located in and around Stockwell Road on the Stockwell Park and Stockwell Gardens estates. Their area of Stockwell is known locally as "Hotspot" and "Gunspot", as it is known as a drugs and guns hotspot. ABM as a gang name had became widely known in the mid 2000s although the area has a long gang history, as a location where the 'Raiders' and the 'Younger Raiders' had made their name in the 1980s and 1990s. They also refer to themselves as 'Broadday' or the 'Broad Day Shooters' (BDS). They identify with the colour blue. Like many London gangs who identify with the colour blue, their motive was because rivals had adopted the Bloods identity, but it was not a clear affirmation that they were a Crip gang although in the gangs early days they had been part of the Cripset alliance around 2006-2008/09, which was a linkup of ALC, MZ, ABM, Dorset Road and Claptown.<br><br>There was a close association with many older members of ABM and the 'Peckham Boys'. Their link was partially owing to certain Peckham families moving into the Stockwell Park estate as a result of regeneration in North Peckham but had also been due to familial connections or extended networks built through the schools and prison systems. Another more complicated link that existed had been between some older members of ABM and OC from Myatts Field in Brixton. Later rivalries between the younger generations of Peckham Boys and OC created some internal gang disputes, predominantly within the younger generations. The younger generations of the gang started to come into serious conflicts with several nearby Blood gangs from 2005/2006 including 031, G-Street CFR and RSG from Brixton and Stockwell.  By 2010 the ABM youngest generations had become more embroiled in rivalry with the younger generation from Brixton, most notably GAS and the youngest OC members.  They also formed alliances with Tulse Hill (TN1), Brixton Hill, Kennington (BYM), Tooting (TTS), Mitcham and some Crip members who were formerly resident around Dorset Road. The previous relationship with the Peckham Boys has become more complicated following internal rivalries within the 'Peckham Boys' in 2010/11.<br><br>In the late 2000s and early 2010s the younger generation of ABM were known as 'M Block'. Since the early to mid 2010s their 'M Block' name has become the more commonly used name for the gang whilst their old ABM name has gradually been faced out over time. 'M Block', particularly the younger generation, have also been known as 'TeamRaw'. The name 'TeamRaw' is in homage of a leading ABM member Seydou Diarrassouba known as both 'Nutz' and 'TunaRaw' who was stabbed to death on Oxford Street in central London on the Boxing Day of 2011. He was from the Phipps Bridge estate, known as Deadbridge, in Mitcham, which is why their gang also rep 'TeamRaw'. The gang are closely allied with Dorset Road, Mitcham, KuKu, LTH, 417 and 674. They beef 031, 17, 150, 410, 37, SIRU, Roadside, Claptown and Uptop.<br><br>Associated Rappers} ReekzMB / CFigures / Youngs Teflon / Mucky / Mamz / Speedy1Up / 16 Shotz]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-3949AB-2701-77</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X4blSgh8QazgIT107JCAbDLKgo057RexUa1beMBCZ77G0S74TZLDeZqsSQaTf3cu5H5kzs4prEfxzr-iMY-9lfliZTdP-hD71PEU_ZYM11cMaaXbeYgv6aCYsqQGB73JsshsXcrxhsFd0Cep5yQApnQjH3pdr1iC4060nMFlmygU74BKfq_sSURSKoDcAB5wwcJcMA?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
          </Data>
