      <Placemark>
        <name>🟤Fudgetown</name>
        <description><![CDATA[London Borough of Wandsworth, Tooting SW17<br><br>Fudgetown are a small street gang most active on the Abbey Orchard estate in the Tooting Junction area situated between the Tooting, Mitcham and Colliers Wood areas,  straddling the SW17, SW19 and CR4 postcodes. In the 2000s they were part of the collective known as the 'Brown Gang'. The 'Brown Gang' was a short lived collection of smaller local street gangs from across Wandsworth, Merton and as far a field as the Kingston upon Thames area on estates including Exeter Close, Halston Close, Fitzhugh and Abbey Orchard.  Sets within 'Brown Gang' included PTS (Point Then Shoot), IBM (Infamous Brown Mob) and MGO (Madly Greazed Out) The 'Brown Gang' would come into conflict with ICE from Kingston Upon Thames in 2007/08 but had began to die out into the later part of the 2000s. They are loosely allied with nearby CR7, 37, 17, 150, 410, Uptop and Claptown. They beef nearby Mitcham, Pollards Hill, CR0, LTH, ABM, 417, 674 and 55.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Warnz / Aimz / Nibz]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-795548-2801-77</styleUrl>
