      <Placemark>
        <name>⚫Ladywell / Black Mafia / BM

https://web.archive.org/web/20111012135724/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/south-london-gangs/black-mafia</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X4w1HvlKKdDQnvmFroksrlZR9RfGO94VhGTps5GrJzpPyiZ2QokqadHRkU6E2xwQKVj5mm68QnbFEOq7YYWd8UbUhnWBf4AdJ1UnLKw4gmAkvWkKdA-C4HciULIE2yE1FSyAS32a_BxJTOvTq3Ug9wLwwc0SD-bLmNk2y6dpgb1AjdPOG0ZAoEO4rs6umyE-g53JhM?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Lewisham, Lewisham SE6/SE13<br><br>Black Mafia, also known as Black Maff, are an inactive street gang who were active in the late 2000s and early 2010s. They were one of many newer smaller Lewisham street gangs that superseded the broken down, and newly independent, cliques of the 'Ghetto Boys'. The gang were active around the Catford and Lewisham area, with the Slagrove estate being their main base. They had beef with Ghetto, Turnham and SG. They were closely affiliated with Block 6 from nearby Catford. The Black Mafia gang are no longer active. Some Black Mafia members have since been incorporated within the Block 6 gang.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-000000-2501-120</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X4w1HvlKKdDQnvmFroksrlZR9RfGO94VhGTps5GrJzpPyiZ2QokqadHRkU6E2xwQKVj5mm68QnbFEOq7YYWd8UbUhnWBf4AdJ1UnLKw4gmAkvWkKdA-C4HciULIE2yE1FSyAS32a_BxJTOvTq3Ug9wLwwc0SD-bLmNk2y6dpgb1AjdPOG0ZAoEO4rs6umyE-g53JhM?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
