      <Placemark>
        <name>🔴OTR

https://web.archive.org/web/20120503225654/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/south-london-gangs/otr-albanians</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X5sG7MVRidgLFDxAQ1nYIhAioDqaKp1S6An-HDSjjsf_1EMc0_IrcClUYVcMepkkA8QLKDCgpwpORTWbxH7tYZkUub8bXDA0sP7fcgYIzFCJzqd2AWprqlrK6TF6QkzPDUXaAohlrNCZbQYMfh_n9xGrJu6zt7NPqUmqKXO6gwAScqKZJasjvwx8zNzGdSNQ8X6-CM?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Bromley, Bromley BR2<br><br>OTR are an Albanian gang originating from the Coppice estate in Bromley borough. Membership also extends to Woolwich in the borough of Greenwich. OTR acronym is often translated as 'On The Run'. OTR gang was formed by a number of Albanian youths in 2002. The group was a street gang who fought with the other Albanian gangs from different parts of London and also with the smaller collectives in the local area of Bromley such as those on the Turpington estate. The gang also have a clique back in Albania which was started by the founding members of OTR when they visited Albania. Photos of OTR gangs members brandishing guns and OTR graffiti and tattoo's were taken of members of the Albanian clique and then displayed on a social networking site. The press created a very exaggerated expose of the OTR clique in Bromley, claiming that the pictures were taken in the UK, however, many of them were taken in Albania. A smaller group of individuals within the gang pursued music and OTR also became the name of the music group born out the gang. A hit made by OTR founder Noizy called "Kosov Shqipni" (see video) became a hit back in Albania and resulted in OTR becoming one of the widest known 'street crews' in Albania having begun in Bromley. Youngest generations have taken part in the annual violence on the celebration of Kosovan Independence Day in Trafalgar Square since 2007. The event takes place each February and provides an opportunity for Albanian gangs from London to meet and fight. Younger members will inevitably progress into more sinister organised criminality, with older members involved in drug trafficking, prostitution, security, people smuggling and firearms offences. Other Albanian gangs from London who they beef with include ASA Albanians from North-west London, Above The Rest or (ATR) from Greenwich, Hellbanianz from Barking and Real Albanian Gangsters/Young Albanian Gangsters from Wood Green]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-FF5252-2701-120</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X5sG7MVRidgLFDxAQ1nYIhAioDqaKp1S6An-HDSjjsf_1EMc0_IrcClUYVcMepkkA8QLKDCgpwpORTWbxH7tYZkUub8bXDA0sP7fcgYIzFCJzqd2AWprqlrK6TF6QkzPDUXaAohlrNCZbQYMfh_n9xGrJu6zt7NPqUmqKXO6gwAScqKZJasjvwx8zNzGdSNQ8X6-CM?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
