      <Placemark>
        <name>🔘Browning17 (B17) / Kartel17

https://web.archive.org/web/20110602072158/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/south-london-gangs/wooly-hood</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X6TFDSlNlrQTZkLrAnyRGbzsIiPBSa5JR0HHBcPheHYs24FEwaFwb7Mh-NZW_Z3MJKR9y3gfPcE9BQiL9gPgeVBTV_Yqp-BPbD1jL8EgMEbTzvqMMFBzavGSJctA35hJ65UiDgGGov_KkHn9GayVrDmXKJLBmHLM5SYj0_MGRRT-NIh7aVv0Woy5g5bR6lxyD7wou8?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Southwark, Walworth SE17<br><br>Browning17 (B17) are a small street gang based on the Browning estate in Walworth, within the SE17 postcode. Previous gangs of the Wooly Hood area were known by different names such as 'Ratchets' and from 2004 OTB, which can be interpreted as 'Out To Ball' or 'Out To Bade' has been around,  although in more recent times relates more so to the music side of things.  Other cliques have included MOB (Mandem on Brandon) and CG (Criminally Gifted), whilst more generic names have included Wooly Road Mandem and Wooly Hood. Wooly Hood have been closely allied with the nearby Peckham Boys, and would share many of the same rivalries, and alliances as them. The relationships between Walworth and Peckham have became more contentious after the younger generations from both areas fell into serious conflict during 2015/16 although their older generations remain allied. They are allied with Moscow17 and AY17. They beef with nearby Zone 2, YPB, CMB, 410, 150, 17, Uptop and Claptown.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-757575-2501-77</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
