      <Placemark>
        <name>🔘🔴Fieldway / 00</name>
        <description><![CDATA[London Borough of Croydon, New Addington CR0<br><br>Fieldway Boys are a street gang based on Fieldway estate in Croydon, within the CR0 postcode.  They are located around the large suburban area of New Addington on estates which includes Fieldway, Kestrel Way and Central Parade. Fieldway and New Addington is often described as a forgotten ghetto due to its unique isolation from the rest of London. Fieldway were formerly known as 'Block Cartel' (BC), and the younger generation 'Young Block Cartel' (YBC), during the late 2000s and early 2010s.  'Block Cartel' were the younger generation to an older gang known by the acronym of KTS, standing for amongst other things, 'Kill Time Set', 'Killers That Shoot' and 'Kiss Tha Snub'. They were once affiliated to a south London Crip gang known as 'Acre Lane Campaign' (ALC). A member of ALC, known by the street name "Rekzee", had also been a leading figure within KTS. A younger generation to KTS took on the acronym CYT which stood for 'Certified Young Thugs' and had went on to amass a large following, however some members began to disband to join now rival gangs, such as DSN (Don't Say Nothin) and GMG (Get Money Gangsterz) as well as P-Block (Penge). The aforementioned "Rekzee" later changed the name of the younger gang members from CYT to BC, which primarily stands for 'Block Cartel', but can also be translated as 'Blood City' or 'Be Cautious'. KTS also have an associated music group known as "GD Music". The gang membership of those groups had once also extended north into part of south London around Norwood Junction (SE25) and nearby Woodside. They are allied with CR0 and MH. They beef STK, SBV, VP, 5th and CR7.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Skatpack / Qwest ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-757575-3201-77</styleUrl>
