      <Placemark>
        <name>🔵Woolwich Boys (CGM)

https://web.archive.org/web/20120414004515/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/south-london-gangs/woolwich-boys</name>
        <description><![CDATA[London Borough of Greenwich, Woolwich SE18<br><br>The Woolwich Boys are based on estates across Woolwich and Plumstead within the SE18 postcode. The groups main territory is the Barnfeld and Woolwich Common estates, but they are active throughout the area including on Nightingale, Dockyard, Morris Walk and Polthorne estates, as well as the Glyndon estate in Plumstead.  They are also known as CGM (Cash Gwop Money).  They are now one of the oldest gangs in Greenwich,  having formed around 1998. Initially the gang was made up of almost entirely Somali youths who grouped together to protect themselves from groups in neighbouring boroughs, such as the 'Ghetto Boys' from Lewisham, as well as racist groups previously resident in areas like Eltham and Thamesmead.  They had felt as though the group was being confined to within the SE18 postcode where they reside and so they would begin to group together in larger numbers for protection however they then began to use their strength for criminal activities.  By the early 2000s they began to take on the Ghetto Boys to establish their own reputation and began to assert their new found dominance over the other areas of Greenwich, which inevitably led to newer gang formations in other parts of the borough.  They are structured by age from olders down to youngers and also divided geographically on the many estates within SE18.  Due to the heightened police pressure the gang began moving their operations outside of the city in counties like Hampshire and Kent. They beef with Cherry, Ferrier and GS28.<br><br><br>They are now an older generation more focused on trapping rather than the streets. The present gang activity in the area comes from 'WildBatch' as they chill on the Barnfield estate. There is also a subset of 'WildBatch' on the Barnfield estate known as 18Hunna/1800.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-3949AB-2401-77</styleUrl>
