      <Placemark>
        <name>🔵1stSide / WK / ICE

https://web.archive.org/web/20111231203239/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/south-london-gangs/who-kares-wk</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X5wFyh8LsldOoiLYmfpIbSl4LDIInDWnbsooie5QQFmZ9SV5KnRfbdaQypnkV4KtZtOWxafSe22CBpth1IOCQ0tjwwoaEsTgGsuPayMSB7IAxkgFTJhYHiaM3Lx3svAc3MZzfaETP3TCjENOuQKSc2zDscMbG9m63ugbUnl6swaM_TtZLlymCeaEbg7Vz40nCgJyfk?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Kingston Upon Thames, Kingston KT1<br><br>WK (WhoKares) were a street gang who are based on the Cambridge Road estate in Kingston Upon Thames, within the KT1 postcode. The WK gang formed around 1995 and the self-proclaimed instigator of the gang was Danny aka Taba (Tabanacle). The gang was exposed in Channel 4's Dispatches documentary, 'Gang War', which lifted the lid on the hidden world of Britain's armed and dangerous youth gangs in 2003. Other smaller WK spin off gangs in Kingston included OSA (One Step Ahead) and PPO (Pissing People Off). Following the documentary members of the WK gang were banned from Kingston town centre and ASBO's were pursued against problematic members. The following generation to the gang became known by the aconym ICE, which stands for 'Incredible Cambridge Estate' or 'Invincible Cambridge Estate'. The younger ICE gang (Tiny ICE) were in conflict with a collective known as the 'Brown Gang' (who were from across south London) throughout 2007/08. The current generation from the estate are known as '1stSide' and identify with light blue colours. They beef OTCU/M-Town and 37.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Don Dadds]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-0097A7-2501-77</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
