      <Placemark>
        <name>🟢Ferrier (FTM)

https://web.archive.org/web/20120112101119/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/south-london-gangs/ferrier-boys</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X7cXm1ygoBz5ZJmGA0B-ptdyq9NqBzprmuk0fWOP4Tu-48GPgBRnKr2q_da_FkzE3pj7fJOmjdr0NWQuTz2GCV_aFi7WOexI2mPzzPeARHNstxvfQ32L5W-Odvb4-gwmN4lw8E5ZbqRqU7yPS4kNh8WzRUaFUgCpacmEJ1OLASNeQWmAq6UDqygj6o6z16kKuoS2ak?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Greenwich, Kidbrooke SE3<br><br>The Ferrier Boys are a street gang that was originally based on the Ferrier estate in Kidbrooke, within SE3 postcode, but Since the abandonment, and subsequent demolition, of the old Ferrier estate between 2009 and 2012, Ferrier have now relocated to a number of smaller estates around Kidbrooke and Eltham, including on the Brook and Middle Park Avenue estates.  The 'Ferrier Boys' have existed in some form since the early 1990s. There were multiple groups of youths from Ferrier that hung around together although the gang did not really begin officially until 2002/2003, when all the separate groups started to go by the names ‘Ferrier Boys’ and ‘Ferrier Crew’, taking their name from the Ferrier estate. Initially the gang formed to protect themselves from attacks by nearby 'Woolwich Boys' but soon developed into an active criminal gang, and a feared force in the borough.<br><br>In the late 1980s rival, or rather competing, local gangs had began to form in the area, including 'The Krays' from Eltham and 'The Firm' from Thamesmead. Both groups consisted of predominantly white males, and had shared values inherited from those old crime families, including sexist, homophobic and racist attitudes. At the centre of those gangs were sons of certain criminals involved in the drug trade. They differed from the older generations in their general recklessness and unpredictability, with a tendency to carry knives. Both gangs would come together if threatened by the multi-racial gangs of nearby Woolwich. The rivalry between the white youths of the 'Thamesmead' and 'Eltham' street gangs on the one side and multiracial Woolwich gangs on the other, inevitably took on a racist dimension. Both 'Thamesmead' and 'Eltham' had widened this out to encompass any Black and Asian person they came across,  regardless of whether they even had any involvement in youth gangs. There were some exceptions to the generally white make-up of the 'Thamesmead Firm'. One of their group was from one of the few black families on the estate and he was made an exception having grown up with and was intimately known to other members of 'The Firm'.<br><br>Under 'The Firm' there were several 'junior' street gangs that had served as proving grounds for youngsters keen to make their names. They had names such as 'the Goldfish Gang' or the Nutty (or Nazi) Turnouts (often known as the NTOs), 'the Rudds' and 'the Tenches'. The 'Thamesmead Firm' and rivals 'Eltham Krays' were both regularly committing racist attacks on black and asian youths in Eltham and Thamesmead, and now somewhat competing against each other. Amongst the long list of victims knifed by both the gangs during the peak of their activities during the early 1990s were a young Asian lad, 'Rohit Duggal', stabbed to death outside a kebab shop in Tudor Parade on Well Hall Road, and two teens killed simply for being black. These were 'Rolan Adams', murdered by the members of the 'Firm' in the February of 1991, and 'Stephen Lawrence', murdered by the 'Eltham Krays' in April 1993.<br><br>By the early 2000s the demographics of the area had began to change, and the once racist element to these local gangs had diminished. By 2007/2008 Ferrier Boys, along with their allies T-Block began to identify with the colour of green. The two gangs began to proclaim the combined gang territories as “Green Town". Sub-divisions of the gang had included the 'Original Ferrier Youths' (OFY) and 'Young Ferrier Boys' (YFB) whilst their youngest generations were known as "Hardbody G’s" (HBG). Since the demolition of the Ferrier estate, a new generation have emerged on the new estate known as FTM (Ferrier Trey Man). Like older Ferrier Boys, they identify with the colour of green. They are allied with GS28. Ferrier beefs with 9Side, Cherry, SRoad and AWB.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Kartel / Mookie B / Buck London]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-7CB342-2501-77</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X7cXm1ygoBz5ZJmGA0B-ptdyq9NqBzprmuk0fWOP4Tu-48GPgBRnKr2q_da_FkzE3pj7fJOmjdr0NWQuTz2GCV_aFi7WOexI2mPzzPeARHNstxvfQ32L5W-Odvb4-gwmN4lw8E5ZbqRqU7yPS4kNh8WzRUaFUgCpacmEJ1OLASNeQWmAq6UDqygj6o6z16kKuoS2ak?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
