      <Placemark>
        <name>North Heath

https://web.archive.org/web/20120414193438/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/south-london-gangs/racist-attack-ra</name>
        <description><![CDATA[London Borough of Bexley, Northumberland Heath DA8<br><br>North Heath are a small street gang based on the Becton Place estate in the Northumberland Heath area, within the DA8 postcode. They beef with GH00, CHG, WildBatch and Block 6.<br><br>North Heath have followed on from older gangs in the area with racist undertones notably a gang known as Racist Attack (RA) who first came to notice in 2004, largely made up of British teenagers from north Bexley borough. Fifteen members of the gang aged between 15 and 20 were arrested for a series of racial attacks, including violent disorder and grievous bodily harm. The victims were predominantly black and Asian young males who were attacked and beaten in the Bexley area. <br><br>As original members left school younger generations carried on the gang, known as Y.RA (Younger Racist Attack). Although the gang is white British and motivated by race some of the definers and identifiers of the RA gang are taken from non-white gang culture. Other derivatives of the RA include 'Red Alert'. The Pheasant Pub in Belmont Road became a hang-out of the RA gang in Northumberland Heath, however, after pressure from local police it was later closed down by parent company Enterprise Inns in 2009. Another drinking establishment that became associated with the gang was the Drayman in Crook Log, Bexleyheath. The pub also had its licence revoked after councillors watched CCTV footage of members of the RA gang openly snorting drugs on the premises.<br><br>A series of young white gangs are present across Bexley borough although not known to the same extent as RA. They are predominantly composed of white British youths who are involved in less serious violence (fights), theft and drug offences.These groups in the past have included Hurstwood Boys (HWB) and Younger Hurstwood Boys (YHWB); Sidcup Take Over (STO); North Heath Boys (NHB) and Younger North Heath Boys (YNHB); The New Estate (TNE); Crayford Fighters and the Frobisher Boys.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Reekz / Agro Albo]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-000000-2801-77</styleUrl>
