      <Placemark>
        <name>🔵⚫JRoad

https://web.archive.org/web/20110530002210/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/south-london-gangs/bermondsey-boys</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X4gcsii9_uknLZFmGSAnFsv90qkRYDO4JLHVyjwCOQdeVUI01Tj-Qh9qRk1ZHNSIM-35HpguJmv7FPHp5fcleoewP7TgUj9__KbPNC7j8GyI06cAI_1atroWfl4hbs7GP0uOr_tJ_4OOEKBQff-z3ZyC5WKclgvWhDhZWMvnPxLfzxS-GSnnSqWoUZVAMaw2dC2bTM?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Southwark, Bermondsey SE1/SE16<br><br>'Jamaica Road Boys' (JRB) are a street gang who are based on several estates around Jamaica Road in the Bermondsey area, within both the SE1 and SE16 postcodes. The area had been home to gangs of white British or Irish origin based on estates that surround Jamaica Road.  There had been white gangs here since the post war period. Unlike the multi-racial and ethnic street gangs they would keep a low profile being more organised, carrying out crimes for financial gain rather than to build a reputation through violence.  The older white Bermondsey cliques included ‘Lucey Way Boys’, ‘Drummond Road Bermz’, ‘Berms Dont Fuck About’, ‘Real Cockney Boys’ and the ‘Millwall Boys’. The current generation from the area are known as the 'Jamaica Road Boys' (JRB). JRB, like most gangs in London, are primarily of black or mixed origin. The older generations flag black, but the younger ones flag blue. They have ties with AY17, Moscow17, Harlem and 16th. The gang beef Zone 2, YPB, Silwood and CMB.<br><br>Associated Rappers} King Lou-Locc / ARisky]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-3949AB-2601-87</styleUrl>
