      <Placemark>
        <name>🟠CR7 / 730 / 7Side

https://web.archive.org/web/20120420051805/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/south-london-gangs/shine-my-nine-ninerz-smn</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X797fj49D_ieFtgOh0B-oBNPcmZrxGGQiC77U2pQv9mc1V9twMN5Mn4Bgz5o5VF6t9pR9e-NtuzE24HB0gullOKGwESEi6s55gw8htNYiDRwe-jUseRmDMpSZ7Aa0_HiXaXMqI208qtbd4-wWT_kZzMSDwTFi7v2CM_HHtRywh8aL_goQ4gXEtxHny5y0xeTUQZOQHC?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Croydon, Thornton Heath CR7<br><br>CR7, also known as 'G Lane', are a street gang based around Green Lane in the Thornton Heath area within CR7 postcode known as the "7" and also "7Side". CR7 sets identify with the colour orange, and are the current generation to older gangs from the area, such as 'Shine My Nine' (SMN),  who were the predecessors to the recent generations of CR7 based gangs active through the 2010s. SMN formed around 2003/04 and uses of the SMN acronym included 'Straight Merkin Niggaz', whilst they were also known as the "Ninerz". Historically the gang had been affiliated with the 3s and 'Gipset' gangs from the Gipsy Hill and West Norwood areas. SMN gang were the younger generation to the older gang known as the 'Dogs To Kill' (D2K). Other affiliated cliques who had arose in the area were LMD (Lick Man Down) and MDS (Mayday Sprayday) as well as some who used the name of 'Heathset'.  The current sets from CR7 are known as 'G Lane' and '730'. The sets are allied with 5th, STK, SBV, VP and SIRU.  Their main rivals are CR0, Fieldway, Pollards Hill, Mitcham and 417.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Tapeoff / SToopid / GR / Skully / Rigz / £Lmoe Bands]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-F57C00-2401-77</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
