      <Placemark>
        <name>🔘Moscow17 (M17)

https://web.archive.org/web/20110602072158/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/south-london-gangs/wooly-hood</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X7qJ8fxHGEXjWpx3uSD7vF2nwBVEjekcL8BULuw4y-v2KIzMOVNe7-64z23_O5kYYDixlrV1OH6LOWRVhs9Xi9uBoWvgcDLjHPpfhTtGpqmC8ko9yGRSS1RW8QfysYFRNFDrC8vZ5VlFdDeiI8xajDBq2HsPhOS_kFlgK4fAFSyRyNOHiB7gFvf1oo9xyucCvxWMQs?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Southwark, Walworth SE17<br><br>Moscow17 (M17) are a large street gang who are based on the Brandon estate and the adjoining blocks situated along John Ruskin Street to the west of Walworth Road in around the Walworth area, within the SE17 postcode. 'Moscow' is a nickname for the 'Wooly Hood' block. Previous gangs of the Walworth area were known under different names including 'Ratchets' and from 2004/05 the OTB acronym which can be interpreted as 'Out To Ball' or 'Out To Bade' has been around, although is now more related to the music side of things, as they are now an older generation. In the 2000s other cliques included 'Mandem on Brandon' (MOB) and 'Criminally Gifted' (CG), whilst more generic names have included Wooly Road Mandem and Wooly Hood. The Wooly Hood sets have been closely allied with the nearby Peckham Boys for many years and have shared many of the same rivals and allies as them although the relationships between Walworth and Peckham have became more contentious after the new and youngest generations from both areas fell into serious conflict during 2015/16 although the older generations remain close. They are allied with nearby Browning17, AY17, Harlem and KuKu. Their main rivals are Zone 2, YPB, CMB, 410, 150, 17, Uptop and Claptown.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Loose / Incognito / Knockoutned / GB / Rizzy Rampz / Zino / Mayski ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-757575-2701-77</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X7qJ8fxHGEXjWpx3uSD7vF2nwBVEjekcL8BULuw4y-v2KIzMOVNe7-64z23_O5kYYDixlrV1OH6LOWRVhs9Xi9uBoWvgcDLjHPpfhTtGpqmC8ko9yGRSS1RW8QfysYFRNFDrC8vZ5VlFdDeiI8xajDBq2HsPhOS_kFlgK4fAFSyRyNOHiB7gFvf1oo9xyucCvxWMQs?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
