      <Placemark>
        <name>⚫417</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X4EoEU6zDoSo9tOTvzOYuHQPxq8nogvBkPfAhDxMLXfoyea2BZiUquAyXO4bOmpUmDPB9X4it3ff-W2zegjHFFMRple0zHNv2NYXQLKrhdN-eYEn-w9zqXdm4hTbjfu-tScOg3aGUq17jy62oMhC6uGj6kDAC04p2JB1k4w13WJkKJ7mEyVdvpUWguBrSM2veCpwfI?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Wandsworth, Tooting SW17<br><br>417 are a large street gang based around Tooting Broadway on several estates, especially the Hazelhurst, Tooting Grove and Church Lane estates which are located within the SW17 postcode. Their claimed territory stretches from the Tooting area along Garratt Lane, and into Earlsfield, within the SW18 postcode. During the 2000s the gang would form in Tooting known as TBG (Tooting Black Gang), and later TTS (Tooting Trapstars). Some Tooting members had earlier also formed part of an alliance known as SNT (Stack N Trap). During this time Tooting were affiliated with 'Terrorzone' (TZ) gang from Mitcham and 'All Bout Money' (ABM) from Stockwell. During this period their main rivals were the SUK (Stick'em Up Kids) gang based in Battersea/Clapham Junction.  During the mid 2010s TTS would become known as '417'. The name '417' is said to derive from the areas postcodes CR4 and SW17 (the numbers pay homage to the alliance between Mitcham, CR4 and Tooting, SW17). Tooting are allied with nearby Mitcham, Pollards Hill, ABM, LTH, 674, 55, Gipsy Hill, Harlem and KuKu whilst they beef  37, 031, 17, 150, 410, Fudgetown, Claptown and Uptop.<br><br>Associated Rappers} KI / SK / Snizz / Nockz ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-000000-2901-120</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
