      <Placemark>
        <name>🟣SMS / Squeeze 4 P$$ / Squeeze Section

https://web.archive.org/web/20111020231259/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/south-london-gangs/south-man-syndicate</name>
        <description><![CDATA[London Borough of Lambeth, Streatham SW16<br><br>South Man Syndicate (SMS), also sometimes referred to as the 'South Muslim Soldiers' are a gang that arose through a collection of young males from south London. Although the gang name was not really widely known until the mid 2000s, the origins of the gang can be traced back to the mid 1990s when the gang began to form as youths. Many of the gangs original members were drawn from both the Streatham and Norwood areas of Lambeth where the gang are most active. They also drew members from areas further afield including Thornton Heath, Tooting, Lewisham, Southwark, and Brixton where their closest allies 'Nastie Squad' (NS), and their later following generation OC (Organised Crime), are located. The main areas of gang activity in Streatham are centred around Streatham High Road with the more specific locations being Leigham Avenue / Leigham Court Road as well as the Valley Road area including Well Close / Curtis Field Road etc.<br><br>There has been a long history between areas in the south of Lambeth borough with Brixton. The main allies of SMS were the 'Nastie Squad' (NS) and OC (Organised Crime) who were from Myatts Fields in Brixton and 'Gipset' from nearby Gipsy Hill and West Norwood. In the 1990s SMS founders were in conflict with the 28s from Brixton. The relationship with late 1990s onwards Brixton gang PDC, and their allies was often an 'on-off' relationship. SMS were attributed by the media as being responsible of the death of a prominent PDC member, Adrian 'Ham' Marriot who was killed in summer 2004. It was alleged at court that their motivation was forcing to convert Marriot to Islam, although there was no evidence to support this. Six months later SMS were implicated in the murder of another member of PDC. Solomon 'Blacker' Martin was shot dead in Thornton Heath on new years eve. SMS were one of the three South London gangs that the media often referred to as the “Muslim Boys”,  the name perpetuated by Police in the media. The other gangs often written about in the media being afforded the "Muslim Boys" label were Brixton OC and PDC gangs. There were many articles from media regarding the rise of "Muslim Boys", often exaggerated playing heavily on their Muslim identity.  Being Muslim is not a requirement to be part of the 'South Man Syndicate'. The rise of the label of 'Muslim Boys' came about in the mid 2000s, a time when many young gang members in South London, particularly in Lambeth Borough, had converted to Islam.<br><br>A younger generation to SMS had emerged in the late 2000s known as 'Squeeze 4 P$$' (S4P), also later referred to as the 'Squeeze Section'.  'Squeeze Section' were what the younger generation of the 'Squeeze 4 P$$' gang became known as in the early 2010s. 'Squeeze Section' also drew members from Croydon and Penge. Several members of the popular music group 'Section Boyz', now known as 'Smoke Boyz', had been affiliated with 'Squeeze Section'. Hence the groups name.<br><br>They are now an older generation more focused on trapping rather than street beefs. The younger generation in the area identify with local sets like GID/55 and Crown Point (CP).<br><br>Associated Rappers} Swift / Deepee / ill Mill / Ghost]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-9C27B0-2801-77</styleUrl>
        <Polygon>
