      <Placemark>
        <name>⚫LTH / 861</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X78bZeHfK4UITHPBWJRSds_4jsz0S8hCShalvRm9Koi2b7I4v8nm-dsT5U5sxxqBRFR8JfDHxbpqbhmsGtnKvoLFJzdpe25aiExD06MgsAOzrSoPcfQ-OcaY0IdAxXZzP2XyiP8q0R9aQHMgXCxArr3QUtkS8xNY0jprwlRjSr6oyzofhEjmK09pnWQaT1zR9NKsZQ?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Lambeth, Tulse Hill SW2<br><br>LTH (Lower Tulse Hill) are a large street gang from the Tulse Hill estate, within the SW2 postcode. In the 1990s and early 2000s Tulse Hill gang members tended to align themselves with Brixton gangs like the 28s and PDC. In the 2000s Tulse Hill members were referred to as 'Tulse Hill Mandem', whilst some used the name 'T-Block'. Until around 2008 both lower and upper Tulse Hill were cool with Brixton but that changed during 2008/2009 when the youngest generation from Tulse Hill estate known as TN1 (Trust No-1 or Tell No-1) started to beef with gangs from Brixton (GAS, OC, SIRU and RSG). TN1 (Lower Tulse Hill)  would also later start to beef Upper Tulse Hill who sided with Brixton. They were closely affiliated with Stockwell (ABM) and Brixton Hill. In the early 2010s the TN1 members changed the name of the gang to '861'. The name '861' is a homage to the previous name of TN1, by using the buttons of a trap phone to reflect this (where 8=T, 6=N and 1 stays on its own). In the late 2010s the youngest generation started to be known as LTH (Lower Tulse Hill). They are now closely affiliated with nearby 674, 55, 417, ABM, BG, Harlem, KuKu, Mitcham and Gipsy Hill. They beef with 150, 410, 031, 17, 37, SIRU, Uptop, Claptown and Roadside.<br><br>Associated Rappers} C1 / G41 / DT / Slimz / Stampface / Scams / Baby R / GunnaGrimes / T Mulla]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-000000-2401-120</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
