      <Placemark>
        <name>⚫Gipsy Hill / Gipset / 019

https://web.archive.org/web/20120427011124/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/south-london-gangs/3s-gipset-dgm</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X7TwjY5kSy2FyswkaSRGKYYOz3rvU_zLDFuAAsNnbnL6pIhRovBs3IpAzMiHmdh2j3BEye7_BylU-7-eIEf_w2FD390mQnSgXO2RPg3P5HZHBihoEMU0eRMCXAKjsorgFvg_4SASjK-0NbLvdC8UoGnvlr4d8SJRiCUHYC7JsVLflrGzayIo6W3cIYrKEi4A_2PjJo?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Lambeth, Gipsy Hill SE19<br><br>Gipset are a street gang from Gipsy Hill and West Norwood, within the SE19 and SE27 postcodes. During the late 1990s up to 2004 the main gang in the area were known as the 3’s. Gangs in the area were historically aligned with upper Tulse Hill, the Nastie Squad (NS) from Brixton and the South Man Syndicate (SMS) from the nearby Streatham area.<br><br>The 3’s drew membership from both Croydon and Lambeth boroughs, including West Norwood, Upper Norwood, Gipsy Hill and Thornton Heath. The Norwood area spans multiple South London boroughs, mainly Lambeth and Croydon, but also Southwark and Lewisham. Urban renewal in inner city parts of Lambeth, Lewisham and Southwark, saw the mass migration of residents, including youth gang members, into this area during the 1990s and 2000s. This resulted in gang members from other areas living amongst one another, and therefore there has always been multiple gang affiliations in the area. Gang members from Gipsy Hill and West Norwood often robbed youths from nearby Croydon, which resulted in Croydon youths banding together for protection and leading to the development of Croydon DSN (Don't Say Nothin) gang during the mid 2000s.<br><br>Gipset had became widely known around 2004/2005. From their influence from nearby South Man Syndicate (SMS), the gang would sometimes refer themselves as "Gipset Taliban" and are also known as 'Dirty Gip Mob' (DGM). The main area of activity is the Central Hill estate and Berridge Road estate known locally as "Red Brick City". Another area of activity is the Dunbar estate and Norwood Road to the York Hill estate in West Norwood in an area nicknamed "Ghost Town" owing to its proximity to West Norwood Cemetery. Historically the Gipset had been affiliated with nearby South Man Syndicate (SMS) from Streatham, Shine My Nine (SMN) from Thornton Heath and 'Tulse Hill Mandem' from Upper Tulse Hill. During the 2000s and early 2010s Gipset would primarily come into conflict with DSN from Croydon.<br><br>Since the mid 2010s the younger generations active around the Gipsy Hill area have referred to themselves as "Gip" and "019" or more recently simply "9" (shortened from 019). The Gipsy Hill area is now allied with 674, LTH, 55, RP, 417, ABM, Harlem and KuKu. The area beef 5th, 150, 410, 37, 17, SIRU, Uptop, Claptown, M20, 25 and VP.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Krept / Konan / Cadet / K Trap / DoRoad / Jabz / GetBusy / T6]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-000000-2201-117</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
