      <Placemark>
        <name>🔴031 / TeamTrizzy / 17 / ABG / TOG

https://web.archive.org/web/20111230013609/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/south-london-gangs/031-o-trey-one</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X5DNmerFIbM9U7pld3gMMg8uJd2G52HLoAU7G5FJDEzDI-lRI5gH320R7uuyujS3Tr1wwY08n2M6Gf5tvo2TT45wZc2Z-aim5A2NBTiw1qDgJZVmonfh9syWu3m2T3ktMeSnQsR9gGYzLAYCvc72ZquQQN8pq3pbqOjkTgldX9dEXEIryaCxMMWaQF_m7HzhDv5yfy8?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Boroughs of Lambeth and Wandsworth, Stockwell and Wandsworth Road SW8<br><br>031 are a large street gang who originated in the Stockwell area, within the SW4 and SW8 postcodes. The gang covers a number of estates situated on the border of Lambeth and Wandsworth boroughs, particularly Patmore, Gaskell Street, Studley, Hartington, Springfield, Lansdowne Green, Hemans and Westbury estates. 031, Pronounced "O-Tray One", were the first Blood gang to be formed in London. Some founder members have links with Blood gang members in New York City, USA. 031 in the "United Blood Nation" (USA East Coast Bloods) loosely translates as "I got love for you Blood". The numbers represent United Blood Nation.<br><br>031 Bloods were founded around 2006 by former PDC gang members, including "Tanna". By 2006, the older members of PDC were undergoing ‘conflicts of interest’ which resulted in some members, including "Tanna", breaking off to form their own sets. 031 would come to be the overarching allegiance of several smaller Blood gangs or sets around Lambeth that would take their names from the local estates in which they are from, including cliques such as G-Street (Gaskell Street), ABG (Albion Blocks), 'Union Blocks' and 'Patmore G’s', which refer to the local geographical gang territories. There is also affiliations with the Brixton gangs who arose from the splits within PDC. The CFR and RSG gangs distanced themselves from PDC by adopting the colour red, and the Blood identity. CFR and RSG would later come to be considered part of the 031 Bloods movement. The CFR, G-Street and RSG factions are independent street gangs rather than simply just sets of 031. Other 031 sets have included 'Original Gangsta Bloods' /'Original Greeze Block' (OGB) and the 'Killa Gangsta Bloods' (KGB) based around Dorset Road, on South Lambeth estate, in territory previously home to the rival 'Dorset Road Cripset' gang. 031 also have affiliations further south in the Croydon area (Byrdgang and KGB). The 'G-Street' (GST) group are the most thorough 031 set having been independent gang since at least the early 2000s. The older generation retain the use of the 'G-Street' name, whilst their later younger generations are more likely to align themselves with the 031 Bloods.<br><br>The older generation had close ties with Brixton gangs such as PDC, PIF, CFR and RSG, whilst younger generations were closely affiliated with Brixton gangs such as GAS and OC as well as SUK from Battersea and Clapham Junction area and 'Brooklyn', from the Old Kent Road area. The natural rivals to 031 became the nearby 'Dorset Road Cripset' and ABM from Stockwell who identify with the colour blue although are not necessarily Crips. 031 versus ABM beef has become one of the bloodiest rivalries of recent years in Lambeth which has claimed several lives since 2007. 031 have also had conflict with the nearby Kennington and Peckham areas. The oldest generations of 031 had beef with OC from Brixton, although the youngest generations of 031 have been closely affiliated with the younger OC generations. During the early 2010s the younger generations from 031 would refer to themselves as 'Team Trizzy'.<br><br>During the mid 2010s the younger members of 'Team Trizzy' (031) would become known as '17' (pronounced one-seven) in honour of a "Trizzy" member who was killed on the 1st of July (7th month of the year) in 2012. 17 are primarily based on the estates around Wandsworth Road, which include the Springfield, Patmore and Westbury estates.  The '17' olders are known as '17Wano' or ABG (Ambition Brings Greatness), whilst the youngest members would also use the name TOG (Tape Off Gang). They are allied with 150, 410, 37, Claptown and Uptop. They beef ABM, 674, LTH, 417, 55, Harlem, KuKu, SIRU, Mitcham, Dorset Road, Moscow17, Browning17, AY17 and VCity.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Wreckit / Striker / Rage / Lil Twin / YP / Blackz / Lil A / Vile Greeze / lil Torment / Timbar]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-FF5252-2601-125</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X5DNmerFIbM9U7pld3gMMg8uJd2G52HLoAU7G5FJDEzDI-lRI5gH320R7uuyujS3Tr1wwY08n2M6Gf5tvo2TT45wZc2Z-aim5A2NBTiw1qDgJZVmonfh9syWu3m2T3ktMeSnQsR9gGYzLAYCvc72ZquQQN8pq3pbqOjkTgldX9dEXEIryaCxMMWaQF_m7HzhDv5yfy8?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
