      <Placemark>
        <name>⚫Mitcham/4th</name>
        <description><![CDATA[London Borough of Merton, Mitcham CR4<br><br>Mitcham sets are based on the Phipps Bridge estate known locally as "Deadbridge", but they are also located on smaller estates such as those around Sadler Close, Laburnum Road, Armfield Crescent, Baron Court and Glebe Court to the close by Eastfields estate, all located within the CR4 postcode.<br><br>The Mitcham sets can be traced back to an older generation known as 'Terrorzone' (TZ). They formed around 2005/2006 and were active until the early 2010s. TZ were mainly active on the Phipps Bridge estate. The gang were allied with PMD (Pollards Hill) TTS (Tooting) and ABM (Stockwell) as well as the younger 'Mitcham' set known as DB (Deadbridge) on the Phipps Bridge estate.   They were known for their rivalry with SUK (Battersea/Clapham Junction) and 031 (Stockwell).<br><br>Despite the rivalries, some members from TZ, TTS and SUK in their early days had formed a set known as SNT (Stack N Trap) during the mid 2000s. By the early 2010s the TZ name began to fade, with many leading TZ members in prison and pressure from rivals SUK. The younger generation would go on to become known as "MTown". Their gang are now more usually known simply as 'Mitcham' or '4rth'. The Deadbridge (DB) set on the Phipps Bridge estate are now also known as 'TeamRaw' owing to the sets close alliance with the original ABM/MBlock/TeamRaw set from Stockwell. The sets name 'TeamRaw' is in homage of a leading ABM member "Seydou Diarrassouba" known as both 'Nutz' and 'TunaRaw' who was stabbed to death on Oxford Street, in central London, on the Boxing Day of 2011. 'Nutz' lived on the Phipps Bridge estate which is why their set also rep 'TeamRaw'.<br><br>'Mitcham' sets are allied with 417, ABM, LTH, 674, 55/GID and 213/Sutton. They beef with 37, 17, Claptown, Pollards Hill/MNS, Moredun/MT and Fudgetown.<br><br>Associated Rappers} SG / MBunny / Mskurrr / Sa Milian / Yaya]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-000000-2386-77</styleUrl>
