      <Placemark>
        <name>🔴🟠3BP / 4B / HTB</name>
        <description><![CDATA[London Borough of Barnet, Hendon NW4<br><br>'300 Blox Plus' (3BP) are a street gang who are based in the Hendon area, particularly the Bell Vue estate within the NW4 postcode. They are now also known as 4B which stands for both '4Boyz', or '4Block'. Although the Grahame Park estate was the gangs main territory they also drew members from across the NW4/NW7/NW9 and HA8 postcodes, that cover Edgware, Mill Hill and Hendon. 3BP identified as Bloods and some members also had ties with SUK (Street Under Kings) Bloodset from 2006/07. 3BP were the dominant gang in the area from the mid 2000s to the early 2010s.  3BP had loose ties with Stonebridge, South Kilburn and Chalkhill. They had came into conflict with areas including, Kingsbury, Finchley, North Kilburn and Church Road.<br><br>During the early 2010s the 3BP gang began to split up with many members serving long prison sentences, some being deported whilst others had left the road. Personal disputes and members turning on each other lead to serious internal conflicts. 3PB moved to the Hendon area, becoming known by various names such as 3BP, 4Boyz (4B), or 9BLOCK. The other members who remained in Grahame Park would form the new gang known as 9th Street and would become fierce rivals to 3BP. Hendon beef with with 9th Street and Finchley.<br><br>Associated Rappers} SD / Nizzy Numbers / Y.Sosa / Rambo Rich / Grizza Go Getta]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-FF5252-2701-120</styleUrl>
        <Polygon>
          <outerBoundaryIs>
            <LinearRing>
              <tessellate>1</tessellate>
              <coordinates>
                -0.2242112,51.5874297,0
                -0.2223873,51.5848032,0
                -0.2153063,51.5863765,0
                -0.2155423,51.5885896,0
