            </LinearRing>
          </outerBoundaryIs>
        </Polygon>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>🔴9th Street </name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X6RSal4yPUC5aL7xQmLbtz6mz2ZCpvy1g1MqvhMYIHCaE_whzZJhWHj3Gi-d23SJ5auZL7PnRTKOXsf8D5hc20mhYGFGsG5g-0369Iepag4EYQjstX7rOd7bx-0fU2lVRFbQm-fzQhYgFW9duxW-3MO0aQKPZgXAcxWfIJXT4GWwIOCPa2LR6anqwy5NWdv_AnvvGBW?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Barnet, Grahame Park NW9<br><br>9th Street are a large street gang from Grahame Park estate in Colindale within the NW9 postcode. Their estate is known locally as G-Block or Brown Block as the main estate blocks are a distinctive brown colour. There has been several street gangs who had been active on the estate since 1990s most notably 'Thug Fam' (TF), '300 Blox Plus' (3BP) and 9th Street<br><br>Due to the estates size gang members from other areas like Kingsbury and Press Road would often come into the estate to hang out and sell drugs in the late 1990s and early 2000s which would later cause tension with those areas. The main gang from Grahame Park estate during this period were the predominantly Somali gang known as 'Thug Fam' (TF). Their gang had built a fearsome reputation in their area during the late 1990s and 2000s. The gang gained notoriety after three gang members were jailed for shooting dead a police officer in Bradford, West Yorkshire whilst trying to escape following an armed robbery. <br><br>In the mid 2000s another gang formed on the estate known as '300 Blox Plus' (3BP). Although the Grahame Park estate was the gangs main territory they also drew members from across the NW4/NW7/NW9 and HA8 postcodes, that cover Edgware, Mill Hill and Hendon. 3BP identified as Bloods and some members also had ties with SUK (Street Under Kings) Bloodset from 2006/07. 3BP were the dominant gang in the area from the mid 2000s to the early 2010s.  3BP had loose ties with Stonebridge, South Kilburn and Chalkhill. They had came into conflict with areas including, Kingsbury, Finchley, North Kilburn and Church Road.<br><br>During the early 2010s the 3BP gang began to split up with many members serving long prison sentences, some being deported whilst others had left the road. Personal disputes and members turning on each other lead to serious internal conflicts. 3PB moved to the Hendon area, becoming known by various names such as 3BP, 4Boyz (4B), or 9BLOCK. The other members who remained in Grahame Park would form the new gang known as 9th Street and would become fierce rivals to 3BP. 9th Street are allied with Stonebridge, Chalkhill South Kilburn, Finchley and Rayners Lane. They beef nearby 3BP, Kingsbury, Church Road, Wealdstone and Wood Green.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Soze / RzoMunna / N90 / Pumpz / YB / YS / Beezy]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-FF5252-2701-117</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X6RSal4yPUC5aL7xQmLbtz6mz2ZCpvy1g1MqvhMYIHCaE_whzZJhWHj3Gi-d23SJ5auZL7PnRTKOXsf8D5hc20mhYGFGsG5g-0369Iepag4EYQjstX7rOd7bx-0fU2lVRFbQm-fzQhYgFW9duxW-3MO0aQKPZgXAcxWfIJXT4GWwIOCPa2LR6anqwy5NWdv_AnvvGBW?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
