      <Placemark>
        <name>🔵Monks Park (MPM)</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X5-vgTIRWvCNxvmPY0sxaOTvxUoWhxn5P2VA6nK0cxaQvgZVdp0GXlrwpvwOBoNNxrTvMsc_bawN3L_L9jk5FnnK2Zf2LEYJeGzR97VDWEbC-4kl4VODqwV9agX2Z2x2ERMENvtz8b3owdQQqkspswBYVf85XmdyDMZQjxyPjP9pqZgi0Zh-rJqS6wiGPse9IvTnaM?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Brent, Monks Park HA9<br><br>The Monks Park Mob (MPM) are a small street gang based around the Monks Park area of Wembley, located within the HA9 postcode.  The origins of the Monks Park gang can be traced back to the late 1990s when youths in the area were referred to as the 'Monks Park Boys' (MPB), although it was not until the opening of the small McArthur Close estate in 2006/2007, which would bring leading figures from nearby Stonebridge into the area leading to Monks Park becoming closely aligned with Stonebridge. This caused tension with other nearby areas who were beefing with Stonebridge and dragged Monks Park area into the same rivalries. A leading figure from Monks Park and Stonebridge known as 'Smallz' was said to have tied blue bandannas on the poles outside Monks Park shops and then written in blue chalk offensive remarks towards rivals gangs. Those remarks were "Monks Park blue gang, fuck St Raphs, Mozart, KG and PDC". Those remarks were seen as the declaration of war as more of his affiliates from Stonebridge estate would be active in Monks Park. Monks Park are allied with Stonebridge, South Kilburn and Chalkhill. They beef St Raphs, Press Road, Church Road Kingsbury, Wembley Fornia Dons, Kensal Green and Mozart]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-3949AB-2601-77</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X5-vgTIRWvCNxvmPY0sxaOTvxUoWhxn5P2VA6nK0cxaQvgZVdp0GXlrwpvwOBoNNxrTvMsc_bawN3L_L9jk5FnnK2Zf2LEYJeGzR97VDWEbC-4kl4VODqwV9agX2Z2x2ERMENvtz8b3owdQQqkspswBYVf85XmdyDMZQjxyPjP9pqZgi0Zh-rJqS6wiGPse9IvTnaM?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
          </Data>
