      <Placemark>
        <name>🔴Kensal Green (KG / KGB / KGR)

https://web.archive.org/web/20120101145024/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/northwest-london-gangs/kensal-green-bloodgang-kgb

https://web.archive.org/web/20120101033935/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/northwest-london-gangs/mus-luv-crew</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X46wYx6-nrYRBfcEBwnbLaixwGSRQ11DymiQPJxqOdsPLJMAI9vmxR2-dDqyb15GMHIGIjUoh_KUPlpIEdf1EJx3n2YFwCoNKTGwp39U6MXOJj7D12S0uRGEjpcHOlrgft_Qythub0Q83e3BEtLX3phmTEjxm20lq5jRl6MkpwhGlHEq7Dv4dsuDqVP-MO_wT_Mhb8?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Brent, Kensal Green NW10<br><br>Kensal Green (KG) are a street gang from the Kensal Green area, within the NW10 postcode. KG identify as Bloods and are also known as 'Kensal Green Bloodgang', 'Kensal Green Bloods' and also the 'Kensal Green Boys' (KGB). The current newer younger generation from Kensal Green are known as 'Kensal Green Riders' (KGR). The Kensal Green Boys formed around 2005/06 as the younger generation to an older gang known as the 'Mus Luv Crew' (MLC). Some of the KGB gang founding members have older siblings who were part of the 'Mus Luv Crew' (MLC).<br><br> The 'Mus Luv Crew' (MLC) (also sometimes written as Much Love Crew, also known as the Love Lords) formed in the late 1990s with members also located in Brixton. 'Mus Luv Crew' (MLC), the 'Lock City Crew' (LCC) and the 'Kickoffhead Crew' gangs were part of a conflict triangle that encompassed the area of Stonebridge, Harlesden, Willesden and Kensal Green between 1997 and 2004. The gangs had the large Jamaican influences and membership. Members from other rival drug networks, such as the 'Link-Up Crew', were often involved in disputes with the gangs. 'Kensal Green Bloods' (KGB) would form around 2005/06 having superseded the older 'Mus Luv Crew' (MLC). The gang identified as Bloods and formed part of the 'SMG' Bloods movement along with allies of St Raphs and Mozart. The 'SMG' name stems from the "S" in St Raphs the "M" in Mozart and the "G" in Kensal Green.  'SMG' Bloods also had ties with leading figures from areas like Tottenham and Brixton.<br><br>They are allied with the nearby Mozart, St Raphs, Kingsbury, Wembley Fornia Dons, Press Road and North Kilburn gangs. They beef South Kilburn, Stonebridge, Chalkhill, Monks Park, Church Road, Lisson Green and Ladbroke Grove.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-FF5252-2601-120</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X46wYx6-nrYRBfcEBwnbLaixwGSRQ11DymiQPJxqOdsPLJMAI9vmxR2-dDqyb15GMHIGIjUoh_KUPlpIEdf1EJx3n2YFwCoNKTGwp39U6MXOJj7D12S0uRGEjpcHOlrgft_Qythub0Q83e3BEtLX3phmTEjxm20lq5jRl6MkpwhGlHEq7Dv4dsuDqVP-MO_wT_Mhb8?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
