      <Placemark>
        <name>🔵South Kilburn (SSK / MMF / FAC / £R)

https://web.archive.org/web/20111231070909/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/northwest-london-gangs/south-kilburn-mandem</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X78ag9Oc-lB_T651FNrCJZDs3GbHDH1fcD2e_mAh207e8nSDclb4tB_AX_olC5W6sRqM0rZmQGlmTPMKMrdCZkJ8iT5vF55UyMlYZaqhf1bdCJF4ABpnfl5eVlgQrEn5AgJClPoVmwy_nXSomRu5s7LhpD24RX_zbESl7Psz9PyUdNONAZMgwLD3S1aHf9pgweTrfI?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Brent, South Kilburn NW6<br><br>South Kilburn (SK) are a large street gang who are based on the South Kilburn estate within the NW6 postcode. They can be traced back to the 1990s, when South Kilburn (SK) gangs did not really have known names and were referred to as the South Kilburn Mandem (SKM). There have been a number of cliques on the estate that combined make up "South Kilburn Mandem".  The sets have included D-Block (Dickens House), FAC (Family About Cash and Firearms Cartel), MMF (Money Motivated Family), LR (London's Realist) and £R (Everything Relevant and Eating Right).  The current younger generation are known as SSK (South Side Killy).<br><br>The South Kilburn estate is characterised by the same style tower blocks that dominated the nearby Stonebridge estate but, like stonebridge before it, South Kilburn has been going through redevelopment which have included the demolition of much of the estate during the 2010s and the early 2020s. Like their close allies from Stonebridge South Kilburn based gangs identify with blue bandanas. They originally identified with the colour red until 2004. Stonebridge began to identify with blue, as an antagonistic response to a growing number of rival Bloods in North West London and with South Kilburn and Stonebridge sharing the same allies and rivals, they had also began identifying with the colour of blue. The close link that exists between Stonebridge estate and South Kilburn is historical. Criminals from the two areas worked together in the days of the Jamaican "Yardie" gangs, whilst throughout the course of Stonebridge being redeveloped, South Kilburn was used for rehousing many displaced Stonebridge estate residents. The growing enmity between rival "Bloods" (reds) and blues in North West London has developed into a large network of colour based affiliations over the years. In Brent, Stonebridge and South Kilburn are integral to this whilst the smaller affiliated gangs include Chalkhill and Monks Park.<br><br>During the 2000s South Kilburn and Chalkhill gangs were in conflicts with Kensal Green, Kingsbury and Press Road. The late 2000s they were also in conflicts with Mozart, St Raphs, Kilburn Bandits and Wembley Fornia Dons, whilst their main rivalry during the late 2000s and early 2010s was with 'SMG' "Bloods" alliance consisting of St Raphs, Mozart and Kensal Green. Before the mid 2000s both South Kilburn and nearby Mozart were on friendly terms, before falling into a now two decades long beef.<br><br>SK are allied with the Stonebridge, Chalkhill, Monks Park, Ladbroke Grove and Lisson Green gangs, whilst they also have ties with 9th Street and Queens Crescent. They beef with Mozart, Kensal Green, St Raphs, Church Road, Press Road, Kingsbury, North Kilburn, Warwick and the Wembley Fornia Dons.<br><br>Associated Rappers} C Biz / Young Tribez / Hurricane / MLo / F1 / Grindz / Fibbz / Lil Krafty / Broadayay / 18Clapo / 18Mish]]></description>
