      <Placemark>
        <name>🔴North Kilburn / Kilburn Bandits / Top6</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X6NdwiRx3XDdbXmMYdchQrLjiQlnvXRw6Y0bP0qe9FzBjsDSjl2YIZWvwdBqe3wVdwkU0kNzD-mVuWR8Ymz4RU1B2roCaq1BCQhvsQ4smAZlJKjK5SzrI_bxH8yDGVsbuABmtG68OuCbI3LxlRcr-TROjA5RT3uu4th9ofYNcO5XSRF7iru4xRJo4WooJncgdovR4k?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Camden, Kilburn NW6<br><br>Kilburn Bandits are a street gang who are based on estates around Kilburn and Brondesbury on the border of Brent and Camden boroughs situated within the NW6 postcode. Their main locations of activity are the Watling Gardens, Templar House, Webheath, Kilburn Gate, Kilburn Square and Kilburn Vale estates. Kilburn Bandits are also known as both 'North Kilburn' and 'Top6'. In the past there were also sets like GTS (Grind Till i Shine) and the 9Mili Kids (9MK). They identify as Bloods and are loosely allied with Mozart, Kensal Green and St Raphs, as well as having links with nearby Swiss Cottage, Press Road, Kingsbury and the Wembley Fornia Dons.  They beef with nearby South Kilburn, Stonebridge and Maida Vale based gangs.<br><br>Associated Rappers} C6]]></description>
