      <Placemark>
        <name>🔵🔴Queens Crescent (QC/OQC)

https://web.archive.org/web/20110529193918/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/northwest-london-gangs/qc-blox</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X4Ya0QBCs_NulIP-13tBc1-b5QY7OVxxjfXVZQA4eHZ7CN1GdSeacg-6Zfj5iqVlajPBHXRi8c10QjbmP6zKd01z00PU4hrn8qRYgBG0Zsja-X4RRouXsLesylgm0UcpTrLx2z1N2Z_9-8ARwUA9BOH4Jan08vRzLmNhOUf6vaDHVcX7n9OG5M06UwUYcJ5xO2qsnzo?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Camden, Queens Crescent NW5<br><br>Queens Crescent (QC) are a large street gang located on the estates around Queens Crescent which runs through Gospel Oak and Kentish Town in Camden, within the NW5 postcode known as 'Crack 5th'.  They are one of the oldest and largest gangs in Camden.  They are also known as 'Original Queens Crescent' (OQC) and the 'QC Blox'.  Their main estate blocks include the Wendling, Weedington Road, Malden Road, West Kentish Town and Lismore estates.<br><br>Youth gangs have been in existence in the Queens Crescent area of Camden since the early 1990s, although these were largely unknown in the early years owing to the fact that the sets had no real recognisable identities.  By the early 2000s the groups of youths in the area became known collectively as 'Queens Crescent', or 'QC Boys', and later the 'QC Blox'. A number of these smaller gang sets that made up 'QC' would become known under their own names as cliques of the QC Blox, such as the 'Silent Movers' and the 'Krucial Goons'. QC Blox had identified as Bloods during the late 2000s, and into the early 2010s identifying with the colour red. <br><br>The current generation are allied with both 'Peckwater' and 'Cumbo' in their alliance known as '51st' after the NW5 and NW1 postcodes where they are based. They also have links with the 'EC1', 'South Kilburn' and 'Stonebridge' gangs. Their main rivals are 'Active Gxng', 'FSG', 'CT1' and 'NRB' who form an alliance known as '71st' after the N7 and NW1 postcodes where they are situated. They also beef with 'Swiss Cottage', 'Hoxton' and 'Cally Road'.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Ambush / Prospect / Rowdy / Gheezy]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-3949AB-2585-87</styleUrl>
