      <Placemark>
        <name>FSG

https://web.archive.org/web/20110529200320/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/northwest-london-gangs/centric-crew</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X4-F-mXZx5ns5fSWfcj2oBI6xJMsAVRzUjzkxOZ1gMtW7TTaEPej5RKm_u6Rf-ZTtGHCSfaENrLDG-xT1m7RGr_whUS8TOOI1vhHUPRqC-eUPrYwqxnfuf2-kLcoZSfXAzTb0gHAxSePvH_38DzrBE-I0_dcFz5Ql3pg2tCb1oWbRDvUh4jNqk6yFJusIOHTFS0PGCdHDJ9V7mVXrNEI_wOYvSOQYAmCI6LJo_og5lpa1j5?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Camden, Chalk Farm NW1<br><br>Ferdinand Street Gang (FSG) or Finnese $tack Grind (F$G) are a street gang who are based on the Ferdinand and Denton estates in the Chalk Farm area of Camden, within the NW1 postcode known locally as 'Crack 1st'. They take their name from Ferdinand Street which runs through the middle of their estate. FSG stands for both 'Ferdinand Street Gang' and 'Finesse Stack Grind'. They are allied with 'Active Gxng', 'CT1' and 'NRB' in an alliance known as '71st' after the N7 and NW1 postcodes where they are based. They have also had links with 'Willesden Green'. Their main rivals are 'Cumbo', 'Peckwater' and 'Queens Crescent' who form an alliance known as '51st' after the NW5 and NW1 postcodes where they are based.<br><br>Associated Rappers} T Scam]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-FF5252-2701-122</styleUrl>
