      <Placemark>
        <name>🔵Cumbo (OS)

https://web.archive.org/web/20110417045507/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/northwest-london-gangs/cumbo-boys-cumbo-blox

https://web.archive.org/web/20110417045508/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/northwest-london-gangs/somers-town-boys</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X7crPA3YLaRsKNYAvToYw47J-Wx6CpMJN_FLFgpP2yNPrpoSGBRdjfj6lyB6P1gBeDqcI9XwCspvhqatnjhYB9dOqV2X7Rd_hS2Ytws1Ew0UvLM2RcW19aNIZuVEUcjvfYnT7DRpo7PLQT6uqN4Fb8ahGw07k5ID_MDl-Rpk6VwRge5mofYx9VXgIodoc4fCecTEwk?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Camden, Regents Park NW1<br><br>Cumbo Boys are based on both the Cumberland Market and Regents Park estates in the south of Camden located within the NW1 postcode, known locally as 'Crack 1st'. The Cumbo Boys were originally a predominantly white gang bourne out of the nearby 'Somers Town Boys'. Cumbo Boys established their own indentity, and developed as their own gang, during the 1990s becoming more ethnically diverse over time. A lot of the gangs current membership are of congolese descent.<br><br>The Cumbo Boys name has existed since the 1990s despite the turnover of members every few years. By 2007/2008 the gangs close association with 'QC Blox' saw the Cumbo Boys begin to refer to their gang as the 'Cumbo Blox' and adopted gang colours. Their red gang colour was initially adopted by Cumbo owing to the relationship with nearby allies 'QC Blox' who identified as Bloods. However the two would come into conflict and Cumbo would then identify with the colour blue akin to Crips. For a short time during this period the Cumbo members changed the name of their gang to SOC (South of Camden). Some of the current generation form a set known as OS (One Side).<br><br>They are allied with 'Peckwater' and 'Queens Crescent' in an alliance known as '51st' after the NW5 and NW1 postcodes where they are situated. Their main rivals are 'Active Gxng', 'FSG', 'CT1' and 'NRB' who form an alliance known as '71st' after the N7 and NW1 postcodes where they are based.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Chinx / Gutta]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-3949AB-2601-77</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X7crPA3YLaRsKNYAvToYw47J-Wx6CpMJN_FLFgpP2yNPrpoSGBRdjfj6lyB6P1gBeDqcI9XwCspvhqatnjhYB9dOqV2X7Rd_hS2Ytws1Ew0UvLM2RcW19aNIZuVEUcjvfYnT7DRpo7PLQT6uqN4Fb8ahGw07k5ID_MDl-Rpk6VwRge5mofYx9VXgIodoc4fCecTEwk?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
