      <Placemark>
        <name>CT1

https://web.archive.org/web/20110529200320/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/northwest-london-gangs/centric-crew</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X7aZ1SpQeR0CSq8SqVwXMhnrDULBxG7kuHKn92Z63b1mHmDjPXVR4OqvXxiyGrOzDxlezl7nT00OiIKiywYP-iR5yICNkz8ue1c6C5hjtDBq9NtCMh6GaiHvzkGQwYoa7HyBMtcgy3DT3n8ht0jYIvejieASS6h7jz4VEaiRq6Xr7bTxXcHku_Rd5qV4C09R2-J8EWhk10g4gSeH7Hjg_iFCIzbEcHr5aT-BsKBZxY1EJ_j?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Camden, Camden Town NW1<br><br>CT1 are a street gang who are based around Camden Town within the NW1 postcode, known locally as 'Crack 1st'. They are active around Camden High Street and surrounding area including the Curnock, Ampthill, Camden Street, Bayham Place, Gilbey's Yard and Three Fields estates.<br><br>They are a predominantly Somali gang and are the current generation of ''Camden Malis'', following on from older gangs like TMS, ANC and Centric. The ''Camden Malis'' were known as the 'Centric Crew' in the late 1990s, claiming the estate around Oval Road and Gilbey's Yard as their main base. The gang took their name from Centric Close, a small street which adjoins Oval Road. The gang came into conflict with the 'North London Somalians' (NLS), from the Turnpike Lane area of North London. 'Centric Crew' had later become referred to as the 'African Nations Crew' (ANC) to reflect the fact their membership was drawn from a number of African countries, and during late 2007/08 their younger generation, including the younger relatives of the olders, had earned the name 'The Money Squad' (TMS) The TMS gang would go on to dominate the drug trade around Camden Town and Kings Cross, being reported regularly by local press during the late 2000s and the 2010s. Many members of 'CT1' also rep 'Active Gxng' who are a larger and more well known set in the area.<br><br>They are allied with 'Active Gxng', 'FSG' and 'NRB' in an alliance known as '71st' after the N7 and NW1 postcodes where they are based. Their main rivals are 'Cumbo', 'Peckwater' and 'Queens Crescent' who form an alliance known as '51st' after the NW5 and NW1 postcodes where they are based.<br><br>Associated Rappers} 2Smokey]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-FF5252-2601-120</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X7aZ1SpQeR0CSq8SqVwXMhnrDULBxG7kuHKn92Z63b1mHmDjPXVR4OqvXxiyGrOzDxlezl7nT00OiIKiywYP-iR5yICNkz8ue1c6C5hjtDBq9NtCMh6GaiHvzkGQwYoa7HyBMtcgy3DT3n8ht0jYIvejieASS6h7jz4VEaiRq6Xr7bTxXcHku_Rd5qV4C09R2-J8EWhk10g4gSeH7Hjg_iFCIzbEcHr5aT-BsKBZxY1EJ_j?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
