      <Placemark>
        <name>🔵Stonebridge (USG / SGB / TOS / SOS)

https://web.archive.org/web/20111228223443/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/northwest-london-gangs/suspect-gang

https://web.archive.org/web/20110721091918/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/northwest-london-gangs/lock-city-crew-lcc</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X5JFdJpiB2xNEp2gGPA7ltvZ-rHmoWZujaXVKWYVDDlzjngbHg14gWEGMQUwUlP3ug6y3A4ZV9CsnpgUdU8XzLRZY0NlAxdI-Ks1dJkVnniWp_DnMhJoxHQ25lUKuryz7r3w_1XO-sC6u5a7tBYlDa2A7DLHkEm22C5BZd-dvpuuqsQfWQSsvq1Rs_T3w1oqGMGv38?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Brent, Stonebridge NW10<br><br>Stonebridge estate, in the Harlesden area, within the NW10 postcode is home to the 'Suspect Gang' (USG) who formed in the late 1990s as the "Usual Suspects Crew" (USC). They are mostly active on the southside of Stonebridge, although draw members from throughout the Stonebridge area. Their younger generational sub-cliques include 'Stonebridge Gang Bangers' (SGB), 'Thugs of Stonebridge' (TOS), and 'Shoot On Sight' (SOS). They are known to identify with blue and black to oppose rival gangs who identify as Bloods. The northside of Stonebridge, who go by the name 'Northside Bizzy' (NSB), have at times had their own sets such as the 'Skrilla Kidz' or 'Machine Gun Murderers' (MGM) and have in the past had a rivalry and conflicts with southside Stonebridge.<br><br>The gangs roots can be traced back to the days of the 'Lock City Crew' (LCC) who were a Jamaican yardie gang who had been active in the late 1990s and early 2000s. Most of their members came from Harlesden and Stonebridge as well as other areas of northwest London such as Kilburn, Willesden, Neasden, Wembley and Kensal Green.  They organised their activities from their main bases of "Stonebridge Community Centre", just off Hillside on Stonebridge estate and the "Elm Tree" and "Palm Shade" pubs, in Harlesden. 'Lock City Crew' (LCC) were lead by "notorious" Jamaican "Yardie" gangsters which included figures including [Winston "Escobar" Harris], [Stephen "Beamer" Murray],  [Jermaine "My Lord" Hamilton], [Rudolf "Rudy" King],  [Ricky "Diney" Sweeney], [Dean "Bobby" Roberts] and [Tyrone "Lofty" Freckleton], the older brother of Church Road rapper "Nines" and the deceased Church Road member Wayne "Zino" Freckleton. Winston "Escobar" Harris had been arrested and charged multiple times for a plethora of drug offences in Queens, New York City, before he fled to London, settling in Harlesden. Other Jamaican drug dealers would join him, some directly from Jamaica and also others from the USA and formed the 'Lock City Crew' (LCC) around 1995.  Some 'Lock City Crew' (LCC) members had close ties with 'Tottenham Mandem' (TMD) particularly their infamous leader Mark Lambie. The 'Lock City Crew' (LCC) were known for the rivalry with 'Mus Luv Crew' (MLC) from Kensal Green and part of the deadly conflict triangle which encompassed an area from Stonebridge, Harlesden, Willesden and Kensal Green between 1997 and 2004. From 1997/98 onwards and especially following the death of a LCC leader Rudolf "Rudy" King, the 'Lock City Crew' (LCC) began to split. Rudolf "Rudy" King was a leading member of the Church Road faction and was rumored to have been killed by a fellow 'Lock City Crew' (LCC) member. After his death the Church Road faction lead by both Dean "Bobby" Roberts and Tyrone "Lofty" Freckleton started to war with the 'Lock City Crew' (LCC), which is what has caused the longstanding feud between Stonebridge and Church Road, which has since been inherited by the younger following generations from both areas since the early 2000s onwards. The break up of "Yardie" gangs, such as 'Lock City Crew' (LCC) lead to the creation of the present day gangs in North West London in the early 2000s, notably Stonebridge, Church Road, Press Road, St Raphs, Kensal Green, Chalkhill and Kingsbury. Founding 'Stonebridge' (USG) members also included members of another local "Yardie" gang, known as the "Kickoffhead Crew" (KOHC), who were affiliated with the 'Lock City Crew' (LCC).<br><br>The 'original' Stonebridge estate had developed a fearsome reputation for gun crime and drug dealing during the 1990s and early 2000s when the area was dominated by Jamaican 'Yardie' gangs. In the late 1990s the majority of the shooting incidents in Harlesden involved both Jamaican born victims and suspects, but by 2003/04 70% had involved victims and suspects that were British born. The old estates dominating and rundown blocks were demolished during the 2000s and replaced with new lower level housing. The new estate was designed to bring an end to the gun crime, drug dealing and gang violence which helped turned Stonebridge into a no-go zone during the 1990s and 2000s, but problems still plague the area. During the redevelopment of their estate residents were moved to South Kilburn estate, and the two areas who already had ties through family connections became closely aligned. As well as South Kilburn Stonebridge are also allied with areas, including Monks Park, Chalkhill, Ladbroke Grove, 9th Street and Lisson Green. They beef with Church Road, St Raphs, Kensal Green, Press Road, the Wembley Fornia Dons, Mozart, Kingsbury and North Kilburn.<br><br>Associated Rappers} k Koke / Skeng / Fibbz / Eazy / Venda / Krashcorn / Lil Shankz / Lil Jay / Smallz / Squingy / Lefty]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-3949AB-2701-77</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X5JFdJpiB2xNEp2gGPA7ltvZ-rHmoWZujaXVKWYVDDlzjngbHg14gWEGMQUwUlP3ug6y3A4ZV9CsnpgUdU8XzLRZY0NlAxdI-Ks1dJkVnniWp_DnMhJoxHQ25lUKuryz7r3w_1XO-sC6u5a7tBYlDa2A7DLHkEm22C5BZd-dvpuuqsQfWQSsvq1Rs_T3w1oqGMGv38?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
