      <Placemark>
        <name>🔴Kingsbury (OKB)</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X6ZfO2UUkzctvTUkYL_POkucWOw-hmV8mP-Zudoo8zpoEywpLJVo0P4o07ZCPA1tbxR6grmxL9dzLVr_9K2_eqBVV6ABzPorcxllGTSWEEo9ccjN34Kk4_EVbKL7NrmlpJYAz3DUHLmCP41ZU8UsIejkxLAGqP_jYoLDEgZ9Dhv5GPrnAp2-5XpZ0Jnqq0jYvi_4IVV?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Brent, Kingsbury NW9<br><br>Original Kingsbury Boys (OKB), who were formerly known as TFL, which stood for 'True Family Loyalty' or 'Thugs For Life', are the street gang based around Kingsbury, within the NW9 postcode. Kingsbury identify with the colour of red and from the later 2000s to early 2010s they had identified as Bloods.<br><br>Some leading figures within the 'Lock City Crew' (LCC) such as Rudolf "Rudy" King and Ricky "Diney" Sweeney were from Kingsbury, although also had ties with nearby areas such as Church Road and Press Road.  In the late 1990s and in early 2000s Kingsbury, and their allies Press Road, were known to operate on nearby larger estates, including the Chalkhill and Grahame Park estates,  causing serious conflicts with those areas. Following the break up of larger gangs, like 'Lock City Crew' (LCC) in the early 2000s a new young generation from Kingsbury formed known as TFL which could stand for 'True Family Loyalty' and 'Thugs For Life' who identified as Bloods and were affiliated with  Press Road, St Raphs, Kensal Green and Mozart. Since the mid 2010s Kingsbury gang have been known as OKB (The Original Kingsbury Boys). Kingsbury are now allied with Mozart, Kensal Green, Press Road, St Raphs, North Kilburn and the Wembley Fornia Dons. The gang beef Chalkhill, A9, 9th Street, South Kilburn, Stonebridge and also Monks Park.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Greezy / B Money / BR / K9]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-FF5252-2601-122</styleUrl>
