      <Placemark>
        <name>🟢Willesden Green (WGB)</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X55VSmzOld8MNbnWyVEe5hb07c77qLr8QQUW0C_pY9bAZOmp7tkzmYewyWgjX9b8PrFES9Ozk-RU520Eis4G2rveKo5NIwyFZH958ZbE1Z3hBJmTpNQgCvVCFU2qtkb_smB_38ObuaXkgDCJ-nRMWv_yHSSl7MunAMV9rPbVgKCcBez5kJqlK4aNc4fUsU1VIpiqSQ?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Brent, Willesden Green NW10<br><br>Willesden Green Boys (WGB) are a small street gang who are based in the Willesden Green area, within the NW10 and NW2 postcodes. They are predominantly based on the Griffin Close estate but they are also located around the Cornwall Gardens, Marley Walk and Kingston Court estates.  They are allied with FSG, Church Road and North Kilburn. Their main rivalry is with Swiss Cottage, South Kilburn, Stonebridge and Press Road.]]></description>
