      <Placemark>
        <name>🔘🔴Warwick </name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X7saVehg9sqV9RPJKXJ7VIExkRDMxWnMc0Y62tu5LdlafJDp7jKRk6XGyZgLte2BcfvFwcMnpFvRpwqNo-JvvGSAuzz2pM94apcNaVXNldZhHFZpqzS9vV7MnJkp6hD7IgbqO9LH7RXRXz12bXqCFo6VNYzjvcEdBCUXa0_sVRVocHgRrJ7-erSupqe32rjQCzPHlY?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>City of Westminster, Harrow Road W2/W9<br><br>Warwick are a small street gang located around the Harrow Road area on both the Warwick and Brindley estates, within the W2 postcode and Amberley estate, within W9 postcode. They identify with the colour of grey and they had also been known as 'Touch Money Greys' (TMG). They are the younger generation to the 'Grey Dayz' (GD) gang, who formed part of the ''Horror Road Alliance'' during the mid to late 2000s. The alliance was made up of a number of smaller groups based on estates around Harrow Road.  These sets were 'Grimiest Movement' (GM), 'Street Dreams' (SD), who had wore brown, 'Grey Dayz' (GD) who had wore grey and C.R.I.M.E (Can’t Roll In My Ends), who wore blue colours. Warwick are allied with Mozart.  The current Warwick generations are more likely to be aligned with nearby Harrow Road Boyz (HRB). They beef with nearby Lisson Green, Ladbroke Grove, Stonebridge and South Kilburn.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-757575-2501-77</styleUrl>
