      <Placemark>
        <name>🔵South Acton / 3rdSet / Original 3rd

https://web.archive.org/web/20120423225918/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/west-london-gangs/murder-dem-pussies-mdp</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X7N0AXaGQoPnEMpGFlXupl0iDQktVz_74z-Iem9THxaianQkimlGT3WIujXArs5TjVRYJpN3LtkDsa3YZKb3DRbc_5j0r2kmOF5-H_CMZTOgsULDkAuMNlwTrDODq_6EiyPJBfPVP3hmrc_ed-5-ZBLM_RileHgxl7cy7x5SHKZ_hu8XrfRvX5cgD4BFhGY_7LxB88?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Ealing, South Acton W3<br><br>South Acton (SA) are known as '3rdSet' or 'Original 3rd'. The gang are mainly based on the South Acton estate, within the W3 postcode. They identify with the colour of blue. They are the younger generation from South Acton who had followed on from the MDP group, who had been active on the estate during much of the 2000s and the early 2010s.  MDP, which stands for 'Murder Dem Pussies', but also for 'Money Drugs Power' and 'Make Death Possible'. MDP are primarily based throughout Ealing (W3, W5, W7, W13), and Hammersmith & Fulham (W6, W12) with smaller representation in Hounslow (W4). MDP were active on estates throughout west London, including the Green Man, Gurnell Grove, South Acton, Friary Park and Trinity Way estates in Ealing and also the Becklow Gardens, Cleverly, White City, and William Church estates in Hammersmith & Fulham. MDP were the younger generation to the MPR gang, which stands for 'Make Paper Regardless', 'Money Power Respect' and 'Make Prayers Reality'. Later the MDP gang formed newer younger sets and affiliated groups including FDA, which stands for 'Fuck Da Authority', 'Feel Da Aggression' or 'Force Da Anger', GFL which stands for 'Gunz Fully Loaded', and OMD, which stands for 'Original Mandem'. The gang were known to identify with blue colours although the FDA clique had also identified with the colour brown and had been referred to as 'Killa Brownz'. MDP gang were most known for their fierce rivalry with Southall (Gritset gang) and Hayes (Purple Hayes), as well as the Ladbroke Grove gangs. They also inherited a rivalry with the Stick'em Up Kids (SUK) based in the Battersea and Clapham Junction area of South London. Some of this generation from Shepherds Bush had also been closely affiliated with another group known as the 'Instruments of Cruelty' (IOC). IOC was a larger collective of youths from across West London, which included members from MPR, MDP, Queens Park and Ladbroke Grove. IOC had two sides. There were the number of older individuals trying to make something of themselves in the music industry and there were younger rappers associated who were still active gang members. South Acton are currently allied with nearby 54z and Ladbroke Grove. They beef nearby Shepherds Bush, Northolt, Greenford and Southall.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Kavelly / Stretch]]></description>
