https://web.archive.org/web/20120423225918/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/west-london-gangs/murder-dem-pussies-mdp</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X5YgisUPi13_abM_m5eAWcRKtAx4KPdZRor-uObSFGiwwftUP6inUhmoisCB8LeFvYKfaHAYd5g9d7sbhZu7kDFJ8RGdC40Zkn8RXF3AQM8wsj3mLKq8FBFP5WPHZt_J7td4eX8mg6akuFiJ98OyflccYR6IMLckR2zoYTuRXJt8GTZ1qmn2m5esR5xKvb3jXqU4jnR?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Ealing, Acton W3<br><br>In the late 1980s Shepherd's Bush like many inner-city areas saw the development of a new type of youth gang that drew membership from local estates, most notably the White City estate but also other estates including Lime Grove, Becklow Gardens and Emlyn Gardens estates, and also nearby Acton estates, such as Trinity Way estate. They were described as steaming gangs but by the early 1990s they had progressed into the drugs economy with Shepherd's Bush area seeing a number of gun killings. By the mid 1990s youth street gangs in the area had acquired a reputation for their steaming and robbery offences while the older members were inextricably linked to the drugs trade. Some of the earlier gangs growing from the mid 1990s were the 'No Face Crew', a combination of two separate gangs and the 'Borer Man Crew' from White City estate, who were mainly African, would often come into conflict with the mainly Caribbean 'Smokers Crew', based in nearby Ladbroke Grove. These conflicts were later replaced by the newer younger generations. The 'Cold Hearted Crew', from the Edward Woods estate and Shepherd's Bush based 'Urban Virus'.<br><br>The Shepherd's Bush gangs were infamously dubbed 'Rolex Robbers' soon after the millennium with the gang members taking advantage of the wealthy residences throughout the borough and nearby Kensington and Chelsea. One group of 'Rolex Robbers' foiled in 2002 were named by the media as the 'Underground G's'. Another similar style gang foiled was dubbed "Prada Mob". The most prominent Shepherds Bush gang forming around 2005/2006 are known as MDP,  which stands for 'Murder Dem Pussies', but also for 'Money Drugs Power' and 'Make Death Possible'. MDP are primarily based throughout Ealing (W3, W5, W7, W13), and Hammersmith & Fulham (W6, W12) with smaller representation in Hounslow (W4). MDP were active on estates throughout west London, including the Green Man, Gurnell Grove, South Acton, Friary Park and Trinity Way estates in Ealing and also the Becklow Gardens, Cleverly, White City, and William Church estates in Hammersmith & Fulham. MDP were the younger generation to the MPR gang, which stands for 'Make Paper Regardless', 'Money Power Respect' and 'Make Prayers Reality'. Later the MDP gang formed newer younger sets and affiliated groups including FDA, which stands for 'Fuck Da Authority', 'Feel Da Aggression' or 'Force Da Anger', GFL which stands for 'Gunz Fully Loaded', and OMD, which stands for 'Original Mandem'. The gang were known to identify with blue colours although the FDA clique had also identified with the colour brown and had been referred to as 'Killa Brownz'. MDP gang were most known for their fierce rivalry with Southall (Gritset gang) and Hayes (Purple Hayes), as well as the Ladbroke Grove gangs. They also inherited a rivalry with the Stick'em Up Kids (SUK) based in the Battersea and Clapham Junction area of South London. Some of this generation from Shepherds Bush had also been closely affiliated with another group known as the 'Instruments of Cruelty' (IOC). IOC was a larger collective of youths from across West London, which included members from MPR, MDP, Queens Park and Ladbroke Grove. IOC had two sides. There were the number of older individuals trying to make something of themselves in the music industry and there were younger rappers associated who were still active gang members.<br><br>The younger generations who followed on from 'MDP' in the early 2010s were known as 'Stay Banging' (SB). The younger generation to them were known as 'Original Bush Youngers' (OBY) before splitting into new sets, which included '12Anti', '12World' '1200' and '8712'. The current sets are most active around the White City, Cleverly, Becklow Gardens and Emlyn Gardens estates in Shepherds Bush W12 and also the Friary Park and Trinity Way estates in Acton W3. They identify with the colour red to oppose rivals from the nearby South Acton and Ladbroke Grove areas who identify with the colour blue. The largest, and most well known, of these current sets are '12Anti' (12A). The current sets are affiliated with Hounslow, Northolt, Greenford and Southall, whilst their main rivalry is with Ladbroke Grove, although they also beef nearby South Acton, Hayes and West Drayton.<br><br>Associated Rappers} BOX12 / A2Anti / Fdot / Sav12 / Ryder / Little Katty]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-FF5252-2501-125</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X5YgisUPi13_abM_m5eAWcRKtAx4KPdZRor-uObSFGiwwftUP6inUhmoisCB8LeFvYKfaHAYd5g9d7sbhZu7kDFJ8RGdC40Zkn8RXF3AQM8wsj3mLKq8FBFP5WPHZt_J7td4eX8mg6akuFiJ98OyflccYR6IMLckR2zoYTuRXJt8GTZ1qmn2m5esR5xKvb3jXqU4jnR?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
