      <Placemark>
        <name>🔴Mozart (HRB)

https://web.archive.org/web/20120421105216/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/west-london-gangs/mozart-bloods-cfr</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X4Nak8vQzTEjr1Xl1VUmI00SibzMBFH-0lDw9U9KzOB37sM_2clVMRlg3cXLcJmiKfz4acuLpaC5G6rf29GEqTOdgXBDQtVhLxXFmRteDiQHueP7XTfrF1jNS3f3obobmREbYonVKzpC1naMcpjB2V6aR1J8siETOKpJnf1gDlTxfpSSEbEooM4nuSyxPp3CTkTfSQ?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>City of Westminster, Harrow Road W9/W10<br><br>The 'Harrow Road Boyz' (HRB) are a large street gang based around Harrow Road on the Mozart estate and the adjoining Queens Park, Avenue Gardens and Lydford estates, situated within the W9/W10 postcodes.  The gang are also known as 'Mozart' and also 'Mozart Bloods'. The gang identify with the colour red and they identified as Bloods from the mid 2000s to the early 2010s.<br><br>The Mozart estate, nicknamed "Mexico" and "Zart", for many years has been a notorious estate dubbed 'Crack City' by the media in the 1990s. Mozart estate was built during the early 1970s and was built up of distinctive red blocks of flats that have largely been renovated or redesigned since the early to mid 1990s. Mozart gang began identifying as Bloods during the late 2000s through their gangs familial association with Brixton’s CFR gang (who are in turn a part of the 031 Bloods movement). The 'Mozart Bloods' or Mozart 'HRB' are closely connected to the other Blood gangs across West, and North West, London and were part of the 'SMG' Bloods movement, with their allies St Raphs and Kensal Green. The 'SMG' name stems from the "S" in St Raphs the "M" in Mozart and the "G" in Kensal Green. Before Mozart Bloods formed there were a number of smaller sets during 2006/2007 that were located in the Harrow Road area who were collectively known as the "Horror Road Alliance",  which included 'Grimiest Movement' (GM), 'Street Dreams' (SD),  C.R.I.M.E (Can’t Roll In My Ends) and 'Grey Dayz' (GD).<br><br>Mozart are allied with nearby Kensal Green, St Raphs, Press Road, Kingsbury, Warwick, North Kilburn, and also Wembley Fornia Dons. Mozart also have close familial connections to CFR and 37, from South London. A more recent alliance has formed with Active Gxng from Camden. Some recent issues between 37 and Active Gxng have strained the relationships with their long time allies in South London. Their main rivals are nearby South Kilburn, Ladbroke Grove, Lisson Green and Stonebridge.  In the past Mozart also had beefs with Church Road, but the two areas are now loosely allied as they share the same rivals.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Fredo / Ratlin / Lil Dotz / Trigz / Rugrat / DB9 / Boss Belly]]></description>
