      <Placemark>
        <name>🔵🟢Ladbroke Grove / LA (CGM)</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X58Bv4KIoxDAW62kYI6peYqPYoroXKIGtHhQny0uyjXMOQ6FGoZPV4xSQkRWYM-78mPR2I-ro7PQlCogkcpZoVxJ8P7-A29PEfIYtMwOG24igRBtEN7R9RKMOSq4MHzoZnYs0_Wp7TahEkmr34Tj3eI4AXJVOP6bpxqXku5tfhVBZLXvY1S5b_vnsQNpeXPigewWhs?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Royal Borough of Kensington & Chelsea, Ladbroke Grove W10<br><br>CGM are a street gang based around Ladbroke Grove, within both W10/W11 postcodes. Within Ladbroke Grove there are several 'blocks', such as "P-Block" which includes Portobello road, Portobello Court, Powis Square, Powis Gardens, Powis Terrace and Powis Court, "Latimer" / "LA" which includes the Silchester and Lancaster West estates, and nearby Delgarno Gardens estate, "Golborne" which includes the areas around Golborne Road, including Trellick and Edenham estates, and "Woodz" which is the Edward Woods estate in neighbouring Hammersmith & Fulham borough, although in gang terms is considered to be Ladbroke Grove's territory. Ladbroke Grove members are also active on the Brunel estate (W2).<br><br>In the 2000s there were many youth gangs and music crews in Ladbroke Grove area such as the 'Grove Side Goons', 'Str8 From Da Manor' and 'Total Knockout'. Another known street gang during that time was 'Out To Terrorise' (OTT). One well known gang that existed prior to the mid 2000s were known as the 'Smokers Crew' a crew who were largely of Caribbean descent. Their generation was followed by a gang based on the Edward Woods estate, which went on to become known as 'Cold Hearted Crew', also an urban music collective. They had came into conflict with the 'Urban Virus Crew' who were from Shepherds Bush. The relationships between the young people from Ladbroke Grove have usually been contentious with the Shepherd's Bush area to the west and Harrow Road which includes the Mozart and Warwick estates to the north<br><br>During the late 2000s into early 2010s the main gang in the Ladbroke Grove area was the 'Ladbroke Grove Bloods' (LBG) who were allied with the nearby Lisson Green, South Kilburn and Stonebridge gangs,  whilst they had primarily come into conflict with the Harrow Road area most notably the Mozart and Warwick gangs. The 'Ladbroke Grove Bloods' had faded away by 2012/2013, after a number of prominent members were imprisoned. With the Ladbroke Grove olders locked up, the youngest generations who followed were part of a short lived set known as 916. The youngest members of 916 then formed CGM, originally more commonly referred to as 1011 after the W10 and W11 postcodes. CGM is said to stand for several things which can include 'Constantly Getting Money' 'Conspiracy Gang Members', and 'Certified Grove Members'. Under their "1011" name, CGM would become prominent in the 'UK Drill' scene. In 2018 Met Police applied for "Criminal Behaviour Orders" (CBO's) to be handed to the group to stop them from making UK drill music. Many of their early videos were deleted off YouTube, later used in court as evidence to help convict members of the gang. As a result the old '1011' name fell out of use. CGM now identify with the colour blue and now self identify as Crips, even though Ladbroke Grove used to identify as Bloods. CGM are allied with South Acton, Rayners Lane, South Kilburn, Stonebridge, Lisson Green and 9th Street. They beef the Mozart, Shepherds Bush, Warwick, Church Road, Northolt, Southall and Greenford areas.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Digga D / Sav'O / Horrid1 / ZK / MSkum / Rack5 / T.Y / Dodgy / Loose1 / Sini Sayso]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-3949AB-2401-77</styleUrl>
