in gang in the Ladbroke Grove area was the 'Ladbroke Grove Bloods' (LBG) who were allied with the nearby Lisson Green, South Kilburn and Stonebridge gangs,  whilst they had primarily come into conflict with the Harrow Road area most notably the Mozart and Warwick gangs. The 'Ladbroke Grove Bloods' had faded away by 2012/2013, after a number of prominent members were imprisoned. With the Ladbroke Grove olders locked up, the youngest generations who followed were part of a short lived set known as 916. The youngest members of 916 then formed CGM, originally more commonly referred to as 1011 after the W10 and W11 postcodes. CGM is said to stand for several things which can include 'Constantly Getting Money' 'Conspiracy Gang Members', and 'Certified Grove Members'. Under their "1011" name, CGM would become prominent in the 'UK Drill' scene. In 2018 Met Police applied for "Criminal Behaviour Orders" (CBO's) to be handed to the group to stop them from making UK drill music. Many of their early videos were deleted off YouTube, later used in court as evidence to help convict members of the gang. As a result the old '1011' name fell out of use. CGM now identify with the colour blue and now self identify as Crips, even though Ladbroke Grove used to identify as Bloods. CGM are allied with South Acton, Rayners Lane, South Kilburn, Stonebridge, Lisson Green and 9th Street. They beef the Mozart, Shepherds Bush, Warwick, Church Road, Northolt, Southall and Greenford areas.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Digga D / Sav'O / Horrid1 / ZK / MSkum / Rack5 / T.Y / Dodgy / Loose1 / Sini Sayso]]></description>
