        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X51LVt5Cgh5Bq2q4eURxoo-dG1t4d7vzO93WGmGcljfJSoWOMCrqoRH7DBLIjkqNFisuT0MUJk5yOWp-d5QS15ecNM3SamodZNNOP23SNk1iwUQlEfo9S6XGauO2h3FQAoIkQovUSlu-atU8D_t4uW2KQuQfmc5PQmoJQKd3Pnjk2gidpZXjqc0HwQGTHDd7KBfUwTB8ylC3Fjgkn9hdnWZ1CzEAAyEFovPr4vvutMhtG2q?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Ealing, Northolt UB5<br><br>156 is a gang alliance of Southall (UB1), Northolt (UB5) and Greenford (UB6). That alliance are active on several estates throughout the three areas.  Their main estates are the Islip Manor, Racecourse, Medlar Farm and Radcliffe Way estates in Northolt (UB5), the Cowgate estate in Greenford (UB6) as well as the Golf Links estate in Southall (UB1). The Northolt based set are known as NGang, whilst there is also the RCG (Racecourse Estate Gang). The Greenford set are known as 6Gang, whilst the Southall set are known as Zone1.<br><br>There is also another set located in Southall, known as YSG, who are based on the Havelock estate (UB2). YSG are often mistakenly assumed part of 156, although they are affiliated their set are not actually part of the alliance and in fact have previously had some minor conflicts with 156. Both 156 and YSG identify with the colour red.<br><br>They are allied with Shepherds Bush. They are most known for their fierce rivalry with Rayners Lane, but also beef with nearby Hayes, West Drayton, Wealdstone, South Acton and Ladbroke Grove.<br><br>Associated Rappers} NitoNB / Workrate / MadMax / 6ixty / AbzSav]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-FF5252-2684-125</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
