      <Placemark>
        <name>🟠Meridian/MWF</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X6kGsiStGda2OWK1AO7mxxsyhXolnKOZVsATFIK-VpDYVmScln4cXKQ-t3BkukNQGU_FF7xDmM4BpZRxlOq9_lkPNfCkFnH4M6nDgeA2PEE45-8tkhsdZ3veVUDoHcgfBbgeW9CeL2HAfPwokEhCPrIcM7adpv-vecA8J2tMmTQZB-VJNL_v6wGikUweWjVeCdn8SM?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Haringey, Tottenham N17<br><br>MWF are a street gang who are based on the Meridian Walk estate in Tottenham, within the N17 postcode. The area is in the far north of Tottenham on the border with Edmonton.<br><br>Although Meridian is a small block the estate is well known having been at the forefront of the local Grime music scene in the 2000s with many well known MCs and rappers hailing from Meridian during the mid 2000s. They were featured on tv series 'Murder Blues' following 'Operation Trident' officers investigating a shooting on Meridian involving the 'Meridian Crew' and members of the 'Wood Green MOB' who had been allies at the time in summer 2004. They had links with Wood Green MOB and Palmers Green gangs as well as most other nearby blocks in Tottenham. The older generations from the 2000s were known as the 'Meridian Crew' or 'Bloodline'.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Skepta / Bossman / Big H / Prez T / JME / Dillz (MWF)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-F57C00-2801-120</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X6kGsiStGda2OWK1AO7mxxsyhXolnKOZVsATFIK-VpDYVmScln4cXKQ-t3BkukNQGU_FF7xDmM4BpZRxlOq9_lkPNfCkFnH4M6nDgeA2PEE45-8tkhsdZ3veVUDoHcgfBbgeW9CeL2HAfPwokEhCPrIcM7adpv-vecA8J2tMmTQZB-VJNL_v6wGikUweWjVeCdn8SM?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
