      <Placemark>
        <name>🔴OFB

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OFB_(rap_group)

https://web.archive.org/web/20111231163728/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/north-london-gangs/broadwater-farm-bloodline

https://web.archive.org/web/20111231053010/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/north-london-gangs/tottenham-mandem-northstar

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tottenham_Mandem</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X7CseN4DIYjjRLOnoLzYdiosMdCfFtIWoz8uEHsGa8qWkBlxgqMSqBWd3TgS4XzRD1utORklrEaF4b2UhJ-RH3ntAVY559zLXuN7xS7gBPzV6Ai9yVuNtLFka77x1W_47h-NhpVE2Zl_BR3ZxU6FKMBSg-lKnZJVQ1Q5g58R6QRZMdvemtDBtmhthkKU9v7L0TKI2k?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Haringey, Tottenham N17<br><br>OFB (Original Farm Boys) are a large gang who are from the Broadwater Farm estate in Tottenham, known as 'The Farm', within the N17 postcode. Broadwater Farm, also referred to as the "Lost Blocks", was the main base for older gangs like the 'Broadwater Farm Posse' and later 'Tottenham Mandem' (TMD) and the associated music crew known as 'NorthStar', which influenced a younger generation known as 'Star Gang'<br><br>Whilst members maintained 'NorthStar' is for entertainment purposes only and the sourcing local music talent the name was the influence for the following younger generation from Broadwater Farm known as ‘Star Gang’. They began to self-identify as Bloods and refer to their cliques as Bloodline and Bloodgang or by the acronoym BWF (Broadwater Farm) and collectively everyone from the area would be known as FMD (Farm Mandem). 'Star Gang', BWF, FMD and so on were also closely linked with their original 'Tottenham Mandem' (TMD) members. The demarcation of Broadwater Farm in terms of new names, and the assertion of the Blood identity has now grown since 2005/06. By then the main rivals to Broadwater Farm grew to be the 'Wood Green MOB', who were an ally of Tottenham until the early 2000s and by 2007/08 they would also begin to beef with 'Dem Africans' (DM) from Edmonton, another area which was once closely allied with Tottenham.<br><br>By the early 2010s the younger generation of the 'Star Gang' had began to make a name for themselves and would go on to form their own group known as OFB (Original Farm Boys) who are now one of the largest and most well known gangs in London.  Like the 'Star Gang', they identify with the colour red and have inherited many of the same allies and rivals as them. Historically OFB had been closely allied with GMG/AP and most other Tottenham sets, particularly NPK who along with OFB are the two largest gangs in Tottenham. Since the late 2010s and early 2020s the close relationships between OFB and NPK have soured leading to a complicated "on-off" relationship following members of OFB and NPK turning on each other accusing each other of snitching when OFB and NPK members were jailed for killing a Wood Green member. Since then the tension between the formerly close allies has developed into a fierce rivalry.  The rivalry between OFB and NPK is complicated as the two gangs had been very closely affiliated for many years with family and former friends now beefing each other. They are allied with N15. They beef with Wood Green/N22, Edmonton/N9, TPL/DC8 and TPL/OTP as well as former allies NPK, GMG/AP and Hornsey/V8.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Headie One / RV / Abra Cadabra / Bandokay / Double Lz / SJ / Kash / Akz / Dezzie / Kush / Izzpot / YF / Bradz / Dsavv]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-FF5252-3001-122</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X7CseN4DIYjjRLOnoLzYdiosMdCfFtIWoz8uEHsGa8qWkBlxgqMSqBWd3TgS4XzRD1utORklrEaF4b2UhJ-RH3ntAVY559zLXuN7xS7gBPzV6Ai9yVuNtLFka77x1W_47h-NhpVE2Zl_BR3ZxU6FKMBSg-lKnZJVQ1Q5g58R6QRZMdvemtDBtmhthkKU9v7L0TKI2k?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
          </Data>
