      <Placemark>
        <name>🔵Reed Road / Bruce Grove</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X6AeuJkTpOV9ZNrXSjWk4FAln3Qlurrfq5AbyTc-KiDR9PywyCZRi8u7nqvF9P1L5vgmtyYvLx1lJau-IEoTK8gZVtdPtuc16rsCnnF06y_mDUCYdXRD1gnwlOd27dxpKjcy_hT9IsFBr8-oL-LZlj7eEUgpCwoCf6gOzHHEducp1fv78k_QkpY_HPmnafN7LUTh6A?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Haringey, Tottenham N17<br><br>Reed Road, sometimes referred to as 'Reed Road Crips', are a street gang based around Reed Road and the Bruce Grove area of Tottenham, within the N17 postcode. Reed Road are the younger generation to an older gang known as EvaStrap sometimes referred to as the EvaStrap Yard Manz. EvaStrap are an older generation predominantly of Jamaican descent and were considered a Yardie gang. EvaStrap were affiliated with 'Red Brick' from Edmonton (N18), and other Tottenham gangs.  They, like most other Tottenham street gangs, come into conflict with the gangs from Edmonton (N9). During the late 2000s EvaStrap were in conflicts with the Dem Africans (DA) gang from Edmonton (N9), and were involved murders of two 'Dem Africans' (DA) gang members, in January 2008. In 2009 an 'EvaStrap' member was also convicted for killing an Edmonton teenager in 2007.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-3949AB-2801-77</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
