      <Placemark>
        <name>🔴Tiverton

https://web.archive.org/web/20111231031737/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/north-london-gangs/tiverton-piru</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X5X2hdAdKrWFkfSmpEt13Mj1zw00-nerzN8AObo8Bm24MENZpTsedPnV86wJFw6Dh0hV0ZxmmchyU7JFkQEG596JSHaAgcrKZCThO4dUARiAsmNeSBouGcgdH8_Ce9qYCkMQQOPLsQuurZQesLV_C_b96Nq__zY5SwyXleqAAjtxnryUsF1Q8GA0oGzVtwzysiGgZ4?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Haringey, South Tottenham N15.<br><br>'Tiverton Mandem' are a street gang located on the Tiverton estate and the nearby estate where the Bourne and Twyford tower blocks are located in South Tottenham within the N15 postcode. South Tottenham is referred to collectively as "T-Block", "15TH Side" and "N-One-Five". During the late 2000s the gang had adopted the identity of Piru's and the wearing of burgundy bandanas along with allies from Manor House and Stamford Hill (MTS).  The area is also more commonly referred to as 'One Five' although also as 'T-Block' or simply Tiverton and 'N15'.<br><br>Tiverton, along with nearby Stonebridge, is considered to be the Broadwater Farm of N15 in that it became an area most central to gang activity in South Tottenham. Tiverton estate formed a part of the "N15" alliance along with neighbouring Ida, Edgecot Grove, Bourne and Twyford blocks, and nearby Stonebridge estate, a once notorious hotspot of N15 South Tottenham gang activity next to Seven Sisters underground station.  The Stonebridge estate is three streets set out in a triangle with Stonebridge Road to the north, Ermine Road to the east down to Plevna Crescent in the south. Tiverton and Stonebridge estates had been an area of 'independent' gang activity since at least the early 1990s. The estates had been used to house Jamaican immigrants, although by the end of 2009/10 it had become one of London's most diverse areas with South Tottenham, in N15, said to be the most culturally diverse area in Europe with over 300 languages spoken. The area has been noted for serious 'organised' criminal activity including Colombians and Turkish-Kurdish criminals. Some original and older members from Broadwater Farm were re-housed in the south of the borough which also contributed to the earlier development as an independent unit.<br><br>Tiverton and South Tottenham generally had gone through periods of conflict with the gangs further north, in the N17 section of Tottenham. During 2004/2005, shortly after the development of smaller area based gangs, Tiverton began conflict with 'Broadwater Farm' and 'NPK'. These conflicts never escalated into serious rivalries as they were usually suppressed amongst a more pressing and growing rivalry with other areas most notably Wood Green and Edmonton. Tiverton are affiliated with nearby N15, Manor House and Stamford Hill. Their main rivalry is with Wood Green/N22, Edmonton/N9 and GLane.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-A52714-2801-122</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X5X2hdAdKrWFkfSmpEt13Mj1zw00-nerzN8AObo8Bm24MENZpTsedPnV86wJFw6Dh0hV0ZxmmchyU7JFkQEG596JSHaAgcrKZCThO4dUARiAsmNeSBouGcgdH8_Ce9qYCkMQQOPLsQuurZQesLV_C_b96Nq__zY5SwyXleqAAjtxnryUsF1Q8GA0oGzVtwzysiGgZ4?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
          </Data>
