      <Placemark>
        <name>🔘Hornsey / V8 / Villside / 8th

https://web.archive.org/web/20110528041625/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/north-london-gangs/grey-gang-hornsey

https://web.archive.org/web/20110721112952/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/north-london-gangs/hornsey-mafia-hornsey-mandem-hornsey-mob</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X4-bo6wFiFtLhtlYJ0_OzdrTXRXb2Hco5mb3_3bgzBq4i65f6641WtAXJVXPWbZxy2_64gR8Scifm-KdC8CS8YKdj2v9IycTikwxfW7I16fSf1CQ2b9tKgvrvYb4T_8QRh0ao7U9xTRRAUdHTObgkuevkD7at68Kxhj7QWzXTh2GWDXhMWFGQFv965HPpb_n0pOQz4?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Haringey, Hornsey N8<br><br>'Hornsey/8th' are a street gang from Hornsey, within the N8 postcode. 'Hornsey' gangs are most active on the Lightfoot and Campsbourne estates. They are also known as 'Villside' and 'V8'. The roots of the Hornsey gang can be traced back to the 1990s when a gang known as the 'Hornsey Mafia', or more commonly the 'Hornsey Mandem' (HMD), were active.<br><br>The 'Hornsey Mafia' began in the late 1990s shortly after the 'Wood Green Firm' started. The 'Hornsey Mafia', or 'Hornsey Mandem', grew and recruited from the same schools as the 'Wood Green Firm', and as the two areas were in such close proximity Hornsey and Wood Green were closely allied. The membership was drawn from around Hornsey, Stroud Green and Crouch End,  although the real defined territory could be found on the Campsbourne and Lightfoot estates and in the Priory Road/Priory Park areas. Hornsey were also allied with the 'Shadow Kings' gang which is partly why they, like Wood Green, came into conflict with parts of South Tottenham. In the early days Hornsey also had a short lived rivalry with the 'Legends of Stokey' (LOS) from Hackney. 'Hornsey Mandem' had firmly established their reputation by 2001 and they had started to recruit their own younger generations.<br><br>The younger Hornsey generation were known collectively by various names including 'Hornsey Mandem' , 'Hornsey MOB' (partly because of the affiliation with the Wood Green MOB) and then 'North Side Soldiers' (NSS), to reflect that the gang was not all from Hornsey. The younger generations had also began to move in area based sets, rather than one large unit as they had before. By the mid 2000s the Hornsey sets were somewhat independent around the Campsbourne, Lightfoot and Chettle Court estates.  'Hornsey' re-grouped collectively in the late 2000s and became known as 'Grey Gang' or 'Grey Bandana Gang' (GBG), forming links with Priory Court, Busy Block, Manor House, Stamford Hill and Tottenham.  Despite the history of affiliation with Wood Green a robbery followed by tit-for-tat stabbings caused conflict between the Hornsey and Wood Green areas and since 2008 the two have been in conflict. Cliques within Hornsey of this period also included 'Warlordz', 'Young Kingz' and 'Villside Youngers'. The current generation are now known as 'Hornsey/8th', or 'Villside', and 'V8'.  They are allied with NPK and TPL/DC8.  They beef with Wood Green/N22, Edmonton/N9, TPL/OTP and 1T.<br><br>Associated Rappers} MoStack / Scarz / Biz / Kraze / Shoota]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-757575-2901-77</styleUrl>
