      <Placemark>
        <name>🔴Stamford Hill (MTS/135 Piru)

https://web.archive.org/web/20120116150116/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/north-london-gangs/mts-135-piru</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X6LAHwEsbGpZOF3koyYhLWwOLrweZbKIAISS9hjqBHFwC7Ei3bFpzVnMAHgqYK6rPJUESW20CW0yPldSUR31Il1fCK6VgqLZvUhOEx35iltL6ENhcWRhMDwDaDWFbjBRBv15-FuOfT28x7gd2Dgs_IrYqcdLmagEQqdU6Ac_4DoNqntGTXVgDG2iLCYEWg12RByutE?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Hackney, Stamford Hill N16<br><br>The 'Manor House Boys' and the 'Stamford Hill Mandem' are allied linked up street gangs both based around the north of Hackney, within both the N4 and N16 postcodes. The linkup is referred to as 416 (after the two areas postcodes) or also MTS (Manor To Stamford). MTS is a combination of the two formerly independent gangs.  The 'Manor House Boys' from the Woodberry Down estate and the 'Stamford Hill Mandem' from Stamford Hill. Both gangs began in the late 1990s and between 2003 up to 2007 had endured very much an 'on-off' relationship with each other before joining up and taking on nearby rivals the 'Lordship Boys' and 'Legends of Stokey'. By late 2007 both the gangs were closely aligned and began to identify with burgundy bandanas and refer to themselves as the ‘135 Piru’ or MTS 135 (pronounced One Tray Five).<br><br>The 'Manor House Boys', once referred to as the 'Woodberry Down Boys', are located on an estate disconnected from the rest of Hackney. Other parts of Hackney have previously not considered Manor House to be part of the borough, and had associated it more with the Tottenham area and borough of Haringey. As a result there have been periods where 'Manor House' members have been more associated with the older Haringey gang members over the years. There has however also been periods when 'Manor House' have been in conflict with South Tottenham gangs such as 'Ida'. Their longer term rivalry has been with gangs from both Stoke Newington and Finsbury Park. By 2005 gang cultural definers became more integral to the gang identity and 'Manor House' began to use their acronym MH, interpreted as numerous things including “Money Hungry”. The gang initially identified mainly with the colour of black, before they began identifying with burgandy and red. The increase in definers came at a time when there was friction between the 'Youngers' and 'Olders' in the gang. The current generation are known as 'Original Manor House' (OMH) and '4Section'.<br><br>'Stamford Hill Mandem' (SMD) would also have a change of the gang identifiers at a similar time to Manor House and by late 2005 they were referring to Stamford Hill as "Blood Hill", and had begun to identify with the colour of red. The current generation of the 'Stamford Hill Mandem' are also known as LLNB (Long Live Nana Banger). 'Nana Banger' was a DJ and associate of 'Stamford Hill', who was stabbed to death after an 18th birthday party in 2018.<br><br>Both sets are affiliated with Homerton and historically have also been affiliated with nearby Tiverton, Hornsey and Busy Block. They have generally been more affiliated with nearby Tottenham gangs further north, rather than fellow Hackney gangs. They beef Stoke Newington, London Fields, A-Road and Southwold.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Clavish / Kirky / Dimma]]></description>
