      <Placemark>
        <name>Andover

https://web.archive.org/web/20110604212751/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/north-london-gangs/finsbury-park-fpk</name>
        <description><![CDATA[London Borough of Islington, Finsbury Park N4/N7<br><br>Andover are a street gang based on both the Andover and Six Acres estates in the Finsbury Park area of Islington, within the N4 and N7 postcodes. Historically there have been on and off relationships between local gangs in Finsbury Park and parts of Tottenham and Manor House, although relationships often shift amongst the younger generations. During the 2000s and into early 2010s Andover had ties with Crouch Hall Court and Wray Kray, whilst they came into conflict with Busy Block and AG. The current generation from Andover are allied with Wray Kray, Holloway, Highbury, London Fields, EC1, SOS, Red Pitch, Elthorne and New Olreans. Their main rivals are nearby Manor House, Essex Road, Cally Road and Hoxton.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-FF5252-2701-120</styleUrl>
        <Polygon>
