      <Placemark>
        <name>🔴🔘Highbury / HB5 / OVE

https://web.archive.org/web/20110602201101/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/north-london-gangs/highbury-blockz</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X7GHXgwT04ajWrYVwLsHHT5ykQ0SmlX-6Q33IV_BLvCt5d_7AftaSOge2WwWn_FDF2QsM_4-s_UpfoFUfxPbhwlLV3OoZz0TCMTMOSsuWRsj1e0_KxuqN54zKUyob8t0BnE7QreVkD7V5Mht5cAra1KNBTdUp8mkx_Oo4PvtuX4ADOgMDDPylaXENFsf9zM6LRFiNI?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Islington, Highbury N5<br><br>The 'Highbury Boys', or the 'Highbury Blockz', are a coalition of former independent gangs based on the Highbury estate (CR£AM Blocc or £ Gang),  the Harvist estate and Highbury Grange (Highbury Hoodstarz gang). They have been known to identify with the colour of both red and grey. The current younger generation from the Highbury estate are known as 'HB5' and 'OVE', who are also a music group. Over the years Highbury have had ties with the Andover, Finsbury Park and Quill Street areas.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Joe Black / Bagzoverfame / Riskey / Greeze]]></description>
