      <Placemark>
        <name>🔴Hoxton

https://web.archive.org/web/20120102102126/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/north-london-gangs/hoxton</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X7LiaM2FLzTlpylBZnOber5mB1Wnk47KlPwiRUJBwkd21_2Q9DPhJFW7f5fzKWO5nXP0PiOx-w7pHdwi9Us6Tshj7wsGvxjNBIOqErZiMEdisT0dS0cVSUPsHxVXQIgOjPvMV4l9hRAYVmy3BDn0KyWobIPixBvUIf98r7Q75KcOUf0XPpZjNCllg9em0L91BJ725U?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Hackney, Hoxton N1<br><br>Hoxton Boys are a street gang who are based in the Hoxton area of Hackney, within the N1 postcode.  They are situated around Murray Grove, Pitfield Street and New North Road on nearby estates including St Johns, Wenlock Barn, Arden and Colville. The Hoxton area is also known as 'Gullyside', or the 'Gully'. Hoxton Boys sets have also included 'Set Pace Gang' (SPG), and the 'Hoxton Young Gunners' (HYG). Hoxton Boys are also referred to as 'HOX' and identify with the colour red.<br><br>The 'Hoxton Boys' had formed from an older gang known as 'Love of Money' (LOM). 'Love of Money' (LOM) are the oldest generation in the area and are one of London's oldest gangs having originated in the 1980s, and were most active during the 1990s up to the mid 2000s. 'Love of Money' (LOM) have close links with nearby Holly Street and Essex Road, and are often recounted as "real money makers", who specialised in armed-robberies and supplying drugs. From early they often targeted youths from nearby London Fields, which caused a rivalry that still exists today between the London Fields area against Hoxton and Holly Street. Historically they have been allied with Holly Street and Fellows Court.  In the late 2000s and early 2010s they had conflict with nearby London Fields as well as EC1, Queens Crescent, Tufnell Park, Gilpin Square and Well Street.<br><br>The current generation from Hoxton are closely allied with nearby Holly Street, Cally Road, Essex Road, Homerton, De Beauvoir, Pembury and Kingshold. Their main rivals are the Fellows Court, London Fields, Stoke Newington, Red Pitch, EC1, Stoke Newington, A-Road, Mountford, Cumbo, Queens Crescent, Wood Green, Peckwater and Andover gangs.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Slipz / S.Savv / ShotGun / Popz / Lil slipz]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-FF5252-2801-125</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
