      <Placemark>
        <name>🔴Red Pitch (RPG)

https://web.archive.org/web/20120502185221/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/north-london-gangs/red-pitch-rp</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X48hF9_SkKZN2HdkfT7tEomsPJGeBgHYfJIXe-QeN-2R_7gaKuaa9l5jh_hID73te--vNIcEVb_XLvi6bAIJFLf8RE7FhGmyiV7EH1WIvxGK3qIrjyDn-NxIthIsu9e2owf1CruLIHiAfLLNwKFL3uiHJ4fVlwKtTKk3daxZ2L4a1ugCN43J0D-3JD5snt8xmIO4qA?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Hackney, Newington Green N16<br><br>Red Pitch are a street gang based around Newington Green on the border of Hackney and Islington boroughs, within the N16 postcode. Red Pitch Gang originated on the Shellgrove estate, but they are also active on the Mayville and Kerridge Court estates.  The gang were formed in the late 1990s and were initially known as "Pellerin Road Boys". The group later became known as "Red Pitch" because of a red sports pitch within the estate where the gang hung out,  and they did not like the "Pellerin Road Boys" name. The new Red Pitch name stuck and was later adopted by the youngest generations of the gang.<br><br>'Red Pitch Gang' (RPG) are closely affiliated with the nearby 'Soldiers of Shakespeare'.  In their early years leaders of the allied 'Soldiers of Shakespeare' (SOS) gang also doubled as generals in the 'Red Pitch Gang'. Historically 'Red Pitch' had been affiliated with the nearby Holly Street, Essex Road and London Fields Boys, with some members affiliated with the Holly Street Boys and the London Fields Boys, who are both fierce rivals, disputes and infighting within the gang caused tension. During the 2000s they were in conflict with the EC1, A-Road, Hoxton and Fellows Court gangs. The relationships between these areas have altered throughout their younger generations throughout the 2010s.<br><br>The current generation are allied with London Fields, Stoke Newington, A-Road, EC1, Somerford Grove and the Soldiers of Shakespeare. They now beef nearby Essex Road, Hoxton, Holly Street, Cally Road, Pembury and Homerton.<br><br>Associated Rappers} MStizzy / SP / Swift / Stayhustling]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-FF5252-2901-117</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X48hF9_SkKZN2HdkfT7tEomsPJGeBgHYfJIXe-QeN-2R_7gaKuaa9l5jh_hID73te--vNIcEVb_XLvi6bAIJFLf8RE7FhGmyiV7EH1WIvxGK3qIrjyDn-NxIthIsu9e2owf1CruLIHiAfLLNwKFL3uiHJ4fVlwKtTKk3daxZ2L4a1ugCN43J0D-3JD5snt8xmIO4qA?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
