      <Placemark>
        <name>Stoke Newington / Stokey16 / Lordship

https://web.archive.org/web/20120421070223/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/north-london-gangs/l-o-r-d-lordship
</name>
        <description><![CDATA[London Borough of Hackney, Stoke Newington N16<br><br>Stokey16 are a large street gang who are based around the Stoke Newington area, within the N16 postcode. The Stoke Newington gang are active on the Lordship North, Lordship South, Hillcourt, Smalley and Rectory estates (N16) and the Nightingale estate in nearby Clapton (E5). The gang are the younger Stoke Newington generation who have followed on from the older 'Lordship Boys' (L.O.R.D) and the 'Legends of Stokey' (LOS) divided between Smalley and Rectory estates.<br><br>The 'Lordship Boys' have been established since the 1990s, and are now an older generation. 'Lordship Boys' main base is Lordship South estate but also occupy the Lordship North and Hillcourt estates. 'Lordship Boys' also have an influence over the nearby Smalley and Rectory estates who combined had formed a new street gang known as 'Legends of Stokey' (LOS) between 2003 to 2007. The 'Legends of Stokey' (LOS) made their reputation carrying out robberies in the area and quickly acquired rivalries on all sides, including the Mothers Square, Stamford Hill and Manor House gangs. By 2006 the gangs numbers had soon dwindled following pressure from Stamford Hill and Manor House. A number of the prominent members from Stoke Newington also went to prison, whilst their younger generations from 2007/08 onward have fallen under the Lordship, Smalley and Rectory gangs. The current youngest generations from these three areas, as well as the Nightingale estate, combined make up the larger "Stokey16" gang also known as simply as 'Stokey', or 'Stoke Newington'<br><br>Their main allies are London Fields, A-Road and Red Pitch. They beef nearby Manor House, Stamford Hill, Holly Street, Pembury, Homerton and Hoxton.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Yargz / Diablo / L'zz / Ra$hy / T16]]></description>
