      <Placemark>
        <name>EC1 / Easy Cash

https://web.archive.org/web/20110531002155/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/north-london-gangs/ec1---easy-cash</name>
        <description><![CDATA[London Borough of Islington, Clerkenwell EC1<br><br>Easy Cash (EC1) are a large street gang who are based in the Finsbury and Clerkenwell areas both in the south of Islington, within the EC1 postcode, with some small territory within the WC postcodes in Camden borough. They originated from the Spa Green estate, but are also active on other nearby estates including Margery Street, Kings Square, Finsbury and Bourne estates. They are also known as 'EC1', 'EC' and 'C1'. The gang was formed in the late 2000s by the youngest members of an older gang known as the 'Krucial Goons'. The purpose of their gang was to generate income, rather than reputations gained through violence. And this was the reason for the name 'Easy Cash'. EC1 are affiliated with London Fields, Queens Crescent and Andover. The gang beefs Cally Road, Essex Road, Hoxton and Holly Street.<br><br>Associated Rappers} YT / MJ / Kenka]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-000000-2501-77</styleUrl>
