      <Placemark>
        <name>🟢Wood Green / 22

https://web.archive.org/web/20120427082631/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/north-london-gangs/wood-green-mob</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X7tJkqT6AtfUC_uh_7cnKGfAmkkW9cOYAm6Gk-fviAWQWl9EUvYqgpR_u5V3g5unUJQ7aCKM2U5PEnUNxgPA5eSKVa5_LI7pEhubbdhwkr9MkkShu4G10XmaMaOGYNz4rCFp1dm08OzLZSiu1oFYYVW6_g41cGMP3qD5iwMUaU1cFe0wiUBJasgc7L72ep20Vbj-YY?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Haringey, Wood Green N22<br><br>Wood Green MOB are a large street gang who are based on a number of estates and blocks around Wood Green, within the N22 postcode. The gangs main areas of activity are the Sky City, Sandlings, Noel Park, Commerce Road and Acacia Road estates. In the early 1990s a gang known as the 'Firm' were active across North London, central to the Tottenham area, but extending to incorporate areas such as Edmonton and Wood Green. By 1996/97 the different area based sets of the 'Firm' had began to identify more with the local areas which is when the 'Edmonton Firm',  or 'Edmonton Mandem' (EMD) and 'Wood Green Firm' (now Wood Green MOB) were established. The 'Wood Green Firm' grew around Gladstone Avenue in Noel Park and on the Sandlings estate. The early generations of 'Wood Green Firm' began to call themselves ‘Junior Mafia’ or ‘Junior Mafia Woodz’ in the late 1990s and early 2000s. Following generation of Wood Green members became known collectively as 'Wood Green MOB' during the early 2000s.  Sets developed geographically placed on local estates including the Avenues (Noel Park), Acacia Road, the Sandlings, Commerce Road, Bracknell Close, Progress Way and Sky City.  A host of gang names have existed under the umbrella of the 'Wood Green MOB',  such as the 'Shell Town Soldiers', 'Junior Mafia Woodz', 'Mobstarz', 'Hoodfellas', City of Gods' (COG), 'Paper Before Pussy' (PBP), the 'Grizzy Side Riders' (GSR) and 'Mobcity Young Gunners' (MYG). The sets loosely denote the different age generations of the gang but 'Wood Green MOB' remains as the collective identity.<br><br>In the late 1990s and the early 2000s the 'Wood Green Firm' were in conflict with the 'Hackney Boys',  a conflict that had came to be generalised as ‘Hackney' versus 'Tottenham’. At this period in time Wood Green and Tottenham were closely affiliated as were Edmonton and Hornsey. Wood Green were also affiliated with an old African set known as the 'Shadow Kings', who's membership came from both Wood Green and Tottenham. The 'Shadow Kings' came conflict with 'Tiverton' from south Tottenham in the mid 2000s. During the conflict the Wood Green membership was torn between loyalties to Tottenham and the 'Shadow Kings'. The members who went on to side with the 'Shadow Kings' then gained a deadly new enemy in Tottenham gangs and by 2005 Wood Green began serious conflict with Tottenham, particularly the gangs from 'Broadwater Farm', 'Ida' and 'Tiverton' areas.  Edmonton and Wood Green had a shared hatred of Tottenham and formed an alliance. With gang definers playing a larger part in gang activity at the time,  symbolism and gang colours started to be used more frequently by younger members of the gangs. The 'Shankstarz' and 'Wood Green MOB' both identified with the colour green and had began sporting green clothing and bandanas. 'Wood Green to Edmonton Green' became known as the ‘Green City’ alliance, and 'Shanktown to Mobtown' (as Wood Green was known). This generation from Wood Green also had ties with the 'Meridian Crew' and 'P-Town' (Palmers Green). They also formed links with with London Fields who older Wood Green gang members once had a shared hatred of alongside their former Tottenham allies during the earlier conflict with Hackney.<br><br>The current generation of the 'Wood Green MOB' continue to be active in the rivalry with Tottenham particularly with OFB, NPK and N15. This rivalry between Wood Green and nearby Tottenham has now become one of the longest running and most active rivalries in London, and claimed numerous lives over the past 16 years. Wood Green also beef with Hornsey. Wood Green and Hornsey had been long-term allies up until late 2008, when younger members fell into conflict with one another. Wood Green are currently allied with Edmonton and TPL/OTP. Their main rivals are the OFB, NPK, N15, TPL/DC8, Hornsey, Hoxton, Finchley, Busy Block and 9th Street gangs.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Crash22 / BD / DipDat / Ridz / GKay / G Money]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-558B2F-2701-77</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X7tJkqT6AtfUC_uh_7cnKGfAmkkW9cOYAm6Gk-fviAWQWl9EUvYqgpR_u5V3g5unUJQ7aCKM2U5PEnUNxgPA5eSKVa5_LI7pEhubbdhwkr9MkkShu4G10XmaMaOGYNz4rCFp1dm08OzLZSiu1oFYYVW6_g41cGMP3qD5iwMUaU1cFe0wiUBJasgc7L72ep20Vbj-YY?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
