      <Placemark>
        <name>🟣NPK

https://web.archive.org/web/20110526170217/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/north-london-gangs/northumberland-park-npk</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X4yPypn8CTOMQwtlFB1PzwZbcMqDPdaIgoJ6nCUDXVsc1ed5vXoWfqOfsMUMz4SU4dElxpHqydf7D5afSTaKnjZQt8Cv7glNRO-oTkDQLwaqmFoaxyYEg5xMcFr_kiwMc9H9fiwNDM0S7LHqGAEmMvuoBdg8CYUoWIQ1WvCAZGsqi6vSWhwdQTTNILIlhqQsa76KIs?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Haringey, Tottenham N17<br><br>NPK are a large street gang based around Northumberland Park and Park Lane in Tottenham, within the N17 postcode. NPK can be translated as 'Northumberland Park Killers' and 'Northumberland Park Kids', or simply as an abbreviation of 'Northumberland Park'. The current NPK generation are also known as 'Park Lane Boys' (PLB) and "Sin Squad". The latter is the name used more for the music side of the gang. They are known to identify with the colour purple and refer to the Northumberland Park area of Tottenham as 'Purple City'.<br><br>NPK began to emerge as an independent gang around 2002 having, like most areas of Tottenham, previously been a part of the 'Tottenham Mandem' (TMD) organisation. 'Tottenham Mandem' (TMD) were central to Broadwater Farm estate but had influence over other blocks in Tottenham. In the early to mid 2000s the larger alliances like the 'Tottenham Mandem' (TMD) began to break up into smaller estate based sets and later independently operating gangs. NPK formed one of the largest and most active of these new Tottenham sets. In the gangs early years they were affiliated with the 'Shoddy Crew' (SC) and 'Bun Dem Crew' (BC) who were music crews active in the Grime scene at the time.<br><br>In 2003 NPK began to beef with the 'Shankstarz' gang from Edmonton. Early NPK and Shankstarz beef was the start of the Tottenham and Edmonton rivalry that has been ongoing ever since. Before this 'Tottenham Mandem' and 'Edmonton Mandem' had for many years been close allies but when the larger alliances began to break up into smaller estate based sets made up of the younger generations many of these old alliances would end and newer rivalries would begin. During the mid 2000s Tottenham gangs, including NPK, also began to beef with former 'Tottenham Mandem' allies Wood Green. Historically NPK have always been affiliated with most other Tottenham gangs, particularly OFB, although over the recent years there has been accusations of snitching and disputes between members of the two gangs which has resulted in a complicated 'on-off' relationship and the two gangs are now beefing each other.<br><br>Most of the Tottenham based gangs tend to be allied with each other against outside rivals such as Wood Green and Edmonton.  The main allies of NPK are TPL/DC8, GMG/AP and also Hornsey/V8. They have also had loose affiliations with a few other areas including Hoxton, Manor House and Stamford Hill.  NPK beefs Wood Green/N22, Edmonton/N9, TPL/OTP, WC8, N15 and OFB.  The rivalry between OFB and NPK is complicated as the two gangs had been very closely affiliated for many years with family and former friends now beefing each other.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Uncs / GP / KayKay / Poppy / LR / ND / MLoose / Tugga / Sneaks / Stewie / Bully B]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-9C27B0-2701-77</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X4yPypn8CTOMQwtlFB1PzwZbcMqDPdaIgoJ6nCUDXVsc1ed5vXoWfqOfsMUMz4SU4dElxpHqydf7D5afSTaKnjZQt8Cv7glNRO-oTkDQLwaqmFoaxyYEg5xMcFr_kiwMc9H9fiwNDM0S7LHqGAEmMvuoBdg8CYUoWIQ1WvCAZGsqi6vSWhwdQTTNILIlhqQsa76KIs?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
