      <Placemark>
        <name>🔴NRB</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X49iWPcQPODoOg6dDdJcuWMpoZgr694G2co0mUDWypk326Zd9NiH_BWxq5x2zHDRaoC-dKLLcaVDCTLaIWhgljbkU0bcV6BdyDBB-rXwY_Qp0my0D_pnS-cIxduIrqaWBf5y8CDtjjnbVAyo56iU8nP3JSVbweh5BaCFPuNBrSlmpxmUYuGIqSSTtUCwY5bXLrGxF2bmzVQN09ixjF_NxONjv3oO3Az4EqtBQTqO6WRmVxs?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Islington, Holloway N7<br><br>North Road Bandits (NRB) are a street gang who are based around North Road and York Way between Kings Cross and Holloway in Islington, within the N7 postcode.  Their gangs main blocks are the Hyde Village estate, also known as the Corporation Street estate, York Way estate and also Market estate.<br><br>The Market estate has been a notorious estate in Islington for several decades and was demolished and rebuilt during the late 2000s and early 2010s. Historically gang members from the area identified as the 'Market Gang' (MKT) or also some affiliated more with nearby 'Cally Road'. <br><br>They are allied with 'Active Gxng', 'FSG' and 'CT1' in an alliance known as '71st' after the N7 and NW1 postcodes where they are based. They also have links with 'Cally Road', 'Essex Road' and 'Hoxton'. Their main rivals are 'Cumbo', 'Peckwater' and 'Queens Crescent' who form an alliance known as '51st' after the NW5 and NW1 postcodes where they are based. They also beef with 'Elthorne', 'New Orleans' and 'Wray Kray'.<br><br>Associated Rappers} ML / Yevz]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-FF5252-2601-120</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
