      <Placemark>
        <name>🟡🔵CHC / Wray Kray

https://web.archive.org/web/20110519100555/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/north-london-gangs/crouch-hall-court-c-blocks</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X6tfft-wxqEWTMiE21Mki-VLCQnsKmYFwvtCAVwn_Qq2_iGA4bj_g-ulC90nXf23BPk4Ap76tIRstp3prwVQ26WyejZbKETMkdBuo_b7gi6Ij0xXQQnKTBUerETdFB0fLdp_fARs2SQSKzDAwjbtcmY68_vI-KSb3-uRev61IVBxatGlTwB0TTvj_UqT28yfbIxuQg?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Islington, Crouch Hill N19<br><br>Crouch Hall Court (CHC), also known as 'C-Block', and 'Wray Kray' are allied sets based on both Crouch Hall Court estate and Wray Crescent area in the Crouch Hill and Finsbury Park areas of Islington within the N4 and N19 postcodes. 'Crouch Hall Court' were formed in the late 2000s, by the 'Cally Road' members who had relocated to the Crouch Hall Court. They identify with yellow and dark blue colours. In the 2000s and early 2010s they were affiliated with Andover and NPK. They came into conflict with Busy Block and Hornsey. The current generation are allied with nearby Andover, Elthorne and New Olreans. They beef NRB, Cally Road, ATeam and Hoxton.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-FFEA00-2401-77</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X6tfft-wxqEWTMiE21Mki-VLCQnsKmYFwvtCAVwn_Qq2_iGA4bj_g-ulC90nXf23BPk4Ap76tIRstp3prwVQ26WyejZbKETMkdBuo_b7gi6Ij0xXQQnKTBUerETdFB0fLdp_fARs2SQSKzDAwjbtcmY68_vI-KSb3-uRev61IVBxatGlTwB0TTvj_UqT28yfbIxuQg?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
