      <Placemark>
        <name>🟢Edmonton / N9

https://web.archive.org/web/20111230114711/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/north-london-gangs/dem-africans

https://web.archive.org/web/20120103064427/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/north-london-gangs/shankstarz

https://web.archive.org/web/20110719072627/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/north-london-gangs/edmonton-firm-edmonton-mandem</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X5PkEQzUs0fiwLoP9cnB__yYuignl_CnMzE2U61wCirF8T6mmLf7BOmHJE4OsbRUgIKXEKFtUTF2XZinf6rmZ261RBMiJuvUWYdlLVQ8aRcKWJWyFXJm31RLVZkz-2Vm55tCV22qq-65HzGo_7vBhr-ANG6E98xWp43QfAEiFRzjNUvC8GGXdb_v3nWJorbYLiDNZY?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Enfield, Edmonton N9<br><br>Edmonton, within the N9 postcode, has been the location of several generational street gangs since the 1990s. The first gang to have influence over Edmonton in the late 1990s and the early 2000s were known as the 'Edmonton Firm' or more commonly the 'Edmonton Mandem' (EMD). The gangs main territory was within the N9 postcode which covers the lower Edmonton area although they would draw their membership from across the borough, especially Edmonton Green, upper Edmonton, Jubilee Park, Bush Hill Park and the Ponders End area. This generation had grown in schools across Haringey and Edmonton would arise as the 'Firm' throughout 1994/95 following on from the Tottenham gangs like the 'Broadwater Farm Posse', and the 'Tottenham Mandem (TMD). When the other areas within the 'Firm' began to associate more locally areas outside of Tottenham became known as 'Wood Green Firm' (which later became known as Wood Green MOB) and 'Edmonton Firm'/ 'Edmonton Mandem' (EMD) from 1996/97. In the mid to late 1990s much of North London (Tottenham, Edmonton, Hornsey and Wood Green) were aligned with one another and the 'Edmonton Mandem' were equally as known as their allies in the 'Tottenham Mandem'. Much of the gang activity in North London from the 1980s and the early 1990s was heavily influenced by Tottenham street gangs and older criminals emanating from the Broadwater Farm estate.<br><br>The younger generation of 'Edmonton Mandem' (EMD) who formed in 2002/03 became known as the 'Shankstarz'. The 'Shankstarz' developed as the younger generation to the old 'Edmonton Mandem' (EMD), and earned the Edmonton area the nickname Shanktown for their numerous stabbings and knife-point robberies. 'Shankstarz' were most active around Lower Edmonton with Bounces Road estate being the main base for 'Shankstarz' and 'Edmonton Mandem' (EMD). They were also active in other areas of the borough including the New Southgate area and Alma Road estate, in Ponders End. The 'Shankstarz' were known for their rivalry with NPK from Tottenham. The beef started around 2003 and was the start of the Edmonton-Tottenham rivalry which has been ongoing to this day. Before this 'Edmonton Mandem' and 'Tottenham Mandem' had been closely allied for many years. Their beef with NPK brought them into conflicts with other Tottenham sets including 'Tiverton', 'Ida' and 'EvaStrap'. The main allies of 'Shankstarz' were the 'Wood Green MOB'.  Edmonton and Wood Green had a shared hatred of Tottenham and formed an alliance. With gang definers playing a larger part in gang activity at the time,  symbolism and gang colours started to be used more frequently by younger members of the gangs. The 'Shankstarz' and 'Wood Green MOB' both identified with the colour green and had began sporting green clothing and bandanas. 'Wood Green to Edmonton Green' became known as the ‘Green City’ alliance, and 'Shanktown to Mobtown' (as Wood Green was known). They were also allied with P-Town (Palmers Green). By the late 2000s some younger members began to refer to themselves as 'Camp' or 'North Camp'.<br><br>By 2007 another Edmonton gang began to make a name for themselves. They are known as the 'Dem Africans' (DA) and are particularly active on the Barbot estate (a.k.a 41st Side), Edmonton Green estate, Osward Place and nearby Croyland Road. The 'Dem Africans' (DA) olders were primarily African youths who started to make a name for themselves in 2007 and were one of a handful of new younger gangs emerging in Edmonton at that time. The others were 'Red Brick Thugs' and 'Edmonton Grey Gang'. Some 'Dem Africans' olders had a few years earlier been part of an old street gang known as ‘Tottenham Foosie Thugs’ 'Foosie Thugs' moved away from Tottenham and began to occupy new areas such as the new Barbot estate redevelopment in the mid 2000s.  The original members used the acronym BMW, which is said to stand for 'Boydems Most Wanted' before they became known by their 'Dem Africans' (DA) gang name. 'Dem Africans' (DA) formed independently of the 'Shankstarz', and were not a spin-off or an associated younger generation. 'Dem Africans' (DA) grew to become the largest and most dominant street gang in the area by the late 2000s. They soon began to recruit their own younger generation, who became known as the 'Young Dem Africans' (YDA). They are also referred to as the 'Dark Green Riders' (DGR), as they identify with dark green colours. YDA recruited their own younger generation known as 'Edmonton Young Gunners' (EYG). 'Dem Africans' (DA) would come into conflict with the 'Black Gang' from Enfield Island Village and GMG from across the Enfield area. YDA often violated 'Black Gang' and 'GMG' members, by travelling in large numbers to Enfield to rob them. The late 2000s saw YDA begin conflicts with 'Grey Gang' and 'Red Brick' from upper Edmonton (N18) and the Tottenham gangs particularly 'NPK' and 'Broadwater Farm' (N17) and 'Tiverton' and 'Ida' (N15).<br><br>By the early 2010s the 'Dem Africans' (DA) were the largest, and most active, gang in the Edmonton N9 area, but by the mid 2010s the younger generations from Edmonton began to be known under new names. The current Edmonton sets now include O9B (Original 9 Boyz), 900/9Double0/41stSide, 3x3/BR9 (Bounces Road 9), and AFG/Afghan0 (All Fuckries Gang). The current sets are affiliated with each other under the "Edmonton N9" name taking on their rivals from Enfield and Tottenham. Like their predecessors, these current sets identify with the colour green and they are allied with Wood Green. The main areas of activity are now the Barbot estate and Edmonton Green areas, the Bounces Road area and the Beaconsfield and Fore Street estates. They are also located further north around Mottingham Road and Cuckoo Hall, in an area known as 'CBlock'. These newer Edmonton N9 sets have inherited rivalries with OFB, NPK, N15 and GMG/AP. <br><br>Associated Rappers} Tion Wayne / E1 / ZT / Rowdy / MSplash , A1 From The 9 / TKay Madmax]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-097138-2601-77</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
