      <Placemark>
        <name>🟤Skengfield / 3rdSide / AP / GMG</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X6aMpDcziGSaum5v9sYjkSlNSHfu6vmyIqK36qx-d-XF3h12A8hseA6LmkJWmvNVj81Rk2UFNnAC4-p3aYGKxsre2MNoMtklV9TETHJjc7ghKJdyh9CKJ-qf9JBdGgp0vYiD3BUBLuNV3IUyB6f1P_c7kcz7rMHgZ8lPLP0Q04wNwG7wXeeoEy4BYTktpyCUu2Bn1Y?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Enfield, Enfield EN3<br><br>GMG (Get Money Gang) are a large street gang based in the Enfield area of North London, within the EN3 postcode. The gang are mostly active on the Albany Park, Lytchet Way and Enfield Island Village estates, although draw members from throughout Enfield. The current generation are known as AP (Albany Park) and 'Skengfield'. They formed in 2007/08 as a younger off-shoot set to the Black Gang from Enfield Island Village. They are a Somali dominated gang, although not all its members are of Somali origin. They are known to identify with the colour brown. In their early days they were targeted by the 'Dem Africans' (DA) from Edmonton who would travel up to Enfield to attack and rob Enfield youths which created a fierce rivalry between the two areas which grew during the late 2000s and 2010s. They have been allied with NPK, OFB, EnnyTown, Hornsey and TPL/DC8.  Their main rivalry is with Edmonton/N9 and Wood Green/N22.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Poky / SKizz / Jango / Unknown C6 / Wez'B / Tuco / Scarzy]]></description>
