      <Placemark>
        <name>🟢TPL / OTP / SmokeSquad</name>
        <description><![CDATA[London Borough of Haringey, Turnpike Lane N8/N22<br><br>TPL, which stands for 'Turnpike Lane' or 'Touch Paper Lane' and 'Take People's Lives', are a street gang situated around the Turnpike Lane and Ducketts Common area, drawing the members from the N8, N15 and N22 postcodes. TPL are of predominantly Somali and Albanian origin. TPL was created through the merger of two local street gangs during the mid 2000s. The local Somali gang were known as 'North London Somalians' (NLS), and the 'Young Militant Somalians' (YMS) The Albanian side were known as 'Albanian Young Gunners' (AYG) 'Young Albanian Gangsters' (YAG) and 'Real Albanian Gangsters' (RAG). In the late 2010s the two TPL sets would start to come into conflict and are now rivals.<br><br>The Somali dominated set are now known as DC8 (Duckets Common 8) and the YMS (Young Militant Somalians). Their members are mainly drawn from the N8 postcode area. The gang are known to identify with the colour of blue. They are allied with nearby Hornsey/V8, GMG/AP and NPK. TPL/DC8 beef nearby OFB, N15, TPL/OTP, 1T, Wood Green, Edmonton and Finchley/197<br><br>The predominantly Albanian dominated set are now known as OTP (Original Turnpike), or 'SmokeSquad'. Although they are predominantly Albanian, the gang are not exclusively of Albanian origin and have members from other backgrounds including Turkish and Black British. Their set predominantly draw membership from within the N15 and N22 postcodes. The TPL/OTP sets are now allied with the nearby 1T, Wood Green/N22 and Edmonton/N9 gangs.  They beef OFB, NPK, N15, TPL/DC8, Hornsey/V8 and Finchley/197.<br><br>Associated Rappers} BM / Mini / Sava]]></description>
