      <Placemark>
        <name>⚫240</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X5hV6qxX2YS2k-e3vipm9erHgNohcYSBhL_lUwewNI3zdnUjLSh_z2DaBZ5JedZVIcwJShtPDQAYA2DY-gLxnDrfsXNqNanG5rkulwwkJoy9VOlyIOS7nBioRnTWuF1PaPxJ44yfnK9XTmr2RZbY7u6h9QBoGZ7rKKdp4nrZ88IWfZfK3iGc-pHpKqZVQC_3T6RU7VsYonglVSuOU57Vtx6qs33eYKEl97fT2vkjfsaZBBm?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Haringey, South Tottenham N15<br><br>RMT240 are a street gang who are based around the South Tottenham area, within the N15 / N17 postcodes. They are most active on the Chestnut estate, and the Imperial Wharf estate around Craven Park Road. The Chestnut estate gang used to be known as the 'Chestnut Black Gang' (CE) and the current generations also identify with the colour black. They are just one of over a dozen smaller street gangs located in the Tottenham area that identify with their local estates and small blocks in N15 and N17. Chestnut first emerged as an independent gang during the mid 2000s after the break ups of larger alliances like the Tottenham Mandem (TMD). They tend to be allied with other Tottenham sets against the rival gangs from Wood Green and Edmonton.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Millz / MK / MA / Weezy]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-000000-2684-122</styleUrl>
