      <Placemark>
        <name>🔴🟡Cally Road

https://web.archive.org/web/20120413233631/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/north-london-gangs/cally-road-gang</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X5v66g5sLekHQT11xg2QIekN3rpVARbHg63eWGs33jOUlCCHYVCRGpyDQGmp5IH53I4Eqo32sLxBoaLhnM1_IeOj-jZfZ-0LGcpAj9y9lxewYI4t1gX_03v2RAdWA_66DyAsV3YfQD2jJYllIjWb1nt4LdyLBBN4UH3YTC73lrZsn-jx8R7TQsZLyGVLl8l-5UgyWmGG7tb21ozIoUhaPJAdqRE7PR2ngcP0T2ATilRokHt?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Islington, Caledonian Road N1<br><br>Cally Road (CR), also known as the 'Cally Boys', or the 'Cally Boyz', are a street gang who are based on the estates along Caledonian Road in Islington, within the N1 postcode. They are mostly active on Bemerton, Barnsbury and Priory Green estates. The street gangs have been present in the area for many years, often taking their names directly from the local estates, such as the 'Bemerton Boys', or the later 'Bemerton Mandem'. During 2007/2008 Cally began to identify with the colour yellow. During this period some Cally olders began to operate on the Crouch Hall Court estate located in the north of the borough forming Crouch Hall Court (CHC) gang. They now identify with the colour red like their closest allies from Essex Road and Hoxton.  They are allied with Hoxton, Essex Road, Holly Street, Homerton and NRB. Their main rivals are EC1, Red Pitch, London Fields, Elthorne, Peckwater, Queens Crescent, Cumbo, New Orleans and Andover.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Loose CR / Rashy / SB / CR1 / Y.Loose]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-FF5252-2485-120</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
