      <Placemark>
        <name>ELT / Busy Block

https://web.archive.org/web/20110607000153/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/north-london-gangs/busy-blocks</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X7xB6sa_aFuXxgHWUZZdwc2W_adiuLcbRLrb7X5pXEseRph3f_JEyGFCXp2C12DbWzPe-BiPQPE0G8QPsaEPWzt2nYWaxzK0ufl5Z2KGQjubJsk1DjYp4L_QI2_ARpYUl8OcpLS-S3RvL3C0CkVKu5CtcIwkA40P7BumNUXDM7PNN4JX_JD1fkOEPzjJIX5OUqRTuu4KgnxYx5jgPtD51iquiyaqRlQ8BrIXx627gW_Un8h?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Islington, Archway N19<br><br>Busy Block are a large street gang based on several estates in the Archway area in the north of Islington, within the N19 postcode. Busy Block are based between Hornsey Rise and Archway Road particularly on the Elthorne and New Orleans Rise estates.  They were formed in the mid 1990s, although originally they had no official name and were just referred to as the 'Archway Mandem' and 'Elthorne Mandem' with some olders being part of the "Shell Town" alliance, formed on the Sandlings estate, in nearby Wood Green. It was not until the early 2000s that the Busy Block name really became official. They identify with the colour red and Busy Block are referred to as "Blood Blocks", or "Busy Blocks".<br><br>Busy Block are now the older generation. They were at their peak during the 2000s and early 2010s. They had close ties with gangs from the Tottenham, Hornsey, Cally Road, Essex Road, Finchley, Manor House and Stamford Hill areas. They had came into conflict with Andover, Wray Kray, Crouch Hall Court and Wood Green. By the mid 2010s many of the Busy Block members were serving prison sentences and the new younger generations are now more fragmented as they have split into Elthorne (ELT), New Orleans (NOL) and the A-Team (Miranda estate).<br><br>Their historical alliances and old rivalries have since shifted through these new generations. ELT / NOL have blessed the beefs with Andover, Wray Kray and Crouch Hall Court, whilst coming into conflict with former allies Cally Road and Essex Road. A-Team are a small set who have ties with Busy Block olders and have inherited many of the original allies and old rivals of Busy Block and now beef with ELT / NOL. ELT / NOL are allied with nearby Andover, Crouch Hall Court, Wray Kray, EC1, Queens Crescent, Peckwater and Cumbo. Those gangs now beef A-Team, Essex Road, Cally Road and NRB. A-Team are allies to the OFB, Essex Road, Cally Road, Hoxton, Active Gxng, NRB, FSG and CT1 gangs.  They now beef with nearby Elthorne, New Orleans, Queens Crescent, Peckwater, Cumbo and Wood Green/N22.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Cheekz (ELT) / Jordy (ELT) / 8th Ball / Future / JR / Vipex / G.B / Ghetto / Miller Matic / Ousier Tom]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-FF5252-2485-115</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X7xB6sa_aFuXxgHWUZZdwc2W_adiuLcbRLrb7X5pXEseRph3f_JEyGFCXp2C12DbWzPe-BiPQPE0G8QPsaEPWzt2nYWaxzK0ufl5Z2KGQjubJsk1DjYp4L_QI2_ARpYUl8OcpLS-S3RvL3C0CkVKu5CtcIwkA40P7BumNUXDM7PNN4JX_JD1fkOEPzjJIX5OUqRTuu4KgnxYx5jgPtD51iquiyaqRlQ8BrIXx627gW_Un8h?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
