      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Stoke Newington / Stokey16 / Nightingale</name>
        <description><![CDATA[London Borough of Hackney, Clapton E5<br><br>Stokey16 are a large street gang who are based around the Stoke Newington area, within the N16 postcode. The Stoke Newington gang are active on the Lordship North, Lordship South, Hillcourt, Smalley and Rectory estates (N16) and the Nightingale estate in nearby Clapton (E5). The gang are the younger Stoke Newington generation who have followed on from the older 'Lordship Boys' (L.O.R.D) and the 'Legends of Stokey' (LOS) divided between Smalley and Rectory estates.<br><br>The 'Lordship Boys' have been established since the 1990s, and are now an older generation. 'Lordship Boys' main base is Lordship South estate but also occupy the Lordship North and Hillcourt estates. 'Lordship Boys' also have an influence over the nearby Smalley and Rectory estates who combined had formed a new street gang known as 'Legends of Stokey' (LOS) between 2003 to 2007. The 'Legends of Stokey' (LOS) made their reputation carrying out robberies in the area and quickly acquired rivalries on all sides, including the Mothers Square, Stamford Hill and Manor House gangs. By 2006 the gangs numbers had soon dwindled following pressure from Stamford Hill and Manor House. A number of the prominent members from Stoke Newington also went to prison, whilst their younger generations from 2007/08 onward have fallen under the Lordship, Smalley and Rectory gangs. The current youngest generations from these three areas, as well as the Nightingale estate, combined make up the larger "Stokey16" gang also known as simply as 'Stokey', or 'Stoke Newington'<br><br>Their main allies are London Fields, A-Road and Red Pitch. They beef nearby Manor House, Stamford Hill, Holly Street, Pembury, Homerton and Hoxton.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Yargz / Diablo / L'zz / Ra$hy / T16]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-000000-2601-77</styleUrl>
        <Polygon>
          <outerBoundaryIs>
            <LinearRing>
              <tessellate>1</tessellate>
              <coordinates>
                -0.0636864,51.5585433,0
                -0.0653601,51.5560352,0
                -0.0654674,51.5555149,0
                -0.0587511,51.5556483,0
                -0.0591159,51.5582765,0
                -0.0636864,51.5585433,0
              </coordinates>
            </LinearRing>
          </outerBoundaryIs>
        </Polygon>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>🔴Pembury

https://web.archive.org/web/20110417121105/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/east-london-gangs/pembury-boys</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X5nnPp8H-9bfxrPi4uZllQgdFYg4k6wXTkQXWVpbOHkqpUK5TolS8kAj5TeNyNUKfmm0LsGFzv2XZXAJeqX7Z1xrRg7f4fKQgLJp6IQBGnGuveaa5N6XBqlkJRYOtICUZJyTXl3UdHD0M6wj9HxSioPIrXL4LmYh0R4vuDOeea_UCVAVxMXDQphfDlQqihavXAUQhY?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Hackney, Hackney E5<br><br>The Pembury Boys are a street gang based on the Pembury estate in Hackney, within the E5 postcode.  Pembury had at one time originally been part of the 'Hackney Boys', until the early 2000s. The 'Hackney Boys' group were centred around London Fields, but had members across much of the E5, E8 and E9 postcodes and had serious beef with the 'Tottenham Mandem' (TMD) between 1996-2003.  During the late 1990s up to the mid 2000s, numerous large gangs in London, such as the 'Hackney Boys', sub-divided into many local estate, or smaller area based sets, often spearheaded by new younger (and more populous) generations. The current younger sets generation are known as 'DABURY'.<br><br>During the 1990s and early 2000s the Pembury Boys part of the larger 'Hackney Boys' gang. They had once been closely affiliated with now rivals the London Fields Boys. Both were bourne out of the 'Hackney Boys' and were affiliated up until the mid 2000s. Pembury formed part of the "925" (E9 to E5) allegiance largely composed of Pembury (E5) and Ballance Road (E9). The alliance was formed in early 2007 known as E9 to E5 often shortened as '925' or 'NTF'. The '925' alliance identified with purple bandanas although now more recently have been identified with red bandanas. The alliance began with Ballance and Gilpin Square, but included other parts of E5 including Pembury. Pembury were once allies to London Fields who have a historic rivalry with parts of E9. When the London Fields area became closely allied with nearby Gilpin Square the old '925' identity was strengthened and involved predominantly Ballance and Pembury,  with Kingshold Boys closely allied.<br><br>The gang are allied with Homerton, Kingshold, Holly Street, Hoxton and Mothers Square. Pembury beef nearby London Fields, Stoke Newington, Gilpin Square, A-Road, Mountford, Red Pitch, Kingsmead and the Soldiers of Shakespeare.<br><br>Associated Rappers} KB / 7Bellz / Remma / MB / Tambo / Coinz / Nut Nut / Free / Rawz Artilla]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-FF5252-2701-117</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X5nnPp8H-9bfxrPi4uZllQgdFYg4k6wXTkQXWVpbOHkqpUK5TolS8kAj5TeNyNUKfmm0LsGFzv2XZXAJeqX7Z1xrRg7f4fKQgLJp6IQBGnGuveaa5N6XBqlkJRYOtICUZJyTXl3UdHD0M6wj9HxSioPIrXL4LmYh0R4vuDOeea_UCVAVxMXDQphfDlQqihavXAUQhY?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
          </Data>
