      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[🟢Drive & Marlowe (GMB)]]></name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X4pX4uIt3T_EpI5U2pSMu5aHJmZFDf_CcFhBM7512JicbaX2bPrJQ9hsSvO3nq10CwhizQvqZqdPFPTZ6VydMO_KEUCRFy2Ha6Qo2SSaVR3yg1Na9tVvVKKeDgm6v3Cb26rEZcJyUO1djl5nvItYLYlZ-3zR0WY44CRXNHb2hdJL_moaTdIpm4bP0fL73SmhGh7TsY?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Waltham Forest, Walthamstow E17<br><br>Drive & Marlowe (DM), sometimes known simply as 'Drive' or GMB are a street gang based on the Drive and Marlowe Road estates in Walthamstow, within the E17 postcode. Their gang abbreviation DM is known to stand for both 'Drive & Marlowe' and 'Doe Makers'.  They had once been closely affiliated with Beaumont, Boundary and Coppermill, forming a 'Green Gang' link up. They are now allied with the Mali Strip, Boundary and Coppermill gangs. They beef with the Chinghall, Priory Court, Selrack, Beaumont and Loyal Soldiers gangs.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Tal£nt / YK]]></description>
