      <Placemark>
        <name>🔴Chinghall / Ching Block (COS)</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X77ZDt4zAgp1uPd1kyYWOf7mB3BfqeLjuMUh6fVPAc6X0Cf-NdoAJkWpaWFM-fPUavBZykIOo5Jc3JUQr2rSzYBGjOxJ64h27vQqfjCjFqtQ_1YcE7PsPaTo8qpaEvBMPpbRr26_QYm81PqO2-PSFchVrwTWIecdZznGNpSitwWITeasqa26opghqU8kebOL8nhgDg?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Waltham Forest, Chingford E4<br><br>The Chingford Hall gang have been known by names such as 'ChingHall', 'Ching Block' and 'Ching On Sight' (COS). They are most active on the Chingford Hall estate, but in the past have been active on other blocks of Chingford like 'Hatch' and Peel Close known locally as 'P-Block'. During the 2000s Chingford were part of the 'Piff City' group along with affiliates OC from Leyton. 'Piff City' had identified with the colour of red and the Chingford factions were known as RBG (Red Bandana Gang). They are allied with Ferry Lane and 8th. They beef with Priory Court, Drive & Marlowe, Selrack, Mali Strip and Edmonton/N9.]]></description>
