      <Placemark>
        <name>⚫SJ / Mali Strip</name>
        <description><![CDATA[London Borough of Waltham Forest, Walthamstow E17<br><br>Mali Strip, often referred to by the media as the Mali Boys, are a large gang based around Leyton, particularly on Leyton High Road, although they are also located in Walthamstow, notably around St James Street.  The gangs elders are predominantly Somali, but younger members are from a range of ethnicities. Mali Strip formed around 2015/2016 absorbing several small local street gangs, and also members from the larger already established street gangs in the borough. They lead the newer economically-driven operating model of street gangs and are less interested in traditional postcode rivalries, unless it is to protect their drugs market.  They are heavily involved in drug supply and have earned the reputation as a violent and much feared group in the borough. Mali Strip are allied with Drive & Marlowe, Boundary, Coppermill and Shrublands. They beef Beaumont, Priory Court, Chinghall, Stoneydown and BHR.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Richi / Ridla / Rondo Montana]]></description>
