      <Placemark>
        <name>⚫Beckton / 6th / ACG

https://web.archive.org/web/20120309003730/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/east-london-gangs/beckton-black-gang</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X6qPBEixnVwSY0roIvGdsHbIIv9Ld8PRe4Zctgb4WhA8CLBEGqHuOJ2fThXNyapeOM-AZRqqI61IsDtlwLF_lzwCFdh0G8BSY4Z-rbbsY-tC-FUFIJYnXPjy3dxgn0noS9iXEOwhgm2YVsU6EJbubxfIIgnZAvVDHRzrSt6KCzDiOgjUx_5MDsQlQGaqnrom_FECF4?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Newham, Beckton E6<br><br>Beckton (6th) are a large street gang from the Beckton area within the E6 postcode, known as both 'Trap 6' and 6th. The current generation are known as ACG (Anyone Can Go) and 6th. The Beckton gang identify with the colour of black, and have developed since 2005/2006. A number of gang names have been used by members in the area, which have shifted through the younger generations. The gang names included 'Beckton Souljahs', 'Beckton Black Squad' (BBS) and 'Harder Than Most' (HTM). They are based throughout Beckton with notable areas of activity around Savage Gardens estate, the Cyprus and Windsor Park estates and the new build estates north and south of Tollgate Road. Beckton gangs have been known to recruit younger members from the nearby Barking and Dagenham areas, as well as locally in Beckton and East Ham.<br><br>The 'Beckton Black Squad' (sometimes abbreviated as BBS or BKT for Beckton) are a relatively new gang that have now developed from numerous earlier cliques in the area  (since 2005/2006). The gang first came to notice as a group when much of their activity was linked to the Windsor Park estate. During the late 2000s and early 2010s Beckton gang were in conflict with their now allies from the nearby Custom House and Canning Town areas. During the mid 2010s new current alliances and rivalries within Newham began to form, which has resulted in Newham borough being divided between the 'Northside Newham' (NSN) and 'Southside Newham' (SSN).<br><br>Beckton are a part of 'Southside Newham' (SSN) with their nearby allies Custom House and Canning Town. They beef with 7th, CGE, M15, 15th and Manor Park from 'Northside Newham' (NSN).<br><br>Associated Rappers} Young Dizz / Twin S / Trapz / Castro / Striker / Double M / Ryda / Lil Sav / StrikeDat / Bankz / H Youngz]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-000000-2701-117</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X6qPBEixnVwSY0roIvGdsHbIIv9Ld8PRe4Zctgb4WhA8CLBEGqHuOJ2fThXNyapeOM-AZRqqI61IsDtlwLF_lzwCFdh0G8BSY4Z-rbbsY-tC-FUFIJYnXPjy3dxgn0noS9iXEOwhgm2YVsU6EJbubxfIIgnZAvVDHRzrSt6KCzDiOgjUx_5MDsQlQGaqnrom_FECF4?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
