      <Placemark>
        <name>🟢Beaumont (LGR)</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X6xXjyUO2n8SnWfF9JPn0lIBYnwXskew6_OhDg38f44L0ko-PAxnsEKPtA1DWnU2L9PMOIzWqIeFW6Zt_6A1fudsuPudvy93xmKRHz1NyvWU6-yRm7wpoht84bor0iUqjLX0hdXV0IGXI1qLx_0ypF--pjXtTU1zn2-8HhXRCRi8ETO3MuUfhGf3pCRWB0fHDPrl_U?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Waltham Forest, Leyton E10<br><br>Beaumont Crew are a large street gang who are based on the Beaumont estate in Leyton, within the E10 postcode. They are one of the oldest and most reputed gangs in the borough who date back to the early 1990s. The gang had once been closely allied with Boundary, Coppermill and Drive & Marlowe forming a 'Green Gang' alliance. The current generations are known as LGR, which can stand for 'Let's Get Rich', Leyton Green Riders' and 'Leyton Green Road'. They beef with OC, Mali Strip and Drive & Marlowe. <br><br>Associated Rappers} Ds]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-7CB342-2501-77</styleUrl>
