      <Placemark>
        <name>A-Road

https://web.archive.org/web/20120115084405/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/east-london-gangs/a---road-evelyn-court</name>
        <description><![CDATA[London Borough of Hackney, Hackney E8<br><br>A-Road are a street gang located around Amhurst Road, on both the Amhurst Road and nearby Evelyn Court estates in Hackney within the E8 postcode. A-Road have been around since at least 2003/2004, although like many other areas of Hackney gangs have been present for some time as smaller estate gangs began to develop following the break down of the larger alliances, such as the 'Hackney Boys', in the early 2000s.<br><br>A-Road are one of many Hackney gangs that are linked with the London Fields Boys. Like their allies London Fields Boys A-Road share a rivalry with Holly Street. Their main allies are London Fields, Hindle House, and remnants of the "Legends of Stokey" (now divided amongst Smalley and Rectory). The gangs within the London Fields group, including A-Road, are closely linked with organised drug traffickers amongst older members, and this includes links to criminals outside of the London area.<br><br>They are allied with London Fields, Mountford, Hindle House and Stoke Newington.  They beef Holly Street, Manor House, Stamford Hill, Pembury, Homerton and Kingshold.]]></description>
