      <Placemark>
        <name>⚫Mothers Square</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X7VCANaUMTovCpaJZEO2cacSKpTbAF2R5ZJqfTeJq56kvoY_GrZweimGleB8GjoXXgagZTQ6TXc5tDot28hFdfiYFSi1O7QDThhARWw74F4C6rDeodtIDO82tWwueZ8JvwKrEn1ZiNYU9lvarW3_Fw0ZJOTkuu77szA5lRal181h8ip5Nv3ibK38T6EAUd-n_ygeTI?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Hackney, Clapton E5<br><br>Mothers Square are a small street gang who are based on the Mothers Square estate in the Clapton area of Hackney, within the E5 postcode. The 'Mothers Square Boys' had been around since the 1990s.  The gang formed part of the 'Hackney Boys' gang in the 1990s and early 2000s,  before the estate became more associated with 'E5TH Rydaz' in the 2000s. The Mothers Square area have been known to identify with the colour black and have been allied with Pembury and Harts Lane. They beef Mountford, Stoke Newington and from further afield ilford.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-000000-2501-120</styleUrl>
