      <Placemark>
        <name>🔵Gilpin Square

https://web.archive.org/web/20110531001451/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/east-london-gangs/gilpin-money-gang

https://web.archive.org/web/20111230003029/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/east-london-gangs/e5th-rydaz</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X5w7I-NGncKAcBEx8RtZY-Gkf0WRoyf3GOLsjEXpa_4yVeg_8afh5HPym1tJVsbBwMqRCoLwlalBFrAWlH04kh09iXV5NumMIqj14e3A7qIh0S6Auv-IzL4Le_jRhopwHfNqBcVZMa0xSKBJCAOPnfw6UoVxbBX1_GtZd9ciF7M7BSn7m6licYHqFXgSYjzYHc55LQ?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Hackney, Clapton E5<br><br>Gilpin Square Gang, originally known as 'Gilpin Square Boys' before becoming known as 'Gilpin Money Gang' (GMG), are a street gang based around Gilpin Square, on Clapton Park, Millfields and Nye Bevan estates within the Clapton area of Hackney, within the E5 postcode. 'Gilpin Square' are one of the 'Square Blocks' alongside Clapton Square and Mothers Square. They have close links with the London Fields Boys. Historically Fields have had members who were associated with Square. The 'Gilpin Square Boys' arose around 2005 as a younger generation that followed on from the E5th Rydaz. <br><br>The E5th Rydaz were located throughout the Lower Clapton, Clapton Park and “Murder Mile” area, situated within the E5 postcode. E5th Rydaz initially covered a large area between "Lea Bridge Road to the north",  "Clarence Road to the west", "Hackney marshes to the east" and "Homerton to the south" Within this area lie a number of estates, some of which are home to smaller gangs. Those estates included Nye Bevan, Clapton Park, Clapton Square and Mothers Square,   as well as the nearby Pembury and Nightingale estates. E5th Rydaz have been around since the 1980s, although did not use the name until the late 1990s, and have a number of associated sets that have since arisen within their territory, such as the 'Square Blocks' of Gilpin Square, Clapton Square and nearby Mothers Square. The latter having originally been part of the 'Hackney Boys'.  E5th are predominantly composed of older members and more akin to an organised "Firm". Historically E5th had conflicts with Holly Street and older 'Stratford' and 'Plaistow Boys', which resulted in several murders. Currently "Square Blocks", of Gilpin and Clapton, have a close alliance with London Fields.<br><br>Their main allies are London Fields. They beef with nearby Southwold, Springfield, Homerton, Kingshold, Holly Street and Pembury.<br><br>Associated Rappers} K Man]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-3949AB-2401-77</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X5w7I-NGncKAcBEx8RtZY-Gkf0WRoyf3GOLsjEXpa_4yVeg_8afh5HPym1tJVsbBwMqRCoLwlalBFrAWlH04kh09iXV5NumMIqj14e3A7qIh0S6Auv-IzL4Le_jRhopwHfNqBcVZMa0xSKBJCAOPnfw6UoVxbBX1_GtZd9ciF7M7BSn7m6licYHqFXgSYjzYHc55LQ?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
