      <Placemark>
        <name>🔴Kingshold</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X5bvBlfoRSwopkgafV0NpLOj1zVlZqwwl-3OZtc8rCy6v7uLJzx2lWRl6NkaKSf20hPIuPw-RJq7Pdk4XUpUz7OKKlLNdDJjVnHxAj_bqPut9xkDKOLvVvJP4Y3mFlSQn2nPbUuuBN6GQnLUGK2AiNrCx1R3HmWZ052nt_7tDCDOpuqy6wOXI8J71iEkUsMgI1KoXur?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Hackney, South Hackney E9<br><br>Kingshold are a small street gang based on the Kingshold estate in South Hackney, within the E9 postcode. They are closely affiliated with nearby Homerton and Pembury who together formed the 925 (E9 to E5) alliance during the late 2000s and the early 2010s. Kingshold also have close ties with Holly Street, Stamford Hill, Manor House and Hoxton, whilst they have conflict with nearby London Fields, Gilpin Square, A-Road, Stoke Newington and Kingsmead.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-FF5252-2501-122</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X5bvBlfoRSwopkgafV0NpLOj1zVlZqwwl-3OZtc8rCy6v7uLJzx2lWRl6NkaKSf20hPIuPw-RJq7Pdk4XUpUz7OKKlLNdDJjVnHxAj_bqPut9xkDKOLvVvJP4Y3mFlSQn2nPbUuuBN6GQnLUGK2AiNrCx1R3HmWZ052nt_7tDCDOpuqy6wOXI8J71iEkUsMgI1KoXur?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
