      <Placemark>
        <name>🔴Homerton / 98s</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X6F9tscmnAff7WqD6ezWRwAMwSIFeEazNS-hRfljkigUqmJ5pqyUQPZxcZue8PTI2_Wj8h_Q5D6Rc0LmFOrz0XHlq5aJ2-P38giQ8k9m8uoFaeeY99HHv1vfwSJAb7dRja8avnyVn8vGc17dKpp4jC6h5ft2NH1HXyPhpqPnIK6bvaWkyF_XvtKAwSQ7jLowDVdIHKK?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Hackney, Homerton E9<br><br>Homerton, known as the 'Niners' / '9iners', are a large street gang based in the Homerton area of Hackney, within the E9 postcode. They are mostly active around the Ballance Road, Well Street and Morning Lane areas on the Gascoyne, Wyke, Frampton Park and Jack Dunning estates, as well as nearby Homerton High Street blocks such as the Nisbet House and Banister House estates. They had initially identified with the colour purple, before switching to red to oppose rival gangs who identify with blue. They are ABG (Anti Blue Gang).<br><br>The gangs roots can be traced back to the 1990s when the 'Hackney Boys' were active. Although central to the London Fields area, 'Hackney Boys' had covered much of the E5, E8 and E9 postcodes, and drew members from the Well Street area (E9). The older Homerton generations from the 1990s to mid 2000s included the Well Street Boys, Graveyard Boys and Ballance Boys.<br><br>The current 'Niners' followed on from older Homerton gang sets, such as 'Certified Ballance Road' (CBR) also known as 'B-Block', or the 'Ballance Boys', and older 'Well Street Boys'. 'Ballance Road' (CBR) had formed part of the 925 (E9 to E5) allegiance largely composed of Pembury (E5) and Ballance Road (E9). The alliance was formed in early 2007 known as E9 to E5 often shortened as '925' or 'NTF'. The '925' alliance identified with purple bandanas although now more recently have been identified with red bandanas. The alliance began with Ballance and Gilpin Square, but included other parts of E5 including Pembury. Pembury were once allies to London Fields who have a historic rivalry with parts of E9. When the London Fields area became closely allied with nearby Gilpin Square the old '925' identity was strengthened and involved predominantly Ballance and Pembury, with Kingshold Boys closely allied. The current Niners now form a close alliance between Homerton and Holly Street referred to as the "98s" after the E9 postcode of Homerton and the E8 postcode of Holly Street.<br><br>'Homerton' are allied with Kingshold, Pembury, Holly Street, Hoxton, Stamford Hill and Manor House. Their main rivalry is with nearby London Fields, Stoke Newington, Kingsmead, Red Pitch, Gilpin Square, A-Road, Fellows Court and SOS.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Kay-O / V9 / Unknown T / Kemzi / Mtrappo / Skitz / Butcher / Kblacko]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-FF5252-2601-122</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X6F9tscmnAff7WqD6ezWRwAMwSIFeEazNS-hRfljkigUqmJ5pqyUQPZxcZue8PTI2_Wj8h_Q5D6Rc0LmFOrz0XHlq5aJ2-P38giQ8k9m8uoFaeeY99HHv1vfwSJAb7dRja8avnyVn8vGc17dKpp4jC6h5ft2NH1HXyPhpqPnIK6bvaWkyF_XvtKAwSQ7jLowDVdIHKK?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Polygon>
          <outerBoundaryIs>
            <LinearRing>
              <tessellate>1</tessellate>
              <coordinates>
                -0.0462658,51.5524045,0
                -0.0490982,51.5521109,0
