      <Placemark>
        <name>🔵London Fields / ZT

https://web.archive.org/web/20111231081438/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/east-london-gangs/london-field-boys

https://web.archive.org/web/20120115095011/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/east-london-gangs/hackney-boys-hakcney-mandem</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X6q5Y5Qxpg3KgQ6CIXtuuzDJFQeLDLm6mxM3tbvDd72jYisMcR9yr1nTC1_n4hGIZykA7vsp1h8dp60lnEcd5MZ5TdqgMkJV_anziEo60HqGVnJ2rIkFsWAljZV6dE3mXiCFhZxYfBeE27NwSn7sGWQVsBkePxztA3hVSWX6KhPh6QCT3qHy3cOXCaVG3v13TXSCt4?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Hackney, London Fields E8<br><br>The London Fields Boys (LF) are a large street gang who are based on estates situated around the London Fields area of Hackney within the E8 postcode. The gangs main territory is the estates adjoining the west side of the London Fields like the Blackstone, Fields and Morland estates. The area is also referred to as "Fields" and "Mashtown". The older generation of London Fields Boys are also known as 'Mashtown', whilst the current younger generation from the London Fields area are known as 'Zero Tolerance' (ZT).  They are also known as CSG (Chest Shot Gang).<br><br>The 'London Fields Boys' had originally made up the largest part of an older gang known as the 'Hackney Boys', up until the late 1990s and early 2000s. 'London Fields Boys' were a significant part of the 'Hackney Boys', and were most active in their rivalry with the 'Tottenham Mandem' (TMD) between 1996-2003. Although the 'Hackney Boys' were mainly drawn from London Fields they would also draw membership from estates around Hackney Downs, Haggerston and Well street covering the E5, E8 and E9 postcodes. By the late 2000s the older members of the 'London Fields Boys' / 'Hackney Boys' had began to move into music production forming their own group known as "Mashtown". The "Mashtown" group is also closely linked to the 'London Fields Boys' as were a younger generation known as 'Ride Out Squad' (ROS).<br><br>Following the Tottenham and Hackney gang wars of the late 1990s and early 2000s the younger generations formed new smaller gangs that had become disaggregated from the old larger gangs such as the 'Hackney Boys' and the 'Tottenham Mandem'. Whilst 'London Fields Boys' were descended from the 'Hackney Boys', their nearby rivals the 'Holly Street Boys' were descended from a group known as the 'Rowdy Bunch', and other nearby rivals 'Hoxton Boys' were descended from another group known as 'Love of Money' (LOM).  The rivalry between London Fields and Holly Street is one of the oldest and most reputed gang rivalries in the city having now been ongoing since the 1990s. There is still bitter rivalry between the older London Fields Boys and older Tottenham Mandem who were active in the Hackney and Tottenham conflict. On rare occasions the bitter personal disputes can still result in incidents. One occurred in 2009 at the Urban Music Awards which involved "Mashtown" (London Fields) and "NorthStar" (Tottenham) at the O2 Arena. 'Tottenham Mandem' leaders Clint 'C1' Ponton and 'Wes Lambie' of the "NorthStar" group were attacked with a champagne bottle during the event. It came as retaliation as they were accused of having gunned down the younger brother of "Mashtown" artist Margs. Over the years the historical Tottenham-Hackney gang wars have faded and the current younger generations from both areas London Fields (ZT) in Hackney and Broadwater Farm (OFB) in Tottenham are now loosely affiliated with each other.<br><br>London Fields are allied with EC1, Stoke Newington, A-Road, Mountford, Kingsmead, Gilpin Square, Red Pitch, and Hindle House, whilst the older generation also have links with other areas, such as the Wood Green, Edmonton, Stonebridge and South Kilburn areas. During the later 2000s into early 2010s the younger generation known as the Ride Out Squad (ROS) also had ties with Beckton and the E3 Bloods (Roman Road and Devons Road). Fields beef Holly Street, Hoxton, Fellows Court, Homerton, Kingshold, Pembury, Stamford Hill, Manor House, Essex Road and Cally Road.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Asco / Balistik / Latts / Dabz / Margs / J Spades / Kaos / Lzz / Scrilla / Dama / Mojo / T80 / 88]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-3949AB-2601-77</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
