      <Placemark>
        <name>🔴Holly Street / 98s

https://web.archive.org/web/20120103144948/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/east-london-gangs/holly-street-boys</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X5QDWF3xVvRw_iAz3QVfQFn3xfiL8SRx_OQbUKztQhnDsHgmAydiBVUEU0pQUNTMdqXbYoawQFUd-ERSBG0Hf0xIAHXsHI4J802abdpAABp8tPzee_r_E_09DLWvwd8ujHh_KiKrUYgw-GQ85ndCYdP1xXnnFOJRRRq7EE6G04GUrgAy8gT5dK0VjjsNtVxwHHBeN0g?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Hackney, Dalston E8<br><br>Holly Street Boys are based on the Holly Street estate in the Dalston area of Hackney, within the E8 postcode.  The Holly Street Boys have been around since the 1980s although the name has not necessarily been used in all that time. Before the Holly Street Boys became a modern household name in Hackney Holly Street Boys who had been close with youths from other areas of the borough,  such as Stoke Newington, were part of a gang known as the 'Rowdy Bunch'. A younger generation, known as the 'Junior Rowdy Bunch', would form the nucleus of the Holly Street Boys in the early 2000s.<br><br>The Holly Street Boys are one of the three largest and most influential gangs in the Borough of Hackney, with influence over a number of smaller newer established gangs, as well as links to other large street gangs both within London and beyond. Like some of the other main gangs in Hackney, like London Fields, large families and influential older members sit at the top. Holly Street Boys have identified with red and black colours during the mid 2000s. The current generation of Holly Street Boys are also known as "BGSG" (Bang Gang Stain Gang) They now form a close alliance with Homerton known as the "98s" after the E9 postcode of Homerton and E8 postcode of Holly Street.<br><br>Historically Holly Street have been affiliated with the 'Rowdy Bunch', and the 'Love of Money' (LOM) crew from Hoxton, as well as Fellows Court, Red Pitch, Homerton, Essex Road and Beaumont whilst they are known for their rivalry with nearby London Fields, A-Road and Gilpin Square. The deadly rivalry between Holly Street and London Fields is one of the oldest and most well renowned rivalries in London.  The two areas have now been in a conflict since the late 1990s as a follow up from the dislike between both 'Rowdy Bunch' and 'Junior Rowdy' members with the London Fields Boys. Their rivalry had been caused by a manslaughter which was committed years previously by a 'Junior Rowdy' member.<br><br>The Holly Street Boys are closely allied with nearby Hoxton, Homerton, Pembury, Kingshold, Essex Road, Cally Road and De Beauvoir. Their main rivals are nearby London Fields, but they also beef the EC1, Stoke Newington, A-Road, Red Pitch, Gilpin Square, Mountford and Kingsmead gangs, as well as having conflict with Fellows Court and Hindle House.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Hitman / DA / Billy Billions / PM]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-FF5252-2501-122</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value><![CDATA[https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X5QDWF3xVvRw_iAz3QVfQFn3xfiL8SRx_OQbUKztQhnDsHgmAydiBVUEU0pQUNTMdqXbYoawQFUd-ERSBG0Hf0xIAHXsHI4J802abdpAABp8tPzee_r_E_09DLWvwd8ujHh_KiKrUYgw-GQ85ndCYdP1xXnnFOJRRRq7EE6G04GUrgAy8gT5dK0VjjsNtVxwHHBeN0g?authuser=0&fife=s16383]]></value>
