      <Placemark>
        <name>⚪Custom House / CH / 16th

https://web.archive.org/web/20120207050536/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/east-london-gangs/custom-house-white-gang</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X7u5roBGjRXbZlys6dbX2v6rOigqbun71DTaolYsLbwPMVKXw_ZrndRlPyAmTt-aWYYI0BYabBVevH4dTfAJZvibDDTiDHSJcJxECKrRZKYKoxNq5Z_35KtNs7Z9tyKP0jfj-_xsY2zFmjPHDIM4QAUZkQ9ACQf0qR8cKYFzwpO68_BKfvE3LksF1qAKxTFnd32k9k?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Newham, Custom House E16<br><br>Custom House (CH) are a large street gang who are located in the Custom House and Canning Town area within the E16 postcode. The gang are mostly active on the estates around Freemasons Road and the area east of Prince Regents Lane which includes the estate around Nottingham Avenue which is made up of white buildings although Custom House draw members throughout the E16 postcode,  including the wider Canning Town area and North Woolwich area. They are also known as 'Hood 16', and '16th'. They identify with the colour white and were formerly the 'Custom House White Gang'. <br><br>Custom House has only since the later 2000s come to have an identifiable gang in terms of definers, such as colours or names, like the other parts of Newham. Custom House use the initials CH and identify with the colour white. CH can be interpreted as ‘Crime Hood’, ‘Certified Hustlers’ or simply as "Custom House". Custom House area has sometimes been regarded as the eastern part of Canning Town, however the link has been downplayed since the Victorian period, due to Canning Town’s poor image.  Historically the area has been swamped with known traditional 'old school' gangsters and infamous organised criminals.  The Freemasons estate has a long reputation of crime and disorder.<br><br>Custom House are a part of 'Southside Newham' (SSN) with the nearby allies Canning Town and Beckton. They beef with 7th, CGE, M15, 15th and Manor Park, in 'Northside Newham' (NSN).<br><br>Associated Rappers} Mover / G28 / Tony Blackz]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-000000-2401-41</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
