      <Placemark>
        <name>🟢CGE / Chadd Green

https://web.archive.org/web/20120228042140/http://sites.google.com/site/londonstreetgangs/gang-lists/east-london-gangs/stratford-plaistow-boys</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AL_Y2X4z6egjnzQHmqqDRajJe-n1yr3v2ZVsVEwH_s0Mx6dAOB29LJ5ag6KecdSc_iBf14CSIO6wONePunvaMMC_R4nFKWvzjASh0RsmVJFV-MpmJCucet48BIo1soK8436irohNDH_khshbHLoLrD8rEEoHrojL5nb8SQ0by8o4wnh0VLNTLUDjzpCaxvfUC0E-TYaGn90?authuser=0&fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>London Borough of Newham, Plaistow E13<br><br>Chadd Green (CGE) are a street gang who are based around the border of Plaistow and Stratford with their main territory being the Chadd Green estate, within the E13 postcode. The gang identify with the colour green. The older generations in Plaistow did not tend to use gang names, however some of the younger generations had used gang names. Some have developed from music crews, whilst others had been solely music crews, but nonetheless have been involved in violent rivalries. One early crew were the 'Boys in Da Hood' headed by Grime MC '"Crazy Titch". A younger generation known as 'Kids in da Hood' also existed. Other music groups that had come from around Stratford and Plaistow, included cliques such as 'Slew Dem Crew', 'Nasty Crew' and 'Collision Squad'. Another set who gained widespread attention and notoriety were the ‘Lords of Stratford’. A number of new rivalries and alliances have since been instigated through their following younger generations. For many years there have been close links between Stratford, Plaistow and Thatched House. The cliques that formed the “Stratford & Plaistow Boys” (the un-official name of the older generations) in recent years have gone by the names 'Stratford Bloodgang' or 'Blood City', but also by their local location, i.e. Carpenters (Dennison Point), Focus, 'Thatched House' and 'Chadd Green Estate'. They are allied with nearby 7th, 15th, M15 and Manor Park to form an alliance known as 'Northside Newham' (NSN). They beef the Custom House, Canning Town and Beckton areas who form a 'Southside Newham' (SSN) alliance.<br><br>Associated Rappers} Myers / S13 / TT / Mobz / MA]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#poly-7CB342-3001-77</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
