      <Placemark>
        <name>SYS / System</name>
        <description><![CDATA[London Borough of Barking & Dagenham, Dagenham RM10<br><br>The Dagenham area currently consists of several younger sets which had formed since the late 2010s throughout the RM8/RM9 and RM10 postcodes. These newer sets include, 'DAG/109', 'DAG/89', 'S17' and 'SYS/System'. These sets are the younger generations to the older Dagenham generation from the 2010s known as '8910', after the areas postcodes.<br><br>The first generation of modern day street gangs in the area were active during the 2000s and early 2010s. They were known as 'D.A.G' (Dagz Ardest Gang) often referred to a 'Dagenham White Gang' as they identified with the colour white. This generation were once allied with Custom House who also identified with the colour white. The Dagenham sets from that time included the "OSG" (Outskirt Gangsters) from Althorne Way on the Becontree Heath estate, "D-Ville" based around Dagenham Village and the 'Mardy/Hoodgang' based around Heathway and Millard Terrace. The younger generation active during the 2010s were known as '8910'. By the late 2010s the younger generation split into new smaller sets.<br><br>The main Dagenham set are known as 'DAG109' or simply '109'. They are active Throughout the RM9 and RM10 postcodes, particularly around the Heathway, Millard Terrace and Heath Park estates. They identify with the colour blue. They beef most gangs in the area including ASB, MTM, SYS, GBlock, TGB, CBT, Horrid Hill, RM/Romford, C17/GTM (Essex), NTG (Essex) and 268 (Essex).<br><br>The Becontree Heath estate, within the RM8 postcode is home to two sets known as 'DAG89' and 'S17'. These sets are based in the northern part of Dagenham within the RM8 and RM9 postcodes.<br><br>The Dagenham Village area, within the RM10 postcode, is home to a set known as 'SYS/System' who are based around Ibscott Close. They are allied with GBlock and ASB. They beef 109/Dagenham and CBT. <br><br>Associated Rappers} Butch]]></description>
